2855
2856static int regnarrate = 0;
2857#endif
2858
2859// Setup to parse the regexp. Used once to get the length and once to do it.
2860static void regcomp_start(uint8_t *expr, int re_flags) // see vim_regcomp()
2861{
2862 initchr((char *)expr);
2863 if (re_flags & RE_MAGIC1) {
2864 reg_magic = MAGIC_ON;
2865 } else {
2866 reg_magic = MAGIC_OFF;
2867 }
2868 reg_string = (re_flags & RE_STRING2);
2869 reg_strict = (re_flags & RE_STRICT4);
2870 get_cpo_flags();
2871
2872 num_complex_braces = 0;
2873 regnpar = 1;
2874 CLEAR_FIELD(had_endbrace)memset(&(had_endbrace), 0, sizeof(had_endbrace));
2875 regnzpar = 1;
2876 re_has_z = 0;
2877 regsize = 0L;
2878 reg_toolong = false0;
2879 regflags = 0;
2880 had_eol = false0;
2881}
2882
2883// Return true if MULTIBYTECODE should be used instead of EXACTLY for
2884// character "c".
2885static bool_Bool use_multibytecode(int c)
2886{
2887 return utf_char2len(c) > 1
2888 && (re_multi_type(peekchr()) != NOT_MULTI0
2889 || utf_iscomposing(c));
2890}
2891
2892// Emit (if appropriate) a byte of code
2893static void regc(int b)
2894{
2895 if (regcode == JUST_CALC_SIZE((uint8_t *)-1)) {
2896 regsize++;
2897 } else {
2898 *regcode++ = (uint8_t)b;
2899 }
2900}
2901
2902// Emit (if appropriate) a multi-byte character of code
2903static void regmbc(int c)
2904{
2905 if (regcode == JUST_CALC_SIZE((uint8_t *)-1)) {
2906 regsize += utf_char2len(c);
2907 } else {
2908 regcode += utf_char2bytes(c, (char *)regcode);
2909 }
2910}

3882
3883// Emit a node.
3884// Return pointer to generated code.
3885static uint8_t *regnode(int op)
3886{
3887 uint8_t *ret;
3888
3889 ret = regcode;
3890 if (ret == JUST_CALC_SIZE((uint8_t *)-1)) {
3891 regsize += 3;
3892 } else {
3893 *regcode++ = (uint8_t)op;
3894 *regcode++ = NUL'\000'; // Null "next" pointer.
3895 *regcode++ = NUL'\000';
3896 }
3897 return ret;
3898}
3899
3900// Write a four bytes number at "p" and return pointer to the next char.
3901static uint8_t *re_put_uint32(uint8_t *p, uint32_t val)
3902{
3903 *p++ = (uint8_t)((val >> 24) & 0377);
3904 *p++ = (uint8_t)((val >> 16) & 0377);
3905 *p++ = (uint8_t)((val >> 8) & 0377);
3906 *p++ = (uint8_t)(val & 0377);
3907 return p;
3908}
3909
3910// regnext - dig the "next" pointer out of a node
3911// Returns NULL when calculating size, when there is no next item and when
3912// there is an error.
3913static uint8_t *regnext(uint8_t *p)
3914 FUNC_ATTR_NONNULL_ALL
3915{
3916 int offset;
3917
3918 if (p == JUST_CALC_SIZE((uint8_t *)-1) || reg_toolong) {
3919 return NULL((void*)0);
3920 }
3921
3922 offset = NEXT(p)(((*((p) + 1) & 0377) << 8) + (*((p) + 2) & 0377
));
3923 if (offset == 0) {
3924 return NULL((void*)0);
3925 }
3926
3927 if (OP(p)((int)(*(p))) == BACK4) {
3928 return p - offset;
3929 } else {
3930 return p + offset;
3931 }
3932}
3933
3934// Set the next-pointer at the end of a node chain.
3935static void regtail(uint8_t *p, const uint8_t *val)
3936{
3937 int offset;
3938
3939 if (p == JUST_CALC_SIZE((uint8_t *)-1)) {
3940 return;
3941 }
3942
3943 // Find last node.
3944 uint8_t *scan = p;
3945 while (true1) {
3946 uint8_t *temp = regnext(scan);
3947 if (temp == NULL((void*)0)) {
3948 break;
3949 }
3950 scan = temp;
3951 }
3952
3953 if (OP(scan)((int)(*(scan))) == BACK4) {
3954 offset = (int)(scan - val);
3955 } else {
3956 offset = (int)(val - scan);
3957 }
3958 // When the offset uses more than 16 bits it can no longer fit in the two
3959 // bytes available. Use a global flag to avoid having to check return
3960 // values in too many places.
3961 if (offset > 0xffff) {
3962 reg_toolong = true1;
3963 } else {
3964 *(scan + 1) = (uint8_t)(((unsigned)offset >> 8) & 0377);
3965 *(scan + 2) = (uint8_t)(offset & 0377);
3966 }
3967}
3968
3969// Like regtail, on item after a BRANCH; nop if none.
3970static void regoptail(uint8_t *p, uint8_t *val)
3971{
3972 // When op is neither BRANCH nor BRACE_COMPLEX0-9, it is "operandless"
3973 if (p == NULL((void*)0) || p == JUST_CALC_SIZE((uint8_t *)-1)
3974 || (OP(p)((int)(*(p))) != BRANCH3
3975 && (OP(p)((int)(*(p))) < BRACE_COMPLEX140 || OP(p)((int)(*(p))) > BRACE_COMPLEX140 + 9))) {
3976 return;
3977 }
3978 regtail(OPERAND(p)((p) + 3), val);
3979}
3980
3981// Insert an operator in front of already-emitted operand
3982//
3983// Means relocating the operand.
3984static void reginsert(int op, uint8_t *opnd)
3985{
3986 uint8_t *src;
3987 uint8_t *dst;
3988 uint8_t *place;
3989
3990 if (regcode == JUST_CALC_SIZE((uint8_t *)-1)) {
3991 regsize += 3;
3992 return;
3993 }
3994 src = regcode;
3995 regcode += 3;
3996 dst = regcode;
3997 while (src > opnd) {
3998 *--dst = *--src;
3999 }
4000
4001 place = opnd; // Op node, where operand used to be.
4002 *place++ = (uint8_t)op;
4003 *place++ = NUL'\000';
4004 *place = NUL'\000';
4005}

4027 *place++ = (uint8_t)op;
4028 *place++ = NUL'\000';
4029 *place++ = NUL'\000';
4030 assert(val >= 0 && (uintmax_t)val <= UINT32_MAX)((void) sizeof ((val >= 0 && (uintmax_t)val <= (
4294967295U)) ? 1 : 0), __extension__ ({ if (val >= 0 &&

4066/// Return true if the back reference is legal. We must have seen the close
4067/// brace.
4068/// TODO(vim): Should also check that we don't refer to something repeated
4069/// (+*=): what instance of the repetition should we match?
4070static int seen_endbrace(int refnum)
4071{
4072 if (!had_endbrace[refnum]) {
4073 uint8_t *p;
4074
4075 // Trick: check if "@<=" or "@<!" follows, in which case
4076 // the \1 can appear before the referenced match.
4077 for (p = (uint8_t *)regparse; *p != NUL'\000'; p++) {
4078 if (p[0] == '@' && p[1] == '<' && (p[2] == '!' || p[2] == '=')) {
4079 break;
4080 }
4081 }
4082
4083 if (*p == NUL'\000') {
4084 emsg(_("E65: Illegal back reference")gettext("E65: Illegal back reference"));
4085 rc_did_emsg = true1;
4086 return false0;
4087 }
4088 }
4089 return true1;
4090}

4092// Parse the lowest level.
4093//
4094// Optimization: gobbles an entire sequence of ordinary characters so that
4095// it can turn them into a single node, which is smaller to store and
4096// faster to run. Don't do this when one_exactly is set.

4171 case Magic('H')((int)('H') - 256):
4172 case Magic('a')((int)('a') - 256):
4173 case Magic('A')((int)('A') - 256):
4174 case Magic('l')((int)('l') - 256):

4508 } else if ((c == 'l' || c == 'c' || c == 'v') && (cur || got_digit)) {
4509 if (cur && n) {
4510 semsg(_(e_regexp_number_after_dot_pos_search_chr)gettext(e_regexp_number_after_dot_pos_search_chr), no_Magic(c));
4511 rc_did_emsg = true1;
4512 return NULL((void*)0);
4513 }
4514 if (c == 'l') {
4515 if (cur) {
4516 n = (uint32_t)curwin->w_cursor.lnum;
4517 }
4518 ret = regnode(RE_LNUM204);
4519 if (save_prev_at_start) {
4520 at_start = true1;
4521 }
4522 } else if (c == 'c') {
4523 if (cur) {
4524 n = (uint32_t)curwin->w_cursor.col;
4525 n++;
4526 }
4527 ret = regnode(RE_COL205);
4528 } else {
4529 if (cur) {
4530 colnr_T vcol = 0;
4531 getvvcol(curwin, &curwin->w_cursor, NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0), &vcol);
4532 n = (uint32_t)(++vcol);
4533 }
4534 ret = regnode(RE_VCOL206);
4535 }
4536 if (ret == JUST_CALC_SIZE((uint8_t *)-1)) {
4537 regsize += 5;
4538 } else {
4539 // put the number and the optional
4540 // comparator after the opcode
4541 regcode = re_put_uint32(regcode, n);
4542 *regcode++ = (uint8_t)cmp;
4543 }
4544 break;
4545 }
4546 }
4547
4548 EMSG2_RET_NULL(_("E71: Invalid character after %s%%"),return (semsg((gettext("E71: Invalid character after %s%%")),
(reg_magic == MAGIC_ALL) ? "" : "\\"), rc_did_emsg = 1, (void
*)((void*)0))
4549 reg_magic == MAGIC_ALL)return (semsg((gettext("E71: Invalid character after %s%%")),
(reg_magic == MAGIC_ALL) ? "" : "\\"), rc_did_emsg = 1, (void
*)((void*)0));
4550 }
4551 break;
4552
4553 case Magic('[')((int)('[') - 256):
4554collection:
4555 {
4556 uint8_t *lp;
4557
4558 // If there is no matching ']', we assume the '[' is a normal
4559 // character. This makes 'incsearch' and ":help [" work.
4560 lp = (uint8_t *)skip_anyof(regparse);
4561 if (*lp == ']') { // there is a matching ']'
4562 int startc = -1; // > 0 when next '-' is a range
4563 int endc;
4564
4565 // In a character class, different parsing rules apply.
4566 // Not even \ is special anymore, nothing is.
4567 if (*regparse == '^') { // Complement of range.
4568 ret = regnode(ANYBUT22 + extra);
4569 regparse++;
4570 } else {
4571 ret = regnode(ANYOF21 + extra);
4572 }
4573
4574 // At the start ']' and '-' mean the literal character.
4575 if (*regparse == ']' || *regparse == '-') {
4576 startc = (uint8_t)(*regparse);
4577 regc(*regparse++);
4578 }
4579
4580 while (*regparse != NUL'\000' && *regparse != ']') {
4581 if (*regparse == '-') {
4582 regparse++;
4583 // The '-' is not used for a range at the end and
4584 // after or before a '\n'.
4585 if (*regparse == ']' || *regparse == NUL'\000'
4586 || startc == -1
4587 || (regparse[0] == '\\' && regparse[1] == 'n')) {
4588 regc('-');
4589 startc = '-'; // [--x] is a range
4590 } else {
4591 // Also accept "a-[.z.]"
4592 endc = 0;
4593 if (*regparse == '[') {
4594 endc = get_coll_element(&regparse);
4595 }
4596 if (endc == 0) {
4597 endc = mb_ptr2char_adv((const char **)&regparse);
4598 }
4599
4600 // Handle \o40, \x20 and \u20AC style sequences
4601 if (endc == '\\' && !reg_cpo_lit) {
4602 endc = coll_get_char();
4603 }
4604
4605 if (startc > endc) {
4606 EMSG_RET_NULL(_(e_reverse_range))return (emsg(gettext(e_reverse_range)), rc_did_emsg = 1, (void
*)((void*)0));
4607 }
4608 if (utf_char2len(startc) > 1
4609 || utf_char2len(endc) > 1) {
4610 // Limit to a range of 256 chars
4611 if (endc > startc + 256) {
4612 EMSG_RET_NULL(_(e_large_class))return (emsg(gettext(e_large_class)), rc_did_emsg = 1, (void *
)((void*)0));
4613 }
4614 while (++startc <= endc) {
4615 regmbc(startc);
4616 }
4617 } else {
4618 while (++startc <= endc) {
4619 regc(startc);
4620 }
4621 }
4622 startc = -1;
4623 }
4624 }
4625 // Only "\]", "\^", "\]" and "\\" are special in Vi. Vim
4626 // accepts "\t", "\e", etc., but only when the 'l' flag in
4627 // 'cpoptions' is not included.
4628 else if (*regparse == '\\'
4629 && (vim_strchr(REGEXP_INRANGE, (uint8_t)regparse[1]) != NULL((void*)0)
4630 || (!reg_cpo_lit
4631 && vim_strchr(REGEXP_ABBR,
4632 (uint8_t)regparse[1]) != NULL((void*)0)))) {
4633 regparse++;
4634 if (*regparse == 'n') {
4635 // '\n' in range: also match NL
4636 if (ret != JUST_CALC_SIZE((uint8_t *)-1)) {
4637 // Using \n inside [^] does not change what
4638 // matches. "[^\n]" is the same as ".".
4639 if (*ret == ANYOF21) {
4640 *ret = ANYOF21 + ADD_NL30;
4641 *flagp |= HASNL0x8;
4642 }
4643 // else: must have had a \n already
4644 }
4645 regparse++;
4646 startc = -1;
4647 } else if (*regparse == 'd'
4648 || *regparse == 'o'
4649 || *regparse == 'x'
4650 || *regparse == 'u'
4651 || *regparse == 'U') {
4652 startc = coll_get_char();
4653 if (startc == 0) {
4654 regc(0x0a);
4655 } else {
4656 regmbc(startc);
4657 }
4658 } else {
4659 startc = backslash_trans(*regparse++);
4660 regc(startc);
4661 }
4662 } else if (*regparse == '[') {
4663 int c_class;
4664 int cu;
4665
4666 c_class = get_char_class(&regparse);
4667 startc = -1;
4668 // Characters assumed to be 8 bits!
4669 switch (c_class) {
4670 case CLASS_NONE99:
4671 c_class = get_equi_class(&regparse);
4672 if (c_class != 0) {
4673 // produce equivalence class
4674 reg_equi_class(c_class);
4675 } else if ((c_class = get_coll_element(&regparse)) != 0) {
4676 // produce a collating element
4677 regmbc(c_class);
4678 } else {
4679 // literal '[', allow [[-x] as a range
4680 startc = (uint8_t)(*regparse++);
4681 regc(startc);
4682 }
4683 break;
4684 case CLASS_ALNUM0:
4685 for (cu = 1; cu < 128; cu++) {
4686 if (isalnum(cu)((*__ctype_b_loc ())[(int) ((cu))] & (unsigned short int)
_ISalnum)) {
4687 regmbc(cu);
4688 }
4689 }
4690 break;
4691 case CLASS_ALPHA1:
4692 for (cu = 1; cu < 128; cu++) {
4693 if (isalpha(cu)((*__ctype_b_loc ())[(int) ((cu))] & (unsigned short int)
_ISalpha)) {
4694 regmbc(cu);
4695 }
4696 }
4697 break;
4698 case CLASS_BLANK2:
4699 regc(' ');
4700 regc('\t');
4701 break;
4702 case CLASS_CNTRL3:
4703 for (cu = 1; cu <= 127; cu++) {
4704 if (iscntrl(cu)((*__ctype_b_loc ())[(int) ((cu))] & (unsigned short int)
_IScntrl)) {
4705 regmbc(cu);
4706 }
4707 }
4708 break;
4709 case CLASS_DIGIT4:
4710 for (cu = 1; cu <= 127; cu++) {
4711 if (ascii_isdigit(cu)) {
4712 regmbc(cu);
4713 }
4714 }
4715 break;
4716 case CLASS_GRAPH5:
4717 for (cu = 1; cu <= 127; cu++) {
4718 if (isgraph(cu)((*__ctype_b_loc ())[(int) ((cu))] & (unsigned short int)
_ISgraph)) {
4719 regmbc(cu);
4720 }
4721 }
4722 break;
4723 case CLASS_LOWER6:
4724 for (cu = 1; cu <= 255; cu++) {
4725 if (mb_islower(cu) && cu != 170 && cu != 186) {
4726 regmbc(cu);
4727 }
4728 }
4729 break;
4730 case CLASS_PRINT7:
4731 for (cu = 1; cu <= 255; cu++) {
4732 if (vim_isprintc(cu)) {
4733 regmbc(cu);
4734 }
4735 }
4736 break;
4737 case CLASS_PUNCT8:
4738 for (cu = 1; cu < 128; cu++) {
4739 if (ispunct(cu)((*__ctype_b_loc ())[(int) ((cu))] & (unsigned short int)
_ISpunct)) {
4740 regmbc(cu);
4741 }
4742 }
4743 break;
4744 case CLASS_SPACE9:
4745 for (cu = 9; cu <= 13; cu++) {
4746 regc(cu);
4747 }
4748 regc(' ');
4749 break;
4750 case CLASS_UPPER10:
4751 for (cu = 1; cu <= 255; cu++) {
4752 if (mb_isupper(cu)) {
4753 regmbc(cu);
4754 }
4755 }
4756 break;
4757 case CLASS_XDIGIT11:
4758 for (cu = 1; cu <= 255; cu++) {
4759 if (ascii_isxdigit(cu)) {
4760 regmbc(cu);
4761 }
4762 }
4763 break;
4764 case CLASS_TAB12:
4765 regc('\t');
4766 break;
4767 case CLASS_RETURN13:
4768 regc('\r');
4769 break;
4770 case CLASS_BACKSPACE14:
4771 regc('\b');
4772 break;
4773 case CLASS_ESCAPE15:
4774 regc(ESC'\033');
4775 break;
4776 case CLASS_IDENT16:
4777 for (cu = 1; cu <= 255; cu++) {
4778 if (vim_isIDc(cu)) {
4779 regmbc(cu);
4780 }
4781 }
4782 break;
4783 case CLASS_KEYWORD17:
4784 for (cu = 1; cu <= 255; cu++) {
4785 if (reg_iswordc(cu)) {
4786 regmbc(cu);
4787 }
4788 }
4789 break;
4790 case CLASS_FNAME18:
4791 for (cu = 1; cu <= 255; cu++) {
4792 if (vim_isfilec(cu)) {
4793 regmbc(cu);
4794 }
4795 }
4796 break;
4797 }
4798 } else {
4799 // produce a multibyte character, including any
4800 // following composing characters.
4801 startc = utf_ptr2char(regparse);
4802 int len = utfc_ptr2len(regparse);
4803 if (utf_char2len(startc) != len) {
4804 // composing chars
4805 startc = -1;
4806 }
4807 while (--len >= 0) {
4808 regc(*regparse++);
4809 }
4810 }
4811 }
4812 regc(NUL'\000');
4813 prevchr_len = 1; // last char was the ']'
4814 if (*regparse != ']') {
4815 EMSG_RET_NULL(_(e_toomsbra))return (emsg(gettext(e_toomsbra)), rc_did_emsg = 1, (void *)(
(void*)0)); // Cannot happen?
4816 }
4817 skipchr(); // let's be friends with the lexer again
4818 *flagp |= HASWIDTH0x1 | SIMPLE0x2;
4819 break;
4820 } else if (reg_strict) {
4821 EMSG2_RET_NULL(_(e_missingbracket), reg_magic > MAGIC_OFF)return (semsg((gettext(e_missingbracket)), (reg_magic > MAGIC_OFF
) ? "" : "\\"), rc_did_emsg = 1, (void *)((void*)0));
4822 }
4823 }
4824 FALLTHROUGH{} __attribute__((fallthrough));
4825
4826 default: {
4827 int len;
4828
4829 // A multi-byte character is handled as a separate atom if it's
4830 // before a multi and when it's a composing char.
4831 if (use_multibytecode(c)) {
4832do_multibyte:
4833 ret = regnode(MULTIBYTECODE200);
4834 regmbc(c);
4835 *flagp |= HASWIDTH0x1 | SIMPLE0x2;
4836 break;
4837 }
4838
4839 ret = regnode(EXACTLY5);
4840
4841 // Append characters as long as:
4842 // - there is no following multi, we then need the character in
4843 // front of it as a single character operand
4844 // - not running into a Magic character
4845 // - "one_exactly" is not set
4846 // But always emit at least one character. Might be a Multi,
4847 // e.g., a "[" without matching "]".
4848 for (len = 0; c != NUL'\000' && (len == 0
4849 || (re_multi_type(peekchr()) == NOT_MULTI0
4850 && !one_exactly
4851 && !is_Magic(c)((c) < 0))); len++) {
4852 c = no_Magic(c);
4853 {
4854 regmbc(c);
4855 {
4856 int l;
4857
4858 // Need to get composing character too.
4859 while (true1) {
4860 l = utf_ptr2len(regparse);
4861 if (!utf_composinglike(regparse, regparse + l)) {
4862 break;
4863 }
4864 regmbc(utf_ptr2char(regparse));
4865 skipchr();
4866 }
4867 }
4868 }
4869 c = getchr();
4870 }
4871 ungetchr();
4872
4873 regc(NUL'\000');
4874 *flagp |= HASWIDTH0x1;
4875 if (len == 1) {
4876 *flagp |= SIMPLE0x2;
4877 }
4878 }
4879 break;
4880 }
4881
4882 return ret;
4883}
4884
4885// Parse something followed by possible [*+=].
4886//
4887// Note that the branching code sequences used for = and the general cases
4888// of * and + are somewhat optimized: they use the same NOTHING node as
4889// both the endmarker for their branch list and the body of the last branch.
4890// It might seem that this node could be dispensed with entirely, but the
4891// endmarker role is not redundant.
4892static uint8_t *regpiece(int *flagp)
4893{
4894 uint8_t *ret;
4895 int op;
4896 uint8_t *next;
4897 int flags;
4898 int minval;
4899 int maxval;
4900
4901 ret = regatom(&flags);
4902 if (ret == NULL((void*)0)) {
4903 return NULL((void*)0);
4904 }
4905
4906 op = peekchr();
4907 if (re_multi_type(op) == NOT_MULTI0) {
4908 *flagp = flags;
4909 return ret;
4910 }
4911 // default flags
4912 *flagp = (WORST0 | SPSTART0x4 | (flags & (HASNL0x8 | HASLOOKBH0x10)));
4913
4914 skipchr();
4915 switch (op) {
4916 case Magic('*')((int)('*') - 256):
4917 if (flags & SIMPLE0x2) {
4918 reginsert(STAR7, ret);
4919 } else {
4920 // Emit x* as (x&|), where & means "self".
4921 reginsert(BRANCH3, ret); // Either x
4922 regoptail(ret, regnode(BACK4)); // and loop
4923 regoptail(ret, ret); // back
4924 regtail(ret, regnode(BRANCH3)); // or
4925 regtail(ret, regnode(NOTHING6)); // null.
4926 }
4927 break;
4928
4929 case Magic('+')((int)('+') - 256):
4930 if (flags & SIMPLE0x2) {
4931 reginsert(PLUS8, ret);
4932 } else {
4933 // Emit x+ as x(&|), where & means "self".
4934 next = regnode(BRANCH3); // Either
4935 regtail(ret, next);
4936 regtail(regnode(BACK4), ret); // loop back
4937 regtail(next, regnode(BRANCH3)); // or
4938 regtail(ret, regnode(NOTHING6)); // null.
4939 }
4940 *flagp = (WORST0 | HASWIDTH0x1 | (flags & (HASNL0x8 | HASLOOKBH0x10)));
4941 break;
4942
4943 case Magic('@')((int)('@') - 256): {
4944 int lop = END0;
4945 int64_t nr = getdecchrs();
4946
4947 switch (no_Magic(getchr())) {
4948 case '=':
4949 lop = MATCH9; break; // \@=
4950 case '!':
4951 lop = NOMATCH10; break; // \@!
4952 case '>':
4953 lop = SUBPAT13; break; // \@>
4954 case '<':
4955 switch (no_Magic(getchr())) {
4956 case '=':
4957 lop = BEHIND11; break; // \@<=
4958 case '!':
4959 lop = NOBEHIND12; break; // \@<!
4960 }
4961 }
4962 if (lop == END0) {
4963 EMSG2_RET_NULL(_(e_invalid_character_after_str_at),return (semsg((gettext(e_invalid_character_after_str_at)), (reg_magic
== MAGIC_ALL) ? "" : "\\"), rc_did_emsg = 1, (void *)((void*
)0))
4964 reg_magic == MAGIC_ALL)return (semsg((gettext(e_invalid_character_after_str_at)), (reg_magic
== MAGIC_ALL) ? "" : "\\"), rc_did_emsg = 1, (void *)((void*
)0));
4965 }
4966 // Look behind must match with behind_pos.
4967 if (lop == BEHIND11 || lop == NOBEHIND12) {
4968 regtail(ret, regnode(BHPOS19));
4969 *flagp |= HASLOOKBH0x10;
4970 }
4971 regtail(ret, regnode(END0)); // operand ends
4972 if (lop == BEHIND11 || lop == NOBEHIND12) {
4973 if (nr < 0) {
4974 nr = 0; // no limit is same as zero limit
4975 }
4976 reginsert_nr(lop, (uint32_t)nr, ret);
4977 } else {
4978 reginsert(lop, ret);
4979 }
4980 break;
4981 }
4982
4983 case Magic('?')((int)('?') - 256):
4984 case Magic('=')((int)('=') - 256):
4985 // Emit x= as (x|)
4986 reginsert(BRANCH3, ret); // Either x
4987 regtail(ret, regnode(BRANCH3)); // or
4988 next = regnode(NOTHING6); // null.
4989 regtail(ret, next);
4990 regoptail(ret, next);
4991 break;
4992
4993 case Magic('{')((int)('{') - 256):
4994 if (!read_limits(&minval, &maxval)) {
4995 return NULL((void*)0);
4996 }
4997 if (flags & SIMPLE0x2) {
4998 reginsert(BRACE_SIMPLE14, ret);
4999 reginsert_limits(BRACE_LIMITS17, minval, maxval, ret);
5000 } else {
5001 if (num_complex_braces >= 10) {
5002 EMSG2_RET_NULL(_("E60: Too many complex %s{...}s"),return (semsg((gettext("E60: Too many complex %s{...}s")), (reg_magic
== MAGIC_ALL) ? "" : "\\"), rc_did_emsg = 1, (void *)((void*
)0))
5003 reg_magic == MAGIC_ALL)return (semsg((gettext("E60: Too many complex %s{...}s")), (reg_magic
== MAGIC_ALL) ? "" : "\\"), rc_did_emsg = 1, (void *)((void*
)0));
5004 }
5005 reginsert(BRACE_COMPLEX140 + num_complex_braces, ret);
5006 regoptail(ret, regnode(BACK4));
5007 regoptail(ret, ret);
5008 reginsert_limits(BRACE_LIMITS17, minval, maxval, ret);
5009 num_complex_braces++;
5010 }
5011 if (minval > 0 && maxval > 0) {
5012 *flagp = (HASWIDTH0x1 | (flags & (HASNL0x8 | HASLOOKBH0x10)));
5013 }
5014 break;
5015 }
5016 if (re_multi_type(peekchr()) != NOT_MULTI0) {
5017 // Can't have a multi follow a multi.
5018 if (peekchr() == Magic('*')((int)('*') - 256)) {
5019 EMSG2_RET_NULL(_("E61: Nested %s*"), reg_magic >= MAGIC_ON)return (semsg((gettext("E61: Nested %s*")), (reg_magic >= MAGIC_ON
) ? "" : "\\"), rc_did_emsg = 1, (void *)((void*)0));
5020 }
5021 EMSG3_RET_NULL(_("E62: Nested %s%c"), reg_magic == MAGIC_ALL, no_Magic(peekchr()))return (semsg((gettext("E62: Nested %s%c")), (reg_magic == MAGIC_ALL
) ? "" : "\\", (no_Magic(peekchr()))), rc_did_emsg = 1, (void
*)((void*)0));
5022 }
5023
5024 return ret;
5025}
5026
5027// Parse one alternative of an | or & operator.
5028// Implements the concatenation operator.
5029static uint8_t *regconcat(int *flagp)
5030{
5031 uint8_t *first = NULL((void*)0);
5032 uint8_t *chain = NULL((void*)0);
5033 uint8_t *latest;
5034 int flags;
5035 int cont = true1;
5036
5037 *flagp = WORST0; // Tentatively.
5038
5039 while (cont) {
5040 switch (peekchr()) {
5041 case NUL'\000':
5042 case Magic('|')((int)('|') - 256):
5043 case Magic('&')((int)('&') - 256):
5044 case Magic(')')((int)(')') - 256):
5045 cont = false0;
5046 break;
5047 case Magic('Z')((int)('Z') - 256):
5048 regflags |= RF_ICOMBINE8;
5049 skipchr_keepstart();
5050 break;
5051 case Magic('c')((int)('c') - 256):
5052 regflags |= RF_ICASE1;
5053 skipchr_keepstart();
5054 break;
5055 case Magic('C')((int)('C') - 256):
5056 regflags |= RF_NOICASE2;
5057 skipchr_keepstart();
5058 break;
5059 case Magic('v')((int)('v') - 256):
5060 reg_magic = MAGIC_ALL;
5061 skipchr_keepstart();
5062 curchr = -1;
5063 break;
5064 case Magic('m')((int)('m') - 256):
5065 reg_magic = MAGIC_ON;
5066 skipchr_keepstart();
5067 curchr = -1;
5068 break;
5069 case Magic('M')((int)('M') - 256):
5070 reg_magic = MAGIC_OFF;
5071 skipchr_keepstart();
5072 curchr = -1;
5073 break;
5074 case Magic('V')((int)('V') - 256):
5075 reg_magic = MAGIC_NONE;
5076 skipchr_keepstart();
5077 curchr = -1;
5078 break;
5079 default:
5080 latest = regpiece(&flags);
5081 if (latest == NULL((void*)0) || reg_toolong) {
5082 return NULL((void*)0);
5083 }
5084 *flagp |= flags & (HASWIDTH0x1 | HASNL0x8 | HASLOOKBH0x10);
5085 if (chain == NULL((void*)0)) { // First piece.
5086 *flagp |= flags & SPSTART0x4;
5087 } else {
5088 regtail(chain, latest);
5089 }
5090 chain = latest;
5091 if (first == NULL((void*)0)) {
5092 first = latest;
5093 }
5094 break;
5095 }
5096 }
5097 if (first == NULL((void*)0)) { // Loop ran zero times.
5098 first = regnode(NOTHING6);
5099 }
5100 return first;
5101}
5102
5103// Parse one alternative of an | operator.
5104// Implements the & operator.
5105static uint8_t *regbranch(int *flagp)
5106{
5107 uint8_t *ret;
5108 uint8_t *chain = NULL((void*)0);
5109 uint8_t *latest;
5110 int flags;
5111
5112 *flagp = WORST0 | HASNL0x8; // Tentatively.
5113
5114 ret = regnode(BRANCH3);
5115 while (true1) {
5116 latest = regconcat(&flags);
5117 if (latest == NULL((void*)0)) {
5118 return NULL((void*)0);
5119 }
5120 // If one of the branches has width, the whole thing has. If one of
5121 // the branches anchors at start-of-line, the whole thing does.
5122 // If one of the branches uses look-behind, the whole thing does.
5123 *flagp |= flags & (HASWIDTH0x1 | SPSTART0x4 | HASLOOKBH0x10);
5124 // If one of the branches doesn't match a line-break, the whole thing
5125 // doesn't.
5126 *flagp &= ~HASNL0x8 | (flags & HASNL0x8);
5127 if (chain != NULL((void*)0)) {
5128 regtail(chain, latest);
5129 }
5130 if (peekchr() != Magic('&')((int)('&') - 256)) {
5131 break;
5132 }
5133 skipchr();
5134 regtail(latest, regnode(END0)); // operand ends
5135 if (reg_toolong) {
5136 break;
5137 }
5138 reginsert(MATCH9, latest);
5139 chain = latest;
5140 }
5141
5142 return ret;
5143}
5144
5145/// Parse regular expression, i.e. main body or parenthesized thing.
5146///
5147/// Caller must absorb opening parenthesis.
5148///
5149/// Combining parenthesis handling with the base level of regular expression
5150/// is a trifle forced, but the need to tie the tails of the branches to what
5151/// follows makes it hard to avoid.
5152///
5153/// @param paren REG_NOPAREN, REG_PAREN, REG_NPAREN or REG_ZPAREN
5154static uint8_t *reg(int paren, int *flagp)
5155{
5156 uint8_t *ret;
5157 uint8_t *br;
5158 uint8_t *ender;
5159 int parno = 0;
5160 int flags;
5161
5162 *flagp = HASWIDTH0x1; // Tentatively.
5163
5164 if (paren == REG_ZPAREN2) {
5165 // Make a ZOPEN node.
5166 if (regnzpar >= NSUBEXP) {
5167 EMSG_RET_NULL(_("E50: Too many \\z("))return (emsg(gettext("E50: Too many \\z(")), rc_did_emsg = 1,
(void *)((void*)0));
5168 }
5169 parno = regnzpar;
5170 regnzpar++;
5171 ret = regnode(ZOPEN110 + parno);
5172 } else if (paren == REG_PAREN1) {
5173 // Make a MOPEN node.
5174 if (regnpar >= NSUBEXP) {
5175 EMSG2_RET_NULL(_("E51: Too many %s("), reg_magic == MAGIC_ALL)return (semsg((gettext("E51: Too many %s(")), (reg_magic == MAGIC_ALL
) ? "" : "\\"), rc_did_emsg = 1, (void *)((void*)0));
5176 }
5177 parno = regnpar;
5178 regnpar++;
5179 ret = regnode(MOPEN80 + parno);
5180 } else if (paren == REG_NPAREN3) {
5181 // Make a NOPEN node.
5182 ret = regnode(NOPEN150);
5183 } else {
5184 ret = NULL((void*)0);
5185 }
5186
5187 // Pick up the branches, linking them together.
5188 br = regbranch(&flags);
5189 if (br == NULL((void*)0)) {
5190 return NULL((void*)0);
5191 }
5192 if (ret != NULL((void*)0)) {
5193 regtail(ret, br); // [MZ]OPEN -> first.
5194 } else {
5195 ret = br;
5196 }
5197 // If one of the branches can be zero-width, the whole thing can.
5198 // If one of the branches has * at start or matches a line-break, the
5199 // whole thing can.
5200 if (!(flags & HASWIDTH0x1)) {
5201 *flagp &= ~HASWIDTH0x1;
5202 }
5203 *flagp |= flags & (SPSTART0x4 | HASNL0x8 | HASLOOKBH0x10);
5204 while (peekchr() == Magic('|')((int)('|') - 256)) {
5205 skipchr();
5206 br = regbranch(&flags);
5207 if (br == NULL((void*)0) || reg_toolong) {
5208 return NULL((void*)0);
5209 }
5210 regtail(ret, br); // BRANCH -> BRANCH.
5211 if (!(flags & HASWIDTH0x1)) {
5212 *flagp &= ~HASWIDTH0x1;
5213 }
5214 *flagp |= flags & (SPSTART0x4 | HASNL0x8 | HASLOOKBH0x10);
5215 }
5216
5217 // Make a closing node, and hook it on the end.
5218 ender = regnode(paren == REG_ZPAREN2 ? ZCLOSE120 + parno
5219 : paren == REG_PAREN1 ? MCLOSE90 + parno
5220 : paren == REG_NPAREN3 ? NCLOSE151 : END0);
5221 regtail(ret, ender);
5222
5223 // Hook the tails of the branches to the closing node.
5224 for (br = ret; br != NULL((void*)0); br = regnext(br)) {
5225 regoptail(br, ender);
5226 }
5227
5228 // Check for proper termination.
5229 if (paren != REG_NOPAREN0 && getchr() != Magic(')')((int)(')') - 256)) {
5230 if (paren == REG_ZPAREN2) {
5231 EMSG_RET_NULL(_("E52: Unmatched \\z("))return (emsg(gettext("E52: Unmatched \\z(")), rc_did_emsg = 1
, (void *)((void*)0));
5232 } else if (paren == REG_NPAREN3) {
5233 EMSG2_RET_NULL(_(e_unmatchedpp), reg_magic == MAGIC_ALL)return (semsg((gettext(e_unmatchedpp)), (reg_magic == MAGIC_ALL
) ? "" : "\\"), rc_did_emsg = 1, (void *)((void*)0));
5234 } else {
5235 EMSG2_RET_NULL(_(e_unmatchedp), reg_magic == MAGIC_ALL)return (semsg((gettext(e_unmatchedp)), (reg_magic == MAGIC_ALL
) ? "" : "\\"), rc_did_emsg = 1, (void *)((void*)0));
5236 }
5237 } else if (paren == REG_NOPAREN0 && peekchr() != NUL'\000') {
5238 if (curchr == Magic(')')((int)(')') - 256)) {
5239 EMSG2_RET_NULL(_(e_unmatchedpar), reg_magic == MAGIC_ALL)return (semsg((gettext(e_unmatchedpar)), (reg_magic == MAGIC_ALL
) ? "" : "\\"), rc_did_emsg = 1, (void *)((void*)0));
5240 } else {
5241 EMSG_RET_NULL(_(e_trailing))return (emsg(gettext(e_trailing)), rc_did_emsg = 1, (void *)(
(void*)0)); // "Can't happen".
5242 }
5243 // NOTREACHED
5244 }
5245 // Here we set the flag allowing back references to this set of
5246 // parentheses.
5247 if (paren == REG_PAREN1) {
5248 had_endbrace[parno] = true1; // have seen the close paren
5249 }
5250 return ret;
5251}
5252
5253// bt_regcomp() - compile a regular expression into internal code for the
5254// traditional back track matcher.
5255// Returns the program in allocated space. Returns NULL for an error.
5256//
5257// We can't allocate space until we know how big the compiled form will be,
5258// but we can't compile it (and thus know how big it is) until we've got a
5259// place to put the code. So we cheat: we compile it twice, once with code
5260// generation turned off and size counting turned on, and once "for real".
5261// This also means that we don't allocate space until we are sure that the
5262// thing really will compile successfully, and we never have to move the
5263// code and thus invalidate pointers into it. (Note that it has to be in
5264// one piece because free() must be able to free it all.)
5265//
5266// Whether upper/lower case is to be ignored is decided when executing the
5267// program, it does not matter here.
5268//
5269// Beware that the optimization-preparation code in here knows about some
5270// of the structure of the compiled regexp.
5271// "re_flags": RE_MAGIC and/or RE_STRING.
5272static regprog_T *bt_regcomp(uint8_t *expr, int re_flags)
5273{
5274 uint8_t *scan;
5275 uint8_t *longest;
5276 int len;
5277 int flags;
5278
5279 if (expr == NULL((void*)0)) {
5280 IEMSG_RET_NULL(_(e_null))return (iemsg(gettext(e_null)), rc_did_emsg = 1, (void *)((void
*)0));
5281 }
5282
5283 init_class_tab();
5284
5285 // First pass: determine size, legality.
5286 regcomp_start(expr, re_flags);
5287 regcode = JUST_CALC_SIZE((uint8_t *)-1);
5288 regc(REGMAGIC0234);
5289 if (reg(REG_NOPAREN0, &flags) == NULL((void*)0)) {
5290 return NULL((void*)0);
5291 }
5292
5293 // Allocate space.
5294 bt_regprog_T *r = xmalloc(offsetof(bt_regprog_T, program)__builtin_offsetof(bt_regprog_T, program) + (size_t)regsize);
5295 r->re_in_use = false0;
5296
5297 // Second pass: emit code.
5298 regcomp_start(expr, re_flags);
5299 regcode = r->program;
5300 regc(REGMAGIC0234);
5301 if (reg(REG_NOPAREN0, &flags) == NULL((void*)0) || reg_toolong) {
5302 xfree(r);
5303 if (reg_toolong) {
5304 EMSG_RET_NULL(_("E339: Pattern too long"))return (emsg(gettext("E339: Pattern too long")), rc_did_emsg =
1, (void *)((void*)0));
5305 }
5306 return NULL((void*)0);
5307 }
5308
5309 // Dig out information for optimizations.
5310 r->regstart = NUL'\000'; // Worst-case defaults.
5311 r->reganch = 0;
5312 r->regmust = NULL((void*)0);
5313 r->regmlen = 0;
5314 r->regflags = regflags;
5315 if (flags & HASNL0x8) {
5316 r->regflags |= RF_HASNL4;
5317 }
5318 if (flags & HASLOOKBH0x10) {
5319 r->regflags |= RF_LOOKBH16;
5320 }
5321 // Remember whether this pattern has any \z specials in it.
5322 r->reghasz = (uint8_t)re_has_z;
5323 scan = r->program + 1; // First BRANCH.
5324 if (OP(regnext(scan))((int)(*(regnext(scan)))) == END0) { // Only one top-level choice.
5325 scan = OPERAND(scan)((scan) + 3);
5326
5327 // Starting-point info.
5328 if (OP(scan)((int)(*(scan))) == BOL1 || OP(scan)((int)(*(scan))) == RE_BOF201) {
5329 r->reganch++;
5330 scan = regnext(scan);
5331 }
5332
5333 if (OP(scan)((int)(*(scan))) == EXACTLY5) {
5334 r->regstart = utf_ptr2char((char *)OPERAND(scan)((scan) + 3));
5335 } else if (OP(scan)((int)(*(scan))) == BOW15
5336 || OP(scan)((int)(*(scan))) == EOW16
5337 || OP(scan)((int)(*(scan))) == NOTHING6
5338 || OP(scan)((int)(*(scan))) == MOPEN80 + 0 || OP(scan)((int)(*(scan))) == NOPEN150
5339 || OP(scan)((int)(*(scan))) == MCLOSE90 + 0 || OP(scan)((int)(*(scan))) == NCLOSE151) {
5340 uint8_t *regnext_scan = regnext(scan);
5341 if (OP(regnext_scan)((int)(*(regnext_scan))) == EXACTLY5) {
5342 r->regstart = utf_ptr2char((char *)OPERAND(regnext_scan)((regnext_scan) + 3));
5343 }
5344 }
5345
5346 // If there's something expensive in the r.e., find the longest
5347 // literal string that must appear and make it the regmust. Resolve
5348 // ties in favor of later strings, since the regstart check works
5349 // with the beginning of the r.e. and avoiding duplication
5350 // strengthens checking. Not a strong reason, but sufficient in the
5351 // absence of others.
5352
5353 // When the r.e. starts with BOW, it is faster to look for a regmust
5354 // first. Used a lot for "#" and "*" commands. (Added by mool).
5355 if ((flags & SPSTART0x4 || OP(scan)((int)(*(scan))) == BOW15 || OP(scan)((int)(*(scan))) == EOW16)
5356 && !(flags & HASNL0x8)) {
5357 longest = NULL((void*)0);
5358 len = 0;
5359 for (; scan != NULL((void*)0); scan = regnext(scan)) {
5360 if (OP(scan)((int)(*(scan))) == EXACTLY5 && strlen((char *)OPERAND(scan)((scan) + 3)) >= (size_t)len) {
5361 longest = OPERAND(scan)((scan) + 3);
5362 len = (int)strlen((char *)OPERAND(scan)((scan) + 3));
5363 }
5364 }
5365 r->regmust = longest;
5366 r->regmlen = len;
5367 }
5368 }
5369#ifdef BT_REGEXP_DUMP
5370 regdump(expr, r);
5371#endif
5372 r->engine = &bt_regengine;
5373 return (regprog_T *)r;
5374}

5376// Check if during the previous call to vim_regcomp the EOL item "$" has been
5377// found. This is messy, but it works fine.
5378int vim_regcomp_had_eol(void)
5379{
5380 return had_eol;
5381}
5382
5383// Get a number after a backslash that is inside [].
5384// When nothing is recognized return a backslash.
5385static int coll_get_char(void)
5386{
5387 int64_t nr = -1;
5388
5389 switch (*regparse++) {
5390 case 'd':
5391 nr = getdecchrs(); break;
5392 case 'o':
5393 nr = getoctchrs(); break;
5394 case 'x':
5395 nr = gethexchrs(2); break;
5396 case 'u':
5397 nr = gethexchrs(4); break;
5398 case 'U':
5399 nr = gethexchrs(8); break;
5400 }
5401 if (nr < 0 || nr > INT_MAX2147483647) {
5402 // If getting the number fails be backwards compatible: the character
5403 // is a backslash.
5404 regparse--;
5405 nr = '\\';
5406 }
5407 return (int)nr;
5408}

5410// Free a compiled regexp program, returned by bt_regcomp().
5411static void bt_regfree(regprog_T *prog)
5412{
5413 xfree(prog);
5414}
5415
5416#define ADVANCE_REGINPUT()(rex.input += utfc_ptr2len((char *)rex.input)) MB_PTR_ADV(rex.input)(rex.input += utfc_ptr2len((char *)rex.input))
5417
5418// The arguments from BRACE_LIMITS are stored here. They are actually local
5419// to regmatch(), but they are here to reduce the amount of stack space used
5420// (it can be called recursively many times).
5421static int64_t bl_minval;
5422static int64_t bl_maxval;
5423
5424// Save the input line and position in a regsave_T.
5425static void reg_save(regsave_T *save, garray_T *gap)
5426 FUNC_ATTR_NONNULL_ALL
5427{
5428 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
5429 save->rs_u.pos.col = (colnr_T)(rex.input - rex.line);
5430 save->rs_u.pos.lnum = rex.lnum;
5431 } else {
5432 save->rs_u.ptr = rex.input;
5433 }
5434 save->rs_len = gap->ga_len;
5435}
5436
5437// Restore the input line and position from a regsave_T.
5438static void reg_restore(regsave_T *save, garray_T *gap)
5439 FUNC_ATTR_NONNULL_ALL
5440{
5441 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
5442 if (rex.lnum != save->rs_u.pos.lnum) {
5443 // only call reg_getline() when the line number changed to save
5444 // a bit of time
5445 rex.lnum = save->rs_u.pos.lnum;
5446 rex.line = (uint8_t *)reg_getline(rex.lnum);
5447 }
5448 rex.input = rex.line + save->rs_u.pos.col;
5449 } else {
5450 rex.input = save->rs_u.ptr;
5451 }
5452 gap->ga_len = save->rs_len;
5453}
5454
5455// Return true if current position is equal to saved position.
5456static bool_Bool reg_save_equal(const regsave_T *save)
5457 FUNC_ATTR_NONNULL_ALL
5458{
5459 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
5460 return rex.lnum == save->rs_u.pos.lnum
5461 && rex.input == rex.line + save->rs_u.pos.col;
5462 }
5463 return rex.input == save->rs_u.ptr;
5464}

5466// Save the sub-expressions before attempting a match.
5467#define save_se(savep, posp, pp)(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0)) ? save_se_multi((savep), (posp)
) : save_se_one((savep), (pp)) \
5468 REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0)) ? save_se_multi((savep), (posp)) : save_se_one((savep), (pp))
5469
5470// After a failed match restore the sub-expressions.
5471#define restore_se(savep, posp, pp){ if ((rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) *(posp) = (savep)->se_u
.pos; else *(pp) = (savep)->se_u.ptr; } { \
5472 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) \
5473 *(posp) = (savep)->se_u.pos; \
5474 else \
5475 *(pp) = (savep)->se_u.ptr; }
5476
5477// Tentatively set the sub-expression start to the current position (after
5478// calling regmatch() they will have changed). Need to save the existing
5479// values for when there is no match.
5480// Use se_save() to use pointer (save_se_multi()) or position (save_se_one()),
5481// depending on REG_MULTI.
5482static void save_se_multi(save_se_T *savep, lpos_T *posp)
5483{
5484 savep->se_u.pos = *posp;
5485 posp->lnum = rex.lnum;
5486 posp->col = (colnr_T)(rex.input - rex.line);
5487}
5488
5489static void save_se_one(save_se_T *savep, uint8_t **pp)
5490{
5491 savep->se_u.ptr = *pp;
5492 *pp = rex.input;
5493}

5495/// regrepeat - repeatedly match something simple, return how many.
5496/// Advances rex.input (and rex.lnum) to just after the matched chars.
5497///
5498/// @param maxcount maximum number of matches allowed
5499static int regrepeat(uint8_t *p, int64_t maxcount)
5500{
5501 int64_t count = 0;
5502 uint8_t *opnd;
5503 int mask;
5504 int testval = 0;
5505
5506 uint8_t *scan = rex.input; // Make local copy of rex.input for speed.
5507 opnd = OPERAND(p)((p) + 3);
5508 switch (OP(p)((int)(*(p)))) {
5509 case ANY20:
5510 case ANY20 + ADD_NL30:
5511 while (count < maxcount) {
5512 // Matching anything means we continue until end-of-line (or
5513 // end-of-file for ANY + ADD_NL), only limited by maxcount.
5514 while (*scan != NUL'\000' && count < maxcount) {
5515 count++;
5516 MB_PTR_ADV(scan)(scan += utfc_ptr2len((char *)scan));
5517 }
5518 if (!REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0)) || !WITH_NL(OP(p))((((int)(*(p)))) >= 20 + 30 && (((int)(*(p)))) <=
48 + 30) || rex.lnum > rex.reg_maxline
5519 || rex.reg_line_lbr || count == maxcount) {
5520 break;
5521 }
5522 count++; // count the line-break
5523 reg_nextline();
5524 scan = rex.input;
5525 if (got_int) {
5526 break;
5527 }
5528 }
5529 break;
5530
5531 case IDENT23:
5532 case IDENT23 + ADD_NL30:
5533 testval = 1;
5534 FALLTHROUGH{} __attribute__((fallthrough));
5535 case SIDENT24:
5536 case SIDENT24 + ADD_NL30:
5537 while (count < maxcount) {
5538 if (vim_isIDc(utf_ptr2char((char *)scan)) && (testval || !ascii_isdigit(*scan))) {
5539 MB_PTR_ADV(scan)(scan += utfc_ptr2len((char *)scan));
5540 } else if (*scan == NUL'\000') {
5541 if (!REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0)) || !WITH_NL(OP(p))((((int)(*(p)))) >= 20 + 30 && (((int)(*(p)))) <=
48 + 30) || rex.lnum > rex.reg_maxline
5542 || rex.reg_line_lbr) {
5543 break;
5544 }
5545 reg_nextline();
5546 scan = rex.input;
5547 if (got_int) {
5548 break;
5549 }
5550 } else if (rex.reg_line_lbr && *scan == '\n' && WITH_NL(OP(p))((((int)(*(p)))) >= 20 + 30 && (((int)(*(p)))) <=
48 + 30)) {
5551 scan++;
5552 } else {
5553 break;
5554 }
5555 count++;
5556 }
5557 break;
5558
5559 case KWORD25:
5560 case KWORD25 + ADD_NL30:
5561 testval = 1;
5562 FALLTHROUGH{} __attribute__((fallthrough));
5563 case SKWORD26:
5564 case SKWORD26 + ADD_NL30:
5565 while (count < maxcount) {
5566 if (vim_iswordp_buf((char *)scan, rex.reg_buf)
5567 && (testval || !ascii_isdigit(*scan))) {
5568 MB_PTR_ADV(scan)(scan += utfc_ptr2len((char *)scan));
5569 } else if (*scan == NUL'\000') {
5570 if (!REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0)) || !WITH_NL(OP(p))((((int)(*(p)))) >= 20 + 30 && (((int)(*(p)))) <=
48 + 30) || rex.lnum > rex.reg_maxline
5571 || rex.reg_line_lbr) {
5572 break;
5573 }
5574 reg_nextline();
5575 scan = rex.input;
5576 if (got_int) {
5577 break;
5578 }
5579 } else if (rex.reg_line_lbr && *scan == '\n' && WITH_NL(OP(p))((((int)(*(p)))) >= 20 + 30 && (((int)(*(p)))) <=
48 + 30)) {
5580 scan++;
5581 } else {
5582 break;
5583 }
5584 count++;
5585 }
5586 break;
5587
5588 case FNAME27:
5589 case FNAME27 + ADD_NL30:
5590 testval = 1;
5591 FALLTHROUGH{} __attribute__((fallthrough));
5592 case SFNAME28:
5593 case SFNAME28 + ADD_NL30:
5594 while (count < maxcount) {
5595 if (vim_isfilec(utf_ptr2char((char *)scan)) && (testval || !ascii_isdigit(*scan))) {
5596 MB_PTR_ADV(scan)(scan += utfc_ptr2len((char *)scan));
5597 } else if (*scan == NUL'\000') {
5598 if (!REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0)) || !WITH_NL(OP(p))((((int)(*(p)))) >= 20 + 30 && (((int)(*(p)))) <=
48 + 30) || rex.lnum > rex.reg_maxline
5599 || rex.reg_line_lbr) {
5600 break;
5601 }
5602 reg_nextline();
5603 scan = rex.input;
5604 if (got_int) {
5605 break;
5606 }
5607 } else if (rex.reg_line_lbr && *scan == '\n' && WITH_NL(OP(p))((((int)(*(p)))) >= 20 + 30 && (((int)(*(p)))) <=
48 + 30)) {
5608 scan++;
5609 } else {
5610 break;
5611 }
5612 count++;
5613 }
5614 break;
5615
5616 case PRINT29:
5617 case PRINT29 + ADD_NL30:
5618 testval = 1;
5619 FALLTHROUGH{} __attribute__((fallthrough));
5620 case SPRINT30:
5621 case SPRINT30 + ADD_NL30:
5622 while (count < maxcount) {
5623 if (*scan == NUL'\000') {
5624 if (!REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0)) || !WITH_NL(OP(p))((((int)(*(p)))) >= 20 + 30 && (((int)(*(p)))) <=
48 + 30) || rex.lnum > rex.reg_maxline
5625 || rex.reg_line_lbr) {
5626 break;
5627 }
5628 reg_nextline();
5629 scan = rex.input;
5630 if (got_int) {
5631 break;
5632 }
5633 } else if (vim_isprintc(utf_ptr2char((char *)scan)) == 1
5634 && (testval || !ascii_isdigit(*scan))) {
5635 MB_PTR_ADV(scan)(scan += utfc_ptr2len((char *)scan));
5636 } else if (rex.reg_line_lbr && *scan == '\n' && WITH_NL(OP(p))((((int)(*(p)))) >= 20 + 30 && (((int)(*(p)))) <=
48 + 30)) {
5637 scan++;
5638 } else {
5639 break;
5640 }
5641 count++;
5642 }
5643 break;
5644
5645 case WHITE31:
5646 case WHITE31 + ADD_NL30:
5647 testval = mask = RI_WHITE0x100;
5648do_class:
5649 while (count < maxcount) {
5650 int l;
5651 if (*scan == NUL'\000') {
5652 if (!REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0)) || !WITH_NL(OP(p))((((int)(*(p)))) >= 20 + 30 && (((int)(*(p)))) <=
48 + 30) || rex.lnum > rex.reg_maxline
5653 || rex.reg_line_lbr) {
5654 break;
5655 }
5656 reg_nextline();
5657 scan = rex.input;
5658 if (got_int) {
5659 break;
5660 }
5661 } else if ((l = utfc_ptr2len((char *)scan)) > 1) {
5662 if (testval != 0) {
5663 break;
5664 }
5665 scan += l;
5666 } else if ((class_tab[*scan] & mask) == testval) {
5667 scan++;
5668 } else if (rex.reg_line_lbr && *scan == '\n' && WITH_NL(OP(p))((((int)(*(p)))) >= 20 + 30 && (((int)(*(p)))) <=
48 + 30)) {
5669 scan++;
5670 } else {
5671 break;
5672 }
5673 count++;
5674 }
5675 break;
5676
5677 case NWHITE32:
5678 case NWHITE32 + ADD_NL30:
5679 mask = RI_WHITE0x100;
5680 goto do_class;
5681 case DIGIT33:
5682 case DIGIT33 + ADD_NL30:
5683 testval = mask = RI_DIGIT0x01;
5684 goto do_class;
5685 case NDIGIT34:
5686 case NDIGIT34 + ADD_NL30:
5687 mask = RI_DIGIT0x01;
5688 goto do_class;
5689 case HEX35:
5690 case HEX35 + ADD_NL30:
5691 testval = mask = RI_HEX0x02;
5692 goto do_class;
5693 case NHEX36:
5694 case NHEX36 + ADD_NL30:
5695 mask = RI_HEX0x02;
5696 goto do_class;
5697 case OCTAL37:
5698 case OCTAL37 + ADD_NL30:
5699 testval = mask = RI_OCTAL0x04;
5700 goto do_class;
5701 case NOCTAL38:
5702 case NOCTAL38 + ADD_NL30:
5703 mask = RI_OCTAL0x04;
5704 goto do_class;
5705 case WORD39:
5706 case WORD39 + ADD_NL30:
5707 testval = mask = RI_WORD0x08;
5708 goto do_class;
5709 case NWORD40:
5710 case NWORD40 + ADD_NL30:
5711 mask = RI_WORD0x08;
5712 goto do_class;
5713 case HEAD41:
5714 case HEAD41 + ADD_NL30:
5715 testval = mask = RI_HEAD0x10;
5716 goto do_class;
5717 case NHEAD42:
5718 case NHEAD42 + ADD_NL30:
5719 mask = RI_HEAD0x10;
5720 goto do_class;
5721 case ALPHA43:
5722 case ALPHA43 + ADD_NL30:
5723 testval = mask = RI_ALPHA0x20;
5724 goto do_class;
5725 case NALPHA44:
5726 case NALPHA44 + ADD_NL30:
5727 mask = RI_ALPHA0x20;
5728 goto do_class;
5729 case LOWER45:
5730 case LOWER45 + ADD_NL30:
5731 testval = mask = RI_LOWER0x40;
5732 goto do_class;
5733 case NLOWER46:
5734 case NLOWER46 + ADD_NL30:
5735 mask = RI_LOWER0x40;
5736 goto do_class;
5737 case UPPER47:
5738 case UPPER47 + ADD_NL30:
5739 testval = mask = RI_UPPER0x80;
5740 goto do_class;
5741 case NUPPER48:
5742 case NUPPER48 + ADD_NL30:
5743 mask = RI_UPPER0x80;
5744 goto do_class;
5745
5746 case EXACTLY5: {
5747 int cu, cl;
5748
5749 // This doesn't do a multi-byte character, because a MULTIBYTECODE
5750 // would have been used for it. It does handle single-byte
5751 // characters, such as latin1.
5752 if (rex.reg_ic) {
5753 cu = mb_toupper(*opnd);
5754 cl = mb_tolower(*opnd);
5755 while (count < maxcount && (*scan == cu || *scan == cl)) {
5756 count++;
5757 scan++;
5758 }
5759 } else {
5760 cu = *opnd;
5761 while (count < maxcount && *scan == cu) {
5762 count++;
5763 scan++;
5764 }
5765 }
5766 break;
5767 }
5768
5769 case MULTIBYTECODE200: {
5770 int i, len, cf = 0;
5771
5772 // Safety check (just in case 'encoding' was changed since
5773 // compiling the program).
5774 if ((len = utfc_ptr2len((char *)opnd)) > 1) {
5775 if (rex.reg_ic) {
5776 cf = utf_fold(utf_ptr2char((char *)opnd));
5777 }
5778 while (count < maxcount && utfc_ptr2len((char *)scan) >= len) {
5779 for (i = 0; i < len; i++) {
5780 if (opnd[i] != scan[i]) {
5781 break;
5782 }
5783 }
5784 if (i < len && (!rex.reg_ic
5785 || utf_fold(utf_ptr2char((char *)scan)) != cf)) {
5786 break;
5787 }
5788 scan += len;
5789 count++;
5790 }
5791 }
5792 }
5793 break;
5794
5795 case ANYOF21:
5796 case ANYOF21 + ADD_NL30:
5797 testval = 1;
5798 FALLTHROUGH{} __attribute__((fallthrough));
5799
5800 case ANYBUT22:
5801 case ANYBUT22 + ADD_NL30:
5802 while (count < maxcount) {
5803 int len;
5804 if (*scan == NUL'\000') {
5805 if (!REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0)) || !WITH_NL(OP(p))((((int)(*(p)))) >= 20 + 30 && (((int)(*(p)))) <=
48 + 30) || rex.lnum > rex.reg_maxline
5806 || rex.reg_line_lbr) {
5807 break;
5808 }
5809 reg_nextline();
5810 scan = rex.input;
5811 if (got_int) {
5812 break;
5813 }
5814 } else if (rex.reg_line_lbr && *scan == '\n' && WITH_NL(OP(p))((((int)(*(p)))) >= 20 + 30 && (((int)(*(p)))) <=
48 + 30)) {
5815 scan++;
5816 } else if ((len = utfc_ptr2len((char *)scan)) > 1) {
5817 if ((cstrchr((char *)opnd, utf_ptr2char((char *)scan)) == NULL((void*)0)) == testval) {
5818 break;
5819 }
5820 scan += len;
5821 } else {
5822 if ((cstrchr((char *)opnd, *scan) == NULL((void*)0)) == testval) {
5823 break;
5824 }
5825 scan++;
5826 }
5827 count++;
5828 }
5829 break;
5830
5831 case NEWL18:
5832 while (count < maxcount
5833 && ((*scan == NUL'\000' && rex.lnum <= rex.reg_maxline && !rex.reg_line_lbr
5834 && REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) || (*scan == '\n' && rex.reg_line_lbr))) {
5835 count++;
5836 if (rex.reg_line_lbr) {
5837 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()(rex.input += utfc_ptr2len((char *)rex.input));
5838 } else {
5839 reg_nextline();
5840 }
5841 scan = rex.input;
5842 if (got_int) {
5843 break;
5844 }
5845 }
5846 break;
5847
5848 default: // Oh dear. Called inappropriately.
5849 iemsg(_(e_re_corr)gettext(e_re_corr));
5850#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
5851 printf("Called regrepeat with op code %d\n", OP(p)((int)(*(p))));
5852#endif
5853 break;
5854 }
5855
5856 rex.input = scan;
5857
5858 return (int)count;
5859}
5860
5861// Push an item onto the regstack.
5862// Returns pointer to new item. Returns NULL when out of memory.
5863static regitem_T *regstack_push(regstate_T state, uint8_t *scan)
5864{
5865 regitem_T *rp;
5866
5867 if ((int64_t)((unsigned)regstack.ga_len >> 10) >= p_mmp) {
5868 emsg(_(e_pattern_uses_more_memory_than_maxmempattern)gettext(e_pattern_uses_more_memory_than_maxmempattern));
5869 return NULL((void*)0);
5870 }
5871 ga_grow(&regstack, sizeof(regitem_T));
5872
5873 rp = (regitem_T *)((char *)regstack.ga_data + regstack.ga_len);
5874 rp->rs_state = state;
5875 rp->rs_scan = scan;
5876
5877 regstack.ga_len += (int)sizeof(regitem_T);
5878 return rp;
5879}
5880
5881// Pop an item from the regstack.
5882static void regstack_pop(uint8_t **scan)
5883{
5884 regitem_T *rp;
5885
5886 rp = (regitem_T *)((char *)regstack.ga_data + regstack.ga_len) - 1;
5887 *scan = rp->rs_scan;
5888
5889 regstack.ga_len -= (int)sizeof(regitem_T);
5890}
5891
5892// Save the current subexpr to "bp", so that they can be restored
5893// later by restore_subexpr().
5894static void save_subexpr(regbehind_T *bp)
5895 FUNC_ATTR_NONNULL_ALL
5896{
5897 // When "rex.need_clear_subexpr" is set we don't need to save the values, only
5898 // remember that this flag needs to be set again when restoring.
5899 bp->save_need_clear_subexpr = rex.need_clear_subexpr;
5900 if (rex.need_clear_subexpr) {
5901 return;
5902 }
5903
5904 for (int i = 0; i < NSUBEXP; i++) {
5905 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
5906 bp->save_start[i].se_u.pos = rex.reg_startpos[i];
5907 bp->save_end[i].se_u.pos = rex.reg_endpos[i];
5908 } else {
5909 bp->save_start[i].se_u.ptr = rex.reg_startp[i];
5910 bp->save_end[i].se_u.ptr = rex.reg_endp[i];
5911 }
5912 }
5913}
5914
5915// Restore the subexpr from "bp".
5916static void restore_subexpr(regbehind_T *bp)
5917 FUNC_ATTR_NONNULL_ALL
5918{
5919 // Only need to restore saved values when they are not to be cleared.
5920 rex.need_clear_subexpr = bp->save_need_clear_subexpr;
5921 if (rex.need_clear_subexpr) {
5922 return;
5923 }
5924
5925 for (int i = 0; i < NSUBEXP; i++) {
5926 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
5927 rex.reg_startpos[i] = bp->save_start[i].se_u.pos;
5928 rex.reg_endpos[i] = bp->save_end[i].se_u.pos;
5929 } else {
5930 rex.reg_startp[i] = bp->save_start[i].se_u.ptr;
5931 rex.reg_endp[i] = bp->save_end[i].se_u.ptr;
5932 }
5933 }
5934}
5935/// Main matching routine
5936///
5937/// Conceptually the strategy is simple: Check to see whether the current node
5938/// matches, push an item onto the regstack and loop to see whether the rest
5939/// matches, and then act accordingly. In practice we make some effort to
5940/// avoid using the regstack, in particular by going through "ordinary" nodes
5941/// (that don't need to know whether the rest of the match failed) by a nested
5942/// loop.
5943///
5944/// @param scan Current node.
5945/// @param tm timeout limit or NULL
5946/// @param timed_out flag set on timeout or NULL
5947///
5948/// @return - true when there is a match. Leaves rex.input and rex.lnum
5949/// just after the last matched character.
5950/// - false when there is no match. Leaves rex.input and rex.lnum in an
5951/// undefined state!
5952static bool_Bool regmatch(uint8_t *scan, const proftime_T *tm, int *timed_out)
5953{
5954 uint8_t *next; // Next node.
5955 int op;
5956 int c;
5957 regitem_T *rp;
5958 int no;
5959 int status; // one of the RA_ values:
5960 int tm_count = 0;
5961
5962 // Make "regstack" and "backpos" empty. They are allocated and freed in
5963 // bt_regexec_both() to reduce malloc()/free() calls.
5964 regstack.ga_len = 0;
5965 backpos.ga_len = 0;
5966
5967 // Repeat until "regstack" is empty.
5968 while (true1) {
5969 // Some patterns may take a long time to match, e.g., "\([a-z]\+\)\+Q".
5970 // Allow interrupting them with CTRL-C.
5971 reg_breakcheck();
5972
5973#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
5974 if (scan != NULL((void*)0) && regnarrate) {
5975 fprintf(stderrstderr, "%s", (char *)regprop(scan));
5976 fprintf(stderrstderr, "%s", "(\n");
5977 }
5978#endif
5979
5980 // Repeat for items that can be matched sequentially, without using the
5981 // regstack.
5982 while (true1) {
5983 if (got_int || scan == NULL((void*)0)) {
5984 status = RA_FAIL1;
5985 break;
5986 }
5987 // Check for timeout once in a 100 times to avoid overhead.
5988 if (tm != NULL((void*)0) && ++tm_count == 100) {
5989 tm_count = 0;
5990 if (profile_passed_limit(*tm)) {
5991 if (timed_out != NULL((void*)0)) {
5992 *timed_out = true1;
5993 }
5994 status = RA_FAIL1;
5995 break;
5996 }
5997 }
5998 status = RA_CONT2;
5999
6000#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
6001 if (regnarrate) {
6002 fprintf(stderrstderr, "%s", (char *)regprop(scan));
6003 fprintf(stderrstderr, "%s", "...\n");
6004 if (re_extmatch_in != NULL((void*)0)) {
6005 int i;
6006
6007 fprintf(stderrstderr, _("External submatches:\n")gettext("External submatches:\n"));
6008 for (i = 0; i < NSUBEXP; i++) {
6009 fprintf(stderrstderr, "%s", " \"");
6010 if (re_extmatch_in->matches[i] != NULL((void*)0)) {
6011 fprintf(stderrstderr, "%s", (char *)re_extmatch_in->matches[i]);
6012 }
6013 fprintf(stderrstderr, "%s", "\"\n");
6014 }
6015 }
6016 }
6017#endif
6018 next = regnext(scan);
6019
6020 op = OP(scan)((int)(*(scan)));
6021 // Check for character class with NL added.
6022 if (!rex.reg_line_lbr && WITH_NL(op)((op) >= 20 + 30 && (op) <= 48 + 30) && REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))
6023 && *rex.input == NUL'\000' && rex.lnum <= rex.reg_maxline) {
6024 reg_nextline();
6025 } else if (rex.reg_line_lbr && WITH_NL(op)((op) >= 20 + 30 && (op) <= 48 + 30) && *rex.input == '\n') {
6026 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()(rex.input += utfc_ptr2len((char *)rex.input));
6027 } else {
6028 if (WITH_NL(op)((op) >= 20 + 30 && (op) <= 48 + 30)) {
6029 op -= ADD_NL30;
6030 }
6031 c = utf_ptr2char((char *)rex.input);
6032 switch (op) {
6033 case BOL1:
6034 if (rex.input != rex.line) {
6035 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
6036 }
6037 break;
6038
6039 case EOL2:
6040 if (c != NUL'\000') {
6041 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
6042 }
6043 break;
6044
6045 case RE_BOF201:
6046 // We're not at the beginning of the file when below the first
6047 // line where we started, not at the start of the line or we
6048 // didn't start at the first line of the buffer.
6049 if (rex.lnum != 0 || rex.input != rex.line
6050 || (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0)) && rex.reg_firstlnum > 1)) {
6051 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
6052 }
6053 break;
6054
6055 case RE_EOF202:
6056 if (rex.lnum != rex.reg_maxline || c != NUL'\000') {
6057 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
6058 }
6059 break;
6060
6061 case CURSOR203:
6062 // Check if the buffer is in a window and compare the
6063 // rex.reg_win->w_cursor position to the match position.
6064 if (rex.reg_win == NULL((void*)0)
6065 || (rex.lnum + rex.reg_firstlnum != rex.reg_win->w_cursor.lnum)
6066 || ((colnr_T)(rex.input - rex.line) !=
6067 rex.reg_win->w_cursor.col)) {
6068 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
6069 }
6070 break;
6071
6072 case RE_MARK207:
6073 // Compare the mark position to the match position.
6074 {
6075 int mark = OPERAND(scan)((scan) + 3)[0];
6076 int cmp = OPERAND(scan)((scan) + 3)[1];
6077 pos_T *pos;
6078 size_t col = REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0)) ? (size_t)(rex.input - rex.line) : 0;
6079 fmark_T *fm = mark_get(rex.reg_buf, curwin, NULL((void*)0), kMarkBufLocal, mark);
6080
6081 // Line may have been freed, get it again.
6082 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
6083 rex.line = (uint8_t *)reg_getline(rex.lnum);
6084 rex.input = rex.line + col;
6085 }
6086
6087 if (fm == NULL((void*)0) // mark doesn't exist
6088 || fm->mark.lnum <= 0) { // mark isn't set in reg_buf
6089 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
6090 } else {
6091 pos = &fm->mark;
6092 const colnr_T pos_col = pos->lnum == rex.lnum + rex.reg_firstlnum
6093 && pos->col == MAXCOL
6094 ? (colnr_T)strlen(reg_getline(pos->lnum - rex.reg_firstlnum))
6095 : pos->col;
6096
6097 if (pos->lnum == rex.lnum + rex.reg_firstlnum
6098 ? (pos_col == (colnr_T)(rex.input - rex.line)
6099 ? (cmp == '<' || cmp == '>')
6100 : (pos_col < (colnr_T)(rex.input - rex.line)
6101 ? cmp != '>'
6102 : cmp != '<'))
6103 : (pos->lnum < rex.lnum + rex.reg_firstlnum
6104 ? cmp != '>'
6105 : cmp != '<')) {
6106 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
6107 }
6108 }
6109 }
6110 break;
6111
6112 case RE_VISUAL208:
6113 if (!reg_match_visual()) {
6114 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
6115 }
6116 break;
6117
6118 case RE_LNUM204:
6119 assert(rex.lnum + rex.reg_firstlnum >= 0((void) sizeof ((rex.lnum + rex.reg_firstlnum >= 0 &&
(uintmax_t)(rex.lnum + rex.reg_firstlnum) <= (4294967295U
)) ? 1 : 0), __extension__ ({ if (rex.lnum + rex.reg_firstlnum
>= 0 && (uintmax_t)(rex.lnum + rex.reg_firstlnum)
<= (4294967295U)) ; else __assert_fail ("rex.lnum + rex.reg_firstlnum >= 0 && (uintmax_t)(rex.lnum + rex.reg_firstlnum) <= UINT32_MAX"
, "/home/runner/work/doc/doc/neovim/src/nvim/regexp.c", 6120,
__extension__ __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); }))
6120 && (uintmax_t)(rex.lnum + rex.reg_firstlnum) <= UINT32_MAX)((void) sizeof ((rex.lnum + rex.reg_firstlnum >= 0 &&
(uintmax_t)(rex.lnum + rex.reg_firstlnum) <= (4294967295U
)) ? 1 : 0), __extension__ ({ if (rex.lnum + rex.reg_firstlnum
>= 0 && (uintmax_t)(rex.lnum + rex.reg_firstlnum)
<= (4294967295U)) ; else __assert_fail ("rex.lnum + rex.reg_firstlnum >= 0 && (uintmax_t)(rex.lnum + rex.reg_firstlnum) <= UINT32_MAX"
, "/home/runner/work/doc/doc/neovim/src/nvim/regexp.c", 6120,
__extension__ __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); }));
6121 if (!REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))
6122 || !re_num_cmp((uint32_t)(rex.lnum + rex.reg_firstlnum), scan)) {
6123 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
6124 }
6125 break;
6126
6127 case RE_COL205:
6128 assert(rex.input - rex.line + 1 >= 0((void) sizeof ((rex.input - rex.line + 1 >= 0 && (
uintmax_t)(rex.input - rex.line + 1) <= (4294967295U)) ? 1
: 0), __extension__ ({ if (rex.input - rex.line + 1 >= 0 &&
(uintmax_t)(rex.input - rex.line + 1) <= (4294967295U)) ;
else __assert_fail ("rex.input - rex.line + 1 >= 0 && (uintmax_t)(rex.input - rex.line + 1) <= UINT32_MAX"
, "/home/runner/work/doc/doc/neovim/src/nvim/regexp.c", 6129,
__extension__ __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); }))
6129 && (uintmax_t)(rex.input - rex.line + 1) <= UINT32_MAX)((void) sizeof ((rex.input - rex.line + 1 >= 0 && (
uintmax_t)(rex.input - rex.line + 1) <= (4294967295U)) ? 1
: 0), __extension__ ({ if (rex.input - rex.line + 1 >= 0 &&
(uintmax_t)(rex.input - rex.line + 1) <= (4294967295U)) ;
else __assert_fail ("rex.input - rex.line + 1 >= 0 && (uintmax_t)(rex.input - rex.line + 1) <= UINT32_MAX"
, "/home/runner/work/doc/doc/neovim/src/nvim/regexp.c", 6129,
__extension__ __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); }));
6130 if (!re_num_cmp((uint32_t)(rex.input - rex.line + 1), scan)) {
6131 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
6132 }
6133 break;
6134
6135 case RE_VCOL206:
6136 if (!re_num_cmp((unsigned)win_linetabsize(rex.reg_win == NULL((void*)0) ? curwin : rex.reg_win,
6137 rex.reg_firstlnum + rex.lnum,
6138 (char *)rex.line,
6139 (colnr_T)(rex.input - rex.line)) + 1,
6140 scan)) {
6141 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
6142 }
6143 break;
6144
6145 case BOW15: // \<word; rex.input points to w
6146 if (c == NUL'\000') { // Can't match at end of line
6147 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
6148 } else {
6149 // Get class of current and previous char (if it exists).
6150 const int this_class =
6151 mb_get_class_tab((char *)rex.input, rex.reg_buf->b_chartab);
6152 if (this_class <= 1) {
6153 status = RA_NOMATCH5; // Not on a word at all.
6154 } else if (reg_prev_class() == this_class) {
6155 status = RA_NOMATCH5; // Previous char is in same word.
6156 }
6157 }
6158 break;
6159
6160 case EOW16: // word\>; rex.input points after d
6161 if (rex.input == rex.line) { // Can't match at start of line
6162 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
6163 } else {
6164 int this_class, prev_class;
6165
6166 // Get class of current and previous char (if it exists).
6167 this_class = mb_get_class_tab((char *)rex.input, rex.reg_buf->b_chartab);
6168 prev_class = reg_prev_class();
6169 if (this_class == prev_class
6170 || prev_class == 0 || prev_class == 1) {
6171 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
6172 }
6173 }
6174 break; // Matched with EOW
6175
6176 case ANY20:
6177 // ANY does not match new lines.
6178 if (c == NUL'\000') {
6179 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
6180 } else {
6181 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()(rex.input += utfc_ptr2len((char *)rex.input));
6182 }
6183 break;
6184
6185 case IDENT23:
6186 if (!vim_isIDc(c)) {
6187 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
6188 } else {
6189 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()(rex.input += utfc_ptr2len((char *)rex.input));
6190 }
6191 break;
6192
6193 case SIDENT24:
6194 if (ascii_isdigit(*rex.input) || !vim_isIDc(c)) {
6195 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
6196 } else {
6197 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()(rex.input += utfc_ptr2len((char *)rex.input));
6198 }
6199 break;
6200
6201 case KWORD25:
6202 if (!vim_iswordp_buf((char *)rex.input, rex.reg_buf)) {
6203 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
6204 } else {
6205 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()(rex.input += utfc_ptr2len((char *)rex.input));
6206 }
6207 break;
6208
6209 case SKWORD26:
6210 if (ascii_isdigit(*rex.input)
6211 || !vim_iswordp_buf((char *)rex.input, rex.reg_buf)) {
6212 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
6213 } else {
6214 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()(rex.input += utfc_ptr2len((char *)rex.input));
6215 }
6216 break;
6217
6218 case FNAME27:
6219 if (!vim_isfilec(c)) {
6220 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
6221 } else {
6222 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()(rex.input += utfc_ptr2len((char *)rex.input));
6223 }
6224 break;
6225
6226 case SFNAME28:
6227 if (ascii_isdigit(*rex.input) || !vim_isfilec(c)) {
6228 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
6229 } else {
6230 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()(rex.input += utfc_ptr2len((char *)rex.input));
6231 }
6232 break;
6233
6234 case PRINT29:
6235 if (!vim_isprintc(utf_ptr2char((char *)rex.input))) {
6236 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
6237 } else {
6238 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()(rex.input += utfc_ptr2len((char *)rex.input));
6239 }
6240 break;
6241
6242 case SPRINT30:
6243 if (ascii_isdigit(*rex.input) || !vim_isprintc(utf_ptr2char((char *)rex.input))) {
6244 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
6245 } else {
6246 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()(rex.input += utfc_ptr2len((char *)rex.input));
6247 }
6248 break;
6249
6250 case WHITE31:
6251 if (!ascii_iswhite(c)) {

6400 if (*opnd != *rex.input
6401 && (!rex.reg_ic)) {
6402 status = RA_NOMATCH5;

6423 // ignored, which is the correct behavior (sometimes)
6424 // for voweled Hebrew texts.

6426 }

6428 rex.input += len;
6429 }

6435 case ANYBUT22: {

6437
6438 if (c == NUL'\000') {
6439 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
6440 } else if ((cstrchr((char *)q, c) == NULL((void*)0)) == (op == ANYOF21)) {
6441 status = RA_NOMATCH5;

6444

6446 q += utf_ptr2len((char *)q);

6454 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
6455 break;

6681 rex.reg_startpos[no].col,

6684 &len);
6685 if (r != RA_MATCH4) {

6789 // We continue and handle the result when done.
6790 }
6791 }
6792 } else {
6793 // Range is backwards, use shortest match first
6794 if (brace_count[no] <= brace_min[no]) {
6795 rp = regstack_push(RS_BRCPLX_SHORT, scan);
6796 if (rp == NULL((void*)0)) {
