6816 if (mb_isupper(rst.nextb)) {
6817 rst.nextb_ic = mb_tolower(rst.nextb);
6818 } else {
6819 rst.nextb_ic = mb_toupper(rst.nextb);
6820 }
6821 } else {
6822 rst.nextb_ic = rst.nextb;
6823 }
6824 } else {
6825 rst.nextb = NUL'\000';
6826 rst.nextb_ic = NUL'\000';
6827 }
6828 if (op != BRACE_SIMPLE14) {
6829 rst.minval = (op == STAR7) ? 0 : 1;
6830 rst.maxval = MAX_LIMIT(32767 << 16);
6831 } else {
6832 rst.minval = bl_minval;
6833 rst.maxval = bl_maxval;
6834 }
6835
6836 // When maxval > minval, try matching as much as possible, up
6837 // to maxval. When maxval < minval, try matching at least the
6838 // minimal number (since the range is backwards, that's also
6839 // maxval!).
6840 rst.count = regrepeat(OPERAND(scan)((scan) + 3), rst.maxval);
6841 if (got_int) {
6842 status = RA_FAIL1;
6843 break;
6844 }
6845 if (rst.minval <= rst.maxval
6846 ? rst.count >= rst.minval : rst.count >= rst.maxval) {
6847 // It could match. Prepare for trying to match what
6848 // follows. The code is below. Parameters are stored in
6849 // a regstar_T on the regstack.
6850 if ((int64_t)((unsigned)regstack.ga_len >> 10) >= p_mmp) {
6851 emsg(_(e_pattern_uses_more_memory_than_maxmempattern)gettext(e_pattern_uses_more_memory_than_maxmempattern));
6852 status = RA_FAIL1;
6853 } else {
6854 ga_grow(&regstack, sizeof(regstar_T));
6855 regstack.ga_len += (int)sizeof(regstar_T);
6856 rp = regstack_push(rst.minval <= rst.maxval ? RS_STAR_LONG : RS_STAR_SHORT, scan);
6857 if (rp == NULL((void*)0)) {
6858 status = RA_FAIL1;
6859 } else {
6860 *(((regstar_T *)rp) - 1) = rst;
6861 status = RA_BREAK3; // skip the restore bits
6862 }
6863 }
6864 } else {
6865 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
6866 }
6867 }
6868 break;
6869
6870 case NOMATCH10:
6871 case MATCH9:
6872 case SUBPAT13:
6873 rp = regstack_push(RS_NOMATCH, scan);
6874 if (rp == NULL((void*)0)) {
6875 status = RA_FAIL1;
6876 } else {
6877 rp->rs_no = (int16_t)op;
6878 reg_save(&rp->rs_un.regsave, &backpos);
6879 next = OPERAND(scan)((scan) + 3);
6880 // We continue and handle the result when done.
6881 }
6882 break;
6883
6884 case BEHIND11:
6885 case NOBEHIND12:
6886 // Need a bit of room to store extra positions.
6887 if ((int64_t)((unsigned)regstack.ga_len >> 10) >= p_mmp) {
6888 emsg(_(e_pattern_uses_more_memory_than_maxmempattern)gettext(e_pattern_uses_more_memory_than_maxmempattern));
6889 status = RA_FAIL1;
6890 } else {
6891 ga_grow(&regstack, sizeof(regbehind_T));
6892 regstack.ga_len += (int)sizeof(regbehind_T);
6893 rp = regstack_push(RS_BEHIND1, scan);
6894 if (rp == NULL((void*)0)) {
6895 status = RA_FAIL1;
6896 } else {
6897 // Need to save the subexpr to be able to restore them
6898 // when there is a match but we don't use it.
6899 save_subexpr(((regbehind_T *)rp) - 1);
6900
6901 rp->rs_no = (int16_t)op;
6902 reg_save(&rp->rs_un.regsave, &backpos);
6903 // First try if what follows matches. If it does then we
6904 // check the behind match by looping.
6905 }
6906 }
6907 break;
6908
6909 case BHPOS19:
6910 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
6911 if (behind_pos.rs_u.pos.col != (colnr_T)(rex.input - rex.line)
6912 || behind_pos.rs_u.pos.lnum != rex.lnum) {
6913 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
6914 }
6915 } else if (behind_pos.rs_u.ptr != rex.input) {
6916 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
6917 }
6918 break;
6919
6920 case NEWL18:
6921 if ((c != NUL'\000' || !REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0)) || rex.lnum > rex.reg_maxline
6922 || rex.reg_line_lbr) && (c != '\n' || !rex.reg_line_lbr)) {
6923 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
6924 } else if (rex.reg_line_lbr) {
6925 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()(rex.input += utfc_ptr2len((char *)rex.input));
6926 } else {
6927 reg_nextline();
6928 }
6929 break;
6930
6931 case END0:
6932 status = RA_MATCH4; // Success!
6933 break;
6934
6935 default:
6936 iemsg(_(e_re_corr)gettext(e_re_corr));
6937#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
6938 printf("Illegal op code %d\n", op);
6939#endif
6940 status = RA_FAIL1;
6941 break;
6942 }
6943 }
6944
6945 // If we can't continue sequentially, break the inner loop.
6946 if (status != RA_CONT2) {
6947 break;
6948 }
6949
6950 // Continue in inner loop, advance to next item.
6951 scan = next;
6952 } // end of inner loop
6953
6954 // If there is something on the regstack execute the code for the state.
6955 // If the state is popped then loop and use the older state.
6956 while (!GA_EMPTY(&regstack)((&regstack)->ga_len <= 0) && status != RA_FAIL1) {
6957 rp = (regitem_T *)((char *)regstack.ga_data + regstack.ga_len) - 1;
6958 switch (rp->rs_state) {
6959 case RS_NOPEN:
6960 // Result is passed on as-is, simply pop the state.
6961 regstack_pop(&scan);
6962 break;
6963
6964 case RS_MOPEN:
6965 // Pop the state. Restore pointers when there is no match.
6966 if (status == RA_NOMATCH5) {
6967 restore_se(&rp->rs_un.sesave, &rex.reg_startpos[rp->rs_no],{ if ((rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) *(&rex.reg_startpos[
rp->rs_no]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave)->se_u.pos; else
*(&rex.reg_startp[rp->rs_no]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave
)->se_u.ptr; }
6968 &rex.reg_startp[rp->rs_no]){ if ((rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) *(&rex.reg_startpos[
rp->rs_no]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave)->se_u.pos; else
*(&rex.reg_startp[rp->rs_no]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave
)->se_u.ptr; };
6969 }
6970 regstack_pop(&scan);
6971 break;
6972
6973 case RS_ZOPEN:
6974 // Pop the state. Restore pointers when there is no match.
6975 if (status == RA_NOMATCH5) {
6976 restore_se(&rp->rs_un.sesave, &reg_startzpos[rp->rs_no],{ if ((rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) *(&reg_startzpos[rp->
rs_no]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave)->se_u.pos; else *(&
reg_startzp[rp->rs_no]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave)->se_u
.ptr; }
6977 &reg_startzp[rp->rs_no]){ if ((rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) *(&reg_startzpos[rp->
rs_no]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave)->se_u.pos; else *(&
reg_startzp[rp->rs_no]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave)->se_u
.ptr; };
6978 }
6979 regstack_pop(&scan);
6980 break;
6981
6982 case RS_MCLOSE:
6983 // Pop the state. Restore pointers when there is no match.
6984 if (status == RA_NOMATCH5) {
6985 restore_se(&rp->rs_un.sesave, &rex.reg_endpos[rp->rs_no],{ if ((rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) *(&rex.reg_endpos[rp
->rs_no]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave)->se_u.pos; else *
(&rex.reg_endp[rp->rs_no]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave
)->se_u.ptr; }
6986 &rex.reg_endp[rp->rs_no]){ if ((rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) *(&rex.reg_endpos[rp
->rs_no]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave)->se_u.pos; else *
(&rex.reg_endp[rp->rs_no]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave
)->se_u.ptr; };
6987 }
6988 regstack_pop(&scan);
6989 break;
6990
6991 case RS_ZCLOSE:
6992 // Pop the state. Restore pointers when there is no match.
6993 if (status == RA_NOMATCH5) {
6994 restore_se(&rp->rs_un.sesave, &reg_endzpos[rp->rs_no],{ if ((rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) *(&reg_endzpos[rp->
rs_no]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave)->se_u.pos; else *(&
reg_endzp[rp->rs_no]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave)->se_u
.ptr; }
6995 &reg_endzp[rp->rs_no]){ if ((rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) *(&reg_endzpos[rp->
rs_no]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave)->se_u.pos; else *(&
reg_endzp[rp->rs_no]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave)->se_u
.ptr; };
6996 }
6997 regstack_pop(&scan);
6998 break;
6999
7000 case RS_BRANCH:
7001 if (status == RA_MATCH4) {
7002 // this branch matched, use it
7003 regstack_pop(&scan);
7004 } else {
7005 if (status != RA_BREAK3) {
7006 // After a non-matching branch: try next one.
7007 reg_restore(&rp->rs_un.regsave, &backpos);
7008 scan = rp->rs_scan;
7009 }
7010 if (scan == NULL((void*)0) || OP(scan)((int)(*(scan))) != BRANCH3) {
7011 // no more branches, didn't find a match
7012 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
7013 regstack_pop(&scan);
7014 } else {
7015 // Prepare to try a branch.
7016 rp->rs_scan = regnext(scan);
7017 reg_save(&rp->rs_un.regsave, &backpos);
7018 scan = OPERAND(scan)((scan) + 3);
7019 }
7020 }
7021 break;
7022
7023 case RS_BRCPLX_MORE:
7024 // Pop the state. Restore pointers when there is no match.
7025 if (status == RA_NOMATCH5) {
7026 reg_restore(&rp->rs_un.regsave, &backpos);
7027 brace_count[rp->rs_no]--; // decrement match count
7028 }
7029 regstack_pop(&scan);
7030 break;
7031
7032 case RS_BRCPLX_LONG:
7033 // Pop the state. Restore pointers when there is no match.
7034 if (status == RA_NOMATCH5) {
7035 // There was no match, but we did find enough matches.
7036 reg_restore(&rp->rs_un.regsave, &backpos);
7037 brace_count[rp->rs_no]--;
7038 // continue with the items after "\{}"
7039 status = RA_CONT2;
7040 }
7041 regstack_pop(&scan);
7042 if (status == RA_CONT2) {
7043 scan = regnext(scan);
7044 }
7045 break;
7046
7047 case RS_BRCPLX_SHORT:
7048 // Pop the state. Restore pointers when there is no match.
7049 if (status == RA_NOMATCH5) {
7050 // There was no match, try to match one more item.
7051 reg_restore(&rp->rs_un.regsave, &backpos);
7052 }
7053 regstack_pop(&scan);
7054 if (status == RA_NOMATCH5) {
7055 scan = OPERAND(scan)((scan) + 3);
7056 status = RA_CONT2;
7057 }
7058 break;
7059
7060 case RS_NOMATCH:
7061 // Pop the state. If the operand matches for NOMATCH or
7062 // doesn't match for MATCH/SUBPAT, we fail. Otherwise backup,
7063 // except for SUBPAT, and continue with the next item.
7064 if (status == (rp->rs_no == NOMATCH10 ? RA_MATCH4 : RA_NOMATCH5)) {
7065 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
7066 } else {
7067 status = RA_CONT2;
7068 if (rp->rs_no != SUBPAT13) { // zero-width
7069 reg_restore(&rp->rs_un.regsave, &backpos);
7070 }
7071 }
7072 regstack_pop(&scan);
7073 if (status == RA_CONT2) {
7074 scan = regnext(scan);
7075 }
7076 break;
7077
7078 case RS_BEHIND1:
7079 if (status == RA_NOMATCH5) {
7080 regstack_pop(&scan);
7081 regstack.ga_len -= (int)sizeof(regbehind_T);
7082 } else {
7083 // The stuff after BEHIND/NOBEHIND matches. Now try if
7084 // the behind part does (not) match before the current
7085 // position in the input. This must be done at every
7086 // position in the input and checking if the match ends at
7087 // the current position.
7088
7089 // save the position after the found match for next
7090 reg_save(&(((regbehind_T *)rp) - 1)->save_after, &backpos);
7091
7092 // Start looking for a match with operand at the current
7093 // position. Go back one character until we find the
7094 // result, hitting the start of the line or the previous
7095 // line (for multi-line matching).
7096 // Set behind_pos to where the match should end, BHPOS
7097 // will match it. Save the current value.
7098 (((regbehind_T *)rp) - 1)->save_behind = behind_pos;
7099 behind_pos = rp->rs_un.regsave;
7100
7101 rp->rs_state = RS_BEHIND2;
7102
7103 reg_restore(&rp->rs_un.regsave, &backpos);
7104 scan = OPERAND(rp->rs_scan)((rp->rs_scan) + 3) + 4;
7105 }
7106 break;
7107
7108 case RS_BEHIND2:
7109 // Looping for BEHIND / NOBEHIND match.
7110 if (status == RA_MATCH4 && reg_save_equal(&behind_pos)) {
7111 // found a match that ends where "next" started
7112 behind_pos = (((regbehind_T *)rp) - 1)->save_behind;
7113 if (rp->rs_no == BEHIND11) {
7114 reg_restore(&(((regbehind_T *)rp) - 1)->save_after,
7115 &backpos);
7116 } else {
7117 // But we didn't want a match. Need to restore the
7118 // subexpr, because what follows matched, so they have
7119 // been set.
7120 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
7121 restore_subexpr(((regbehind_T *)rp) - 1);
7122 }
7123 regstack_pop(&scan);
7124 regstack.ga_len -= (int)sizeof(regbehind_T);
7125 } else {
7126 int64_t limit;
7127
7128 // No match or a match that doesn't end where we want it: Go
7129 // back one character. May go to previous line once.
7130 no = OK1;
7131 limit = OPERAND_MIN(rp->rs_scan)(((int64_t)(rp->rs_scan)[3] << 24) + ((int64_t)(rp->
rs_scan)[4] << 16) + ((int64_t)(rp->rs_scan)[5] <<
8) + (int64_t)(rp->rs_scan)[6]);
7132 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
7133 if (limit > 0
7134 && ((rp->rs_un.regsave.rs_u.pos.lnum
7135 < behind_pos.rs_u.pos.lnum
7136 ? (colnr_T)strlen((char *)rex.line)
7137 : behind_pos.rs_u.pos.col)
7138 - rp->rs_un.regsave.rs_u.pos.col >= limit)) {
7139 no = FAIL0;
7140 } else if (rp->rs_un.regsave.rs_u.pos.col == 0) {
7141 if (rp->rs_un.regsave.rs_u.pos.lnum
7142 < behind_pos.rs_u.pos.lnum
7143 || reg_getline(--rp->rs_un.regsave.rs_u.pos.lnum)
7144 == NULL((void*)0)) {
7145 no = FAIL0;
7146 } else {
7147 reg_restore(&rp->rs_un.regsave, &backpos);
7148 rp->rs_un.regsave.rs_u.pos.col =
7149 (colnr_T)strlen((char *)rex.line);
7150 }
7151 } else {
7152 const uint8_t *const line =
7153 (uint8_t *)reg_getline(rp->rs_un.regsave.rs_u.pos.lnum);
7154
7155 rp->rs_un.regsave.rs_u.pos.col -=
7156 utf_head_off((char *)line,
7157 (char *)line + rp->rs_un.regsave.rs_u.pos.col - 1)
7158 + 1;
7159 }
7160 } else {
7161 if (rp->rs_un.regsave.rs_u.ptr == rex.line) {
7162 no = FAIL0;
7163 } else {
7164 MB_PTR_BACK(rex.line, rp->rs_un.regsave.rs_u.ptr)(rp->rs_un.regsave.rs_u.ptr -= utf_head_off((char *)(rex.line
), (char *)(rp->rs_un.regsave.rs_u.ptr) - 1) + 1);
7165 if (limit > 0
7166 && (behind_pos.rs_u.ptr - rp->rs_un.regsave.rs_u.ptr) > (ptrdiff_t)limit) {
7167 no = FAIL0;
7168 }
7169 }
7170 }
7171 if (no == OK1) {
7172 // Advanced, prepare for finding match again.
7173 reg_restore(&rp->rs_un.regsave, &backpos);
7174 scan = OPERAND(rp->rs_scan)((rp->rs_scan) + 3) + 4;
7175 if (status == RA_MATCH4) {
7176 // We did match, so subexpr may have been changed,
7177 // need to restore them for the next try.
7178 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
7179 restore_subexpr(((regbehind_T *)rp) - 1);
7180 }
7181 } else {
7182 // Can't advance. For NOBEHIND that's a match.
7183 behind_pos = (((regbehind_T *)rp) - 1)->save_behind;
7184 if (rp->rs_no == NOBEHIND12) {
7185 reg_restore(&(((regbehind_T *)rp) - 1)->save_after,
7186 &backpos);
7187 status = RA_MATCH4;
7188 } else {
7189 // We do want a proper match. Need to restore the
7190 // subexpr if we had a match, because they may have
7191 // been set.
7192 if (status == RA_MATCH4) {
7193 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
7194 restore_subexpr(((regbehind_T *)rp) - 1);
7195 }
7196 }
7197 regstack_pop(&scan);
7198 regstack.ga_len -= (int)sizeof(regbehind_T);
7199 }
7200 }
7201 break;
7202
7203 case RS_STAR_LONG:
7204 case RS_STAR_SHORT: {
7205 regstar_T *rst = ((regstar_T *)rp) - 1;
7206
7207 if (status == RA_MATCH4) {
7208 regstack_pop(&scan);
7209 regstack.ga_len -= (int)sizeof(regstar_T);
7210 break;
7211 }
7212
7213 // Tried once already, restore input pointers.
7214 if (status != RA_BREAK3) {
7215 reg_restore(&rp->rs_un.regsave, &backpos);
7216 }
7217
7218 // Repeat until we found a position where it could match.
7219 while (true1) {
7220 if (status != RA_BREAK3) {
7221 // Tried first position already, advance.
7222 if (rp->rs_state == RS_STAR_LONG) {
7223 // Trying for longest match, but couldn't or
7224 // didn't match -- back up one char.
7225 if (--rst->count < rst->minval) {
7226 break;
7227 }
7228 if (rex.input == rex.line) {
7229 // backup to last char of previous line
7230 if (rex.lnum == 0) {
7231 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
7232 break;
7233 }
7234 rex.lnum--;
7235 rex.line = (uint8_t *)reg_getline(rex.lnum);
7236 // Just in case regrepeat() didn't count right.
7237 if (rex.line == NULL((void*)0)) {
7238 break;
7239 }
7240 rex.input = rex.line + strlen((char *)rex.line);
7241 reg_breakcheck();
7242 } else {
7243 MB_PTR_BACK(rex.line, rex.input)(rex.input -= utf_head_off((char *)(rex.line), (char *)(rex.input
) - 1) + 1);
7244 }
7245 } else {
7246 // Range is backwards, use shortest match first.
7247 // Careful: maxval and minval are exchanged!
7248 // Couldn't or didn't match: try advancing one
7249 // char.
7250 if (rst->count == rst->minval
7251 || regrepeat(OPERAND(rp->rs_scan)((rp->rs_scan) + 3), 1L) == 0) {
7252 break;
7253 }
7254 rst->count++;
7255 }
7256 if (got_int) {
7257 break;
7258 }
7259 } else {
7260 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
7261 }
7262
7263 // If it could match, try it.
7264 if (rst->nextb == NUL'\000' || *rex.input == rst->nextb
7265 || *rex.input == rst->nextb_ic) {
7266 reg_save(&rp->rs_un.regsave, &backpos);
7267 scan = regnext(rp->rs_scan);
7268 status = RA_CONT2;
7269 break;
7270 }
7271 }
7272 if (status != RA_CONT2) {
7273 // Failed.
7274 regstack_pop(&scan);
7275 regstack.ga_len -= (int)sizeof(regstar_T);
7276 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
7277 }
7278 }
7279 break;
7280 }
7281
7282 // If we want to continue the inner loop or didn't pop a state
7283 // continue matching loop
7284 if (status == RA_CONT2 || rp == (regitem_T *)
7285 ((char *)regstack.ga_data + regstack.ga_len) - 1) {
7286 break;
7287 }
7288 }
7289
7290 // May need to continue with the inner loop, starting at "scan".
7291 if (status == RA_CONT2) {
7292 continue;
7293 }
7294
7295 // If the regstack is empty or something failed we are done.
7296 if (GA_EMPTY(&regstack)((&regstack)->ga_len <= 0) || status == RA_FAIL1) {
7297 if (scan == NULL((void*)0)) {
7298 // We get here only if there's trouble -- normally "case END" is
7299 // the terminating point.
7300 iemsg(_(e_re_corr)gettext(e_re_corr));
7301#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
7302 printf("Premature EOL\n");
7303#endif
7304 }
7305 return status == RA_MATCH4;
7306 }
7307 } // End of loop until the regstack is empty.
7308
7309 // NOTREACHED
7310}
7311
7312/// Try match of "prog" with at rex.line["col"].
7313///
7314/// @param tm timeout limit or NULL
7315/// @param timed_out flag set on timeout or NULL
7316///
7317/// @return 0 for failure, or number of lines contained in the match.
7318static int regtry(bt_regprog_T *prog, colnr_T col, proftime_T *tm, int *timed_out)
7319{
7320 rex.input = rex.line + col;
7321 rex.need_clear_subexpr = true1;
7322 // Clear the external match subpointers if necessaey.
7323 rex.need_clear_zsubexpr = (prog->reghasz == REX_SET1);
7324
7325 if (regmatch(prog->program + 1, tm, timed_out) == 0) {
7326 return 0;
7327 }
7328
7329 cleanup_subexpr();
7330 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
7331 if (rex.reg_startpos[0].lnum < 0) {
7332 rex.reg_startpos[0].lnum = 0;
7333 rex.reg_startpos[0].col = col;
7334 }
7335 if (rex.reg_endpos[0].lnum < 0) {
7336 rex.reg_endpos[0].lnum = rex.lnum;
7337 rex.reg_endpos[0].col = (int)(rex.input - rex.line);
7338 } else {
7339 // Use line number of "\ze".
7340 rex.lnum = rex.reg_endpos[0].lnum;
7341 }
7342 } else {
7343 if (rex.reg_startp[0] == NULL((void*)0)) {
7344 rex.reg_startp[0] = rex.line + col;
7345 }
7346 if (rex.reg_endp[0] == NULL((void*)0)) {
7347 rex.reg_endp[0] = rex.input;
7348 }
7349 }
7350 // Package any found \z(...\) matches for export. Default is none.
7351 unref_extmatch(re_extmatch_out);
7352 re_extmatch_out = NULL((void*)0);
7353
7354 if (prog->reghasz == REX_SET1) {
7355 int i;
7356
7357 cleanup_zsubexpr();
7358 re_extmatch_out = make_extmatch();
7359 for (i = 0; i < NSUBEXP; i++) {
7360 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
7361 // Only accept single line matches.
7362 if (reg_startzpos[i].lnum >= 0
7363 && reg_endzpos[i].lnum == reg_startzpos[i].lnum
7364 && reg_endzpos[i].col >= reg_startzpos[i].col) {
7365 re_extmatch_out->matches[i] =
7366 (uint8_t *)xstrnsave(reg_getline(reg_startzpos[i].lnum) + reg_startzpos[i].col,
7367 (size_t)(reg_endzpos[i].col - reg_startzpos[i].col));
7368 }
7369 } else {
7370 if (reg_startzp[i] != NULL((void*)0) && reg_endzp[i] != NULL((void*)0)) {
7371 re_extmatch_out->matches[i] =
7372 (uint8_t *)xstrnsave((char *)reg_startzp[i], (size_t)(reg_endzp[i] - reg_startzp[i]));
7373 }
7374 }
7375 }
7376 }
7377 return 1 + rex.lnum;
7378}
7379
7380/// Match a regexp against a string ("line" points to the string) or multiple
7381/// lines (if "line" is NULL, use reg_getline()).
7382///
7383/// @param startcol column to start looking for match
7384/// @param tm timeout limit or NULL
7385/// @param timed_out flag set on timeout or NULL
7386///
7387/// @return 0 for failure, or number of lines contained in the match.
7388static int bt_regexec_both(uint8_t *line, colnr_T startcol, proftime_T *tm, int *timed_out)
7389{
7390 bt_regprog_T *prog;
7391 uint8_t *s;
7392 colnr_T col = startcol;
7393 int retval = 0;
7394
7395 // Create "regstack" and "backpos" if they are not allocated yet.
7396 // We allocate *_INITIAL amount of bytes first and then set the grow size
7397 // to much bigger value to avoid many malloc calls in case of deep regular
7398 // expressions.
7399 if (regstack.ga_data == NULL((void*)0)) {
7400 // Use an item size of 1 byte, since we push different things
7401 // onto the regstack.
7402 ga_init(&regstack, 1, REGSTACK_INITIAL2048);
7403 ga_grow(&regstack, REGSTACK_INITIAL2048);
7404 ga_set_growsize(&regstack, REGSTACK_INITIAL2048 * 8);
7405 }
7406
7407 if (backpos.ga_data == NULL((void*)0)) {
7408 ga_init(&backpos, sizeof(backpos_T), BACKPOS_INITIAL64);
7409 ga_grow(&backpos, BACKPOS_INITIAL64);
7410 ga_set_growsize(&backpos, BACKPOS_INITIAL64 * 8);
7411 }
7412
7413 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
7414 prog = (bt_regprog_T *)rex.reg_mmatch->regprog;
7415 line = (uint8_t *)reg_getline(0);
7416 rex.reg_startpos = rex.reg_mmatch->startpos;
7417 rex.reg_endpos = rex.reg_mmatch->endpos;
7418 } else {
7419 prog = (bt_regprog_T *)rex.reg_match->regprog;
7420 rex.reg_startp = (uint8_t **)rex.reg_match->startp;
7421 rex.reg_endp = (uint8_t **)rex.reg_match->endp;
7422 }
7423
7424 // Be paranoid...
7425 if (prog == NULL((void*)0) || line == NULL((void*)0)) {
7426 iemsg(_(e_null)gettext(e_null));
7427 goto theend;
7428 }
7429
7430 // Check validity of program.
7431 if (prog_magic_wrong()) {
7432 goto theend;
7433 }
7434
7435 // If the start column is past the maximum column: no need to try.
7436 if (rex.reg_maxcol > 0 && col >= rex.reg_maxcol) {
7437 goto theend;
7438 }
7439
7440 // If pattern contains "\c" or "\C": overrule value of rex.reg_ic
7441 if (prog->regflags & RF_ICASE1) {
7442 rex.reg_ic = true1;
7443 } else if (prog->regflags & RF_NOICASE2) {
7444 rex.reg_ic = false0;
7445 }
7446
7447 // If pattern contains "\Z" overrule value of rex.reg_icombine
7448 if (prog->regflags & RF_ICOMBINE8) {
7449 rex.reg_icombine = true1;
7450 }
7451
7452 // If there is a "must appear" string, look for it.
7453 if (prog->regmust != NULL((void*)0)) {
7454 int c = utf_ptr2char((char *)prog->regmust);
7455 s = line + col;
7456
7457 // This is used very often, esp. for ":global". Use two versions of
7458 // the loop to avoid overhead of conditions.
7459 if (!rex.reg_ic) {
7460 while ((s = (uint8_t *)vim_strchr((char *)s, c)) != NULL((void*)0)) {
7461 if (cstrncmp((char *)s, (char *)prog->regmust, &prog->regmlen) == 0) {
7462 break; // Found it.
7463 }
7464 MB_PTR_ADV(s)(s += utfc_ptr2len((char *)s));
7465 }
7466 } else {
7467 while ((s = (uint8_t *)cstrchr((char *)s, c)) != NULL((void*)0)) {
7468 if (cstrncmp((char *)s, (char *)prog->regmust, &prog->regmlen) == 0) {
7469 break; // Found it.
7470 }
7471 MB_PTR_ADV(s)(s += utfc_ptr2len((char *)s));
7472 }
7473 }
7474 if (s == NULL((void*)0)) { // Not present.
7475 goto theend;
7476 }
7477 }
7478
7479 rex.line = line;
7480 rex.lnum = 0;
7481 reg_toolong = false0;
7482
7483 // Simplest case: Anchored match need be tried only once.
7484 if (prog->reganch) {
7485 int c = utf_ptr2char((char *)rex.line + col);
7486 if (prog->regstart == NUL'\000'
7487 || prog->regstart == c
7488 || (rex.reg_ic
7489 && (utf_fold(prog->regstart) == utf_fold(c)
7490 || (c < 255 && prog->regstart < 255
7491 && mb_tolower(prog->regstart) == mb_tolower(c))))) {
7492 retval = regtry(prog, col, tm, timed_out);
7493 } else {
7494 retval = 0;
7495 }
7496 } else {
7497 int tm_count = 0;
7498 // Messy cases: unanchored match.
7499 while (!got_int) {
7500 if (prog->regstart != NUL'\000') {
7501 // Skip until the char we know it must start with.
7502 s = (uint8_t *)cstrchr((char *)rex.line + col, prog->regstart);
7503 if (s == NULL((void*)0)) {
7504 retval = 0;
7505 break;
7506 }
7507 col = (int)(s - rex.line);
7508 }
7509
7510 // Check for maximum column to try.
7511 if (rex.reg_maxcol > 0 && col >= rex.reg_maxcol) {
7512 retval = 0;
7513 break;
7514 }
7515
7516 retval = regtry(prog, col, tm, timed_out);
7517 if (retval > 0) {
7518 break;
7519 }
7520
7521 // if not currently on the first line, get it again
7522 if (rex.lnum != 0) {
7523 rex.lnum = 0;
7524 rex.line = (uint8_t *)reg_getline(0);
7525 }
7526 if (rex.line[col] == NUL'\000') {
7527 break;
7528 }
7529 col += utfc_ptr2len((char *)rex.line + col);
7530 // Check for timeout once in a twenty times to avoid overhead.
7531 if (tm != NULL((void*)0) && ++tm_count == 20) {
7532 tm_count = 0;
7533 if (profile_passed_limit(*tm)) {
7534 if (timed_out != NULL((void*)0)) {
7535 *timed_out = true1;
7536 }
7537 break;
7538 }
7539 }
7540 }
7541 }
7542
7543theend:
7544 // Free "reg_tofree" when it's a bit big.
7545 // Free regstack and backpos if they are bigger than their initial size.
7546 if (reg_tofreelen > 400) {
7547 XFREE_CLEAR(reg_tofree)do { void **ptr_ = (void **)&(reg_tofree); xfree(*ptr_); *
ptr_ = ((void*)0); (void)(*ptr_); } while (0);
7548 }
7549 if (regstack.ga_maxlen > REGSTACK_INITIAL2048) {
7550 ga_clear(&regstack);
7551 }
7552 if (backpos.ga_maxlen > BACKPOS_INITIAL64) {
7553 ga_clear(&backpos);
7554 }
7555
7556 if (retval > 0) {
7557 // Make sure the end is never before the start. Can happen when \zs
7558 // and \ze are used.
7559 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
7560 const lpos_T *const start = &rex.reg_mmatch->startpos[0];
7561 const lpos_T *const end = &rex.reg_mmatch->endpos[0];
7562
7563 if (end->lnum < start->lnum
7564 || (end->lnum == start->lnum && end->col < start->col)) {
7565 rex.reg_mmatch->endpos[0] = rex.reg_mmatch->startpos[0];
7566 }
7567
7568 // startpos[0] may be set by "\zs", also return the column where
7569 // the whole pattern matched.
7570 rex.reg_mmatch->rmm_matchcol = col;
7571 } else {
7572 if (rex.reg_match->endp[0] < rex.reg_match->startp[0]) {
7573 rex.reg_match->endp[0] = rex.reg_match->startp[0];
7574 }
7575
7576 // startpos[0] may be set by "\zs", also return the column where
7577 // the whole pattern matched.
7578 rex.reg_match->rm_matchcol = col;
7579 }
7580 }
7581
7582 return retval;
7583}
7584
7585/// Match a regexp against a string.
7586/// "rmp->regprog" is a compiled regexp as returned by vim_regcomp().
7587/// Uses curbuf for line count and 'iskeyword'.
7588/// If "line_lbr" is true, consider a "\n" in "line" to be a line break.
7589///
7590/// @param line string to match against
7591/// @param col column to start looking for match
7592///
7593/// @return 0 for failure, number of lines contained in the match otherwise.
7594static int bt_regexec_nl(regmatch_T *rmp, uint8_t *line, colnr_T col, bool_Bool line_lbr)
7595{
7596 rex.reg_match = rmp;
7597 rex.reg_mmatch = NULL((void*)0);
7598 rex.reg_maxline = 0;
7599 rex.reg_line_lbr = line_lbr;
7600 rex.reg_buf = curbuf;
7601 rex.reg_win = NULL((void*)0);
7602 rex.reg_ic = rmp->rm_ic;
7603 rex.reg_icombine = false0;
7604 rex.reg_nobreak = rmp->regprog->re_flags & RE_NOBREAK16;
7605 rex.reg_maxcol = 0;
7606
7607 int64_t r = bt_regexec_both(line, col, NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0));
7608 assert(r <= INT_MAX)((void) sizeof ((r <= 2147483647) ? 1 : 0), __extension__ (
{ if (r <= 2147483647) ; else __assert_fail ("r <= INT_MAX"
, "/home/runner/work/doc/doc/neovim/src/nvim/regexp.c", 7608,
__extension__ __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); }));
7609 return (int)r;
7610}
7611
7612/// Matches a regexp against multiple lines.
7613/// "rmp->regprog" is a compiled regexp as returned by vim_regcomp().
7614/// Uses curbuf for line count and 'iskeyword'.
7615///
7616/// @param win Window in which to search or NULL
7617/// @param buf Buffer in which to search
7618/// @param lnum Number of line to start looking for match
7619/// @param col Column to start looking for match
7620/// @param tm Timeout limit or NULL
7621///
7622/// @return zero if there is no match and number of lines contained in the match
7623/// otherwise.
7624static int bt_regexec_multi(regmmatch_T *rmp, win_T *win, buf_T *buf, linenr_T lnum, colnr_T col,
7625 proftime_T *tm, int *timed_out)
7626{
7627 init_regexec_multi(rmp, win, buf, lnum);
7628 return bt_regexec_both(NULL((void*)0), col, tm, timed_out);
7629}
7630
7631// Compare a number with the operand of RE_LNUM, RE_COL or RE_VCOL.
7632static int re_num_cmp(uint32_t val, const uint8_t *scan)
7633{
7634 uint32_t n = (uint32_t)OPERAND_MIN(scan)(((int64_t)(scan)[3] << 24) + ((int64_t)(scan)[4] <<
16) + ((int64_t)(scan)[5] << 8) + (int64_t)(scan)[6]);
7635
7636 if (OPERAND_CMP(scan)(scan)[7] == '>') {
7637 return val > n;
7638 }
7639 if (OPERAND_CMP(scan)(scan)[7] == '<') {
7640 return val < n;
7641 }
7642 return val == n;
7643}
7644
7645#ifdef BT_REGEXP_DUMP
7646
7647// regdump - dump a regexp onto stdout in vaguely comprehensible form
7648static void regdump(uint8_t *pattern, bt_regprog_T *r)
7649{
7650 uint8_t *s;
7651 int op = EXACTLY5; // Arbitrary non-END op.
7652 uint8_t *next;
7653 uint8_t *end = NULL((void*)0);
7654 FILE *f;
7655
7656# ifdef BT_REGEXP_LOG
7657 f = fopen("bt_regexp_log.log", "a");
7658# else
7659 f = stdoutstdout;
7660# endif
7661 if (f == NULL((void*)0)) {
7662 return;
7663 }
7664 fprintf(f, "-------------------------------------\n\r\nregcomp(%s):\r\n",
7665 pattern);
7666
7667 s = r->program + 1;
7668 // Loop until we find the END that isn't before a referred next (an END
7669 // can also appear in a NOMATCH operand).
7670 while (op != END0 || s <= end) {
7671 op = OP(s)((int)(*(s)));
7672 fprintf(f, "%2d%s", (int)(s - r->program), regprop(s)); // Where, what.
7673 next = regnext(s);
7674 if (next == NULL((void*)0)) { // Next ptr.
7675 fprintf(f, "(0)");
7676 } else {
7677 fprintf(f, "(%d)", (int)((s - r->program) + (next - s)));
7678 }
7679 if (end < next) {
7680 end = next;
7681 }
7682 if (op == BRACE_LIMITS17) {
7683 // Two ints
7684 fprintf(f, " minval %" PRId64"l" "d" ", maxval %" PRId64"l" "d",
7685 (int64_t)OPERAND_MIN(s)(((int64_t)(s)[3] << 24) + ((int64_t)(s)[4] << 16
) + ((int64_t)(s)[5] << 8) + (int64_t)(s)[6]), (int64_t)OPERAND_MAX(s)(((int64_t)((s) + 4)[3] << 24) + ((int64_t)((s) + 4)[4]
<< 16) + ((int64_t)((s) + 4)[5] << 8) + (int64_t
)((s) + 4)[6]));
7686 s += 8;
7687 } else if (op == BEHIND11 || op == NOBEHIND12) {
7688 // one int
7689 fprintf(f, " count %" PRId64"l" "d", (int64_t)OPERAND_MIN(s)(((int64_t)(s)[3] << 24) + ((int64_t)(s)[4] << 16
) + ((int64_t)(s)[5] << 8) + (int64_t)(s)[6]));
7690 s += 4;
7691 } else if (op == RE_LNUM204 || op == RE_COL205 || op == RE_VCOL206) {
7692 // one int plus comparator
7693 fprintf(f, " count %" PRId64"l" "d", (int64_t)OPERAND_MIN(s)(((int64_t)(s)[3] << 24) + ((int64_t)(s)[4] << 16
) + ((int64_t)(s)[5] << 8) + (int64_t)(s)[6]));
7694 s += 5;
7695 }
7696 s += 3;
7697 if (op == ANYOF21 || op == ANYOF21 + ADD_NL30
7698 || op == ANYBUT22 || op == ANYBUT22 + ADD_NL30
7699 || op == EXACTLY5) {
7700 // Literal string, where present.
7701 fprintf(f, "\nxxxxxxxxx\n");
7702 while (*s != NUL'\000') {
7703 fprintf(f, "%c", *s++);
7704 }
7705 fprintf(f, "\nxxxxxxxxx\n");
7706 s++;
7707 }
7708 fprintf(f, "\r\n");
7709 }
7710
7711 // Header fields of interest.
7712 if (r->regstart != NUL'\000') {
7713 fprintf(f, "start `%s' 0x%x; ", r->regstart < 256
7714 ? (char *)transchar(r->regstart)
7715 : "multibyte", r->regstart);
7716 }
7717 if (r->reganch) {
7718 fprintf(f, "anchored; ");
7719 }
7720 if (r->regmust != NULL((void*)0)) {
7721 fprintf(f, "must have \"%s\"", r->regmust);
7722 }
7723 fprintf(f, "\r\n");
7724
7725# ifdef BT_REGEXP_LOG
7726 fclose(f);
7727# endif
7728}
7729#endif // BT_REGEXP_DUMP

7999 case BACKREF100 + 3:
8000 case BACKREF100 + 4:
8001 case BACKREF100 + 5:
8002 case BACKREF100 + 6:
8003 case BACKREF100 + 7:
8004 case BACKREF100 + 8:
8005 case BACKREF100 + 9:
8006 snprintf(buf + strlen(buf), sizeof(buf) - strlen(buf), "BACKREF%d", OP(op)((int)(*(op))) - BACKREF100);
8007 p = NULL((void*)0);
8008 break;
8009 case NOPEN150:
8010 p = "NOPEN";
8011 break;

8014 break;
8015 case ZOPEN110 + 1:

8023 case ZOPEN110 + 9:
8024 snprintf(buf + strlen(buf), sizeof(buf) - strlen(buf), "ZOPEN%d", OP(op)((int)(*(op))) - ZOPEN110);
8025 p = NULL((void*)0);
8026 break;
8027 case ZCLOSE120 + 1:

8037 p = NULL((void*)0);
8038 break;
8039 case ZREF130 + 1:

8077 break;

8089 OP(op)((int)(*(op))) - BRACE_COMPLEX140);

8100 p = NULL((void*)0);
8101 break;
8102 }
8103 if (p != NULL((void*)0)) {
8104 STRCAT(buf, p)strcat((char *)(buf), (char *)(p));
8105 }
8106 return (uint8_t *)buf;
8107}

8112// regexp_nfa.c {{{1
8113// NFA regular expression implementation.
8114
8115// Logging of NFA engine.
8116//
8117// The NFA engine can write four log files:
8118// - Error log: Contains NFA engine's fatal errors.
8119// - Dump log: Contains compiled NFA state machine's information.
8120// - Run log: Contains information of matching procedure.
8121// - Debug log: Contains detailed information of matching procedure. Can be
8122// disabled by undefining NFA_REGEXP_DEBUG_LOG.
8123// The first one can also be used without debug mode.
8124// The last three are enabled when compiled as debug mode and individually
8125// disabled by commenting them out.
8126// The log files can get quite big!
8127// To disable all of this when compiling Vim for debugging, undefine REGEXP_DEBUG in
8128// regexp.c
8129#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
8130# define NFA_REGEXP_ERROR_LOG "nfa_regexp_error.log"
8131# define NFA_REGEXP_DUMP_LOG "nfa_regexp_dump.log"
8132# define NFA_REGEXP_RUN_LOG "nfa_regexp_run.log"
8133# define NFA_REGEXP_DEBUG_LOG "nfa_regexp_debug.log"
8134#endif

8350// Variables only used in nfa_regcomp() and descendants.
8351static int nfa_re_flags; ///< re_flags passed to nfa_regcomp().
8352static int *post_start; ///< holds the postfix form of r.e.
8353static int *post_end;
8354static int *post_ptr;
8355
8356// Set when the pattern should use the NFA engine.
8357// E.g. [[:upper:]] only allows 8bit characters for BT engine,
8358// while NFA engine handles multibyte characters correctly.
8359static bool_Bool wants_nfa;
8360
8361static int nstate; ///< Number of states in the NFA. Also used when executing.
8362static int istate; ///< Index in the state vector, used in alloc_state()
8363
8364// If not NULL match must end at this position
8365static save_se_T *nfa_endp = NULL((void*)0);
8366
8367// 0 for first call to nfa_regmatch(), 1 for recursive call.
8368static int nfa_ll_index = 0;
8369
8370// Helper functions used when doing re2post() ... regatom() parsing
8371#define EMIT(c)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = c; } while (0) \
8372 do { \
8373 if (post_ptr >= post_end) { \
8374 realloc_post_list(); \
8375 } \
8376 *post_ptr++ = c; \
8377 } while (0)
8378
8379/// Initialize internal variables before NFA compilation.
8380///
8381/// @param re_flags @see vim_regcomp()
8382static void nfa_regcomp_start(uint8_t *expr, int re_flags)
8383{
8384 size_t postfix_size;
8385 size_t nstate_max;
8386
8387 nstate = 0;
8388 istate = 0;
8389 // A reasonable estimation for maximum size
8390 nstate_max = (strlen((char *)expr) + 1) * 25;
8391
8392 // Some items blow up in size, such as [A-z]. Add more space for that.
8393 // When it is still not enough realloc_post_list() will be used.
8394 nstate_max += 1000;
8395
8396 // Size for postfix representation of expr.
8397 postfix_size = sizeof(int) * nstate_max;
8398
8399 post_start = (int *)xmalloc(postfix_size);
8400 post_ptr = post_start;
8401 post_end = post_start + nstate_max;
8402 wants_nfa = false0;
8403 rex.nfa_has_zend = false0;
8404 rex.nfa_has_backref = false0;
8405
8406 // shared with BT engine
8407 regcomp_start(expr, re_flags);
8408}
8409
8410// Figure out if the NFA state list starts with an anchor, must match at start
8411// of the line.
8412static int nfa_get_reganch(nfa_state_T *start, int depth)
8413{
8414 nfa_state_T *p = start;
8415
8416 if (depth > 4) {
8417 return 0;
8418 }
8419
8420 while (p != NULL((void*)0)) {
8421 switch (p->c) {
8422 case NFA_BOL:
8423 case NFA_BOF:
8424 return 1; // yes!
8425
8426 case NFA_ZSTART:
8427 case NFA_ZEND:
8428 case NFA_CURSOR:
8429 case NFA_VISUAL:
8430
8431 case NFA_MOPEN:
8432 case NFA_MOPEN1:
8433 case NFA_MOPEN2:
8434 case NFA_MOPEN3:
8435 case NFA_MOPEN4:
8436 case NFA_MOPEN5:
8437 case NFA_MOPEN6:
8438 case NFA_MOPEN7:
8439 case NFA_MOPEN8:
8440 case NFA_MOPEN9:
8441 case NFA_NOPEN:
8442 case NFA_ZOPEN:
8443 case NFA_ZOPEN1:
8444 case NFA_ZOPEN2:
8445 case NFA_ZOPEN3:
8446 case NFA_ZOPEN4:
8447 case NFA_ZOPEN5:
8448 case NFA_ZOPEN6:
8449 case NFA_ZOPEN7:
8450 case NFA_ZOPEN8:
8451 case NFA_ZOPEN9:
8452 p = p->out;
8453 break;
8454
8455 case NFA_SPLIT:
8456 return nfa_get_reganch(p->out, depth + 1)
8457 && nfa_get_reganch(p->out1, depth + 1);
8458
8459 default:
8460 return 0; // noooo
8461 }
8462 }
8463 return 0;
8464}
8465
8466// Figure out if the NFA state list starts with a character which must match
8467// at start of the match.
8468static int nfa_get_regstart(nfa_state_T *start, int depth)
8469{
8470 nfa_state_T *p = start;
8471
8472 if (depth > 4) {
8473 return 0;
8474 }
8475
8476 while (p != NULL((void*)0)) {
8477 switch (p->c) {
8478 // all kinds of zero-width matches
8479 case NFA_BOL:
8480 case NFA_BOF:
8481 case NFA_BOW:
8482 case NFA_EOW:
8483 case NFA_ZSTART:
8484 case NFA_ZEND:
8485 case NFA_CURSOR:
8486 case NFA_VISUAL:
8487 case NFA_LNUM:
8488 case NFA_LNUM_GT:
8489 case NFA_LNUM_LT:
8490 case NFA_COL:
8491 case NFA_COL_GT:
8492 case NFA_COL_LT:
8493 case NFA_VCOL:
8494 case NFA_VCOL_GT:
8495 case NFA_VCOL_LT:
8496 case NFA_MARK:
8497 case NFA_MARK_GT:
8498 case NFA_MARK_LT:
8499
8500 case NFA_MOPEN:
8501 case NFA_MOPEN1:
8502 case NFA_MOPEN2:
8503 case NFA_MOPEN3:
8504 case NFA_MOPEN4:
8505 case NFA_MOPEN5:
8506 case NFA_MOPEN6:
8507 case NFA_MOPEN7:
8508 case NFA_MOPEN8:
8509 case NFA_MOPEN9:
8510 case NFA_NOPEN:
8511 case NFA_ZOPEN:
8512 case NFA_ZOPEN1:
8513 case NFA_ZOPEN2:
8514 case NFA_ZOPEN3:
8515 case NFA_ZOPEN4:
8516 case NFA_ZOPEN5:
8517 case NFA_ZOPEN6:
8518 case NFA_ZOPEN7:
8519 case NFA_ZOPEN8:
8520 case NFA_ZOPEN9:
8521 p = p->out;
8522 break;
8523
8524 case NFA_SPLIT: {
8525 int c1 = nfa_get_regstart(p->out, depth + 1);
8526 int c2 = nfa_get_regstart(p->out1, depth + 1);
8527
8528 if (c1 == c2) {
8529 return c1; // yes!
8530 }
8531 return 0;
8532 }
8533
8534 default:
8535 if (p->c > 0) {
8536 return p->c; // yes!
8537 }
8538 return 0;
8539 }
8540 }
8541 return 0;
8542}
8543
8544// Figure out if the NFA state list contains just literal text and nothing
8545// else. If so return a string in allocated memory with what must match after
8546// regstart. Otherwise return NULL.
8547static uint8_t *nfa_get_match_text(nfa_state_T *start)
8548{
8549 nfa_state_T *p = start;
8550 int len = 0;
8551 uint8_t *ret;
8552 uint8_t *s;
8553
8554 if (p->c != NFA_MOPEN) {
8555 return NULL((void*)0); // just in case
8556 }
8557 p = p->out;
8558 while (p->c > 0) {
8559 len += utf_char2len(p->c);
8560 p = p->out;
8561 }
8562 if (p->c != NFA_MCLOSE || p->out->c != NFA_MATCH) {
8563 return NULL((void*)0);
8564 }
8565
8566 ret = xmalloc((size_t)len);
8567 p = start->out->out; // skip first char, it goes into regstart
8568 s = ret;
8569 while (p->c > 0) {
8570 s += utf_char2bytes(p->c, (char *)s);
8571 p = p->out;
8572 }
8573 *s = NUL'\000';
8574
8575 return ret;
8576}
8577
8578// Allocate more space for post_start. Called when
8579// running above the estimated number of states.
8580static void realloc_post_list(void)
8581{
8582 // For weird patterns the number of states can be very high. Increasing by
8583 // 50% seems a reasonable compromise between memory use and speed.
8584 const size_t new_max = (size_t)(post_end - post_start) * 3 / 2;
8585 int *new_start = xrealloc(post_start, new_max * sizeof(int));
8586 post_ptr = new_start + (post_ptr - post_start);
8587 post_end = new_start + new_max;
8588 post_start = new_start;
8589}
8590
8591// Search between "start" and "end" and try to recognize a
8592// character class in expanded form. For example [0-9].
8593// On success, return the id the character class to be emitted.
8594// On failure, return 0 (=FAIL)
8595// Start points to the first char of the range, while end should point
8596// to the closing brace.
8597// Keep in mind that 'ignorecase' applies at execution time, thus [a-z] may
8598// need to be interpreted as [a-zA-Z].
8599static int nfa_recognize_char_class(uint8_t *start, const uint8_t *end, int extra_newl)
8600{
8601#define CLASS_not0x80 0x80
8602#define CLASS_af0x40 0x40
8603#define CLASS_AF0x20 0x20
8604#define CLASS_az0x10 0x10
8605#define CLASS_AZ0x08 0x08
8606#define CLASS_o70x04 0x04
8607#define CLASS_o90x02 0x02
8608#define CLASS_underscore0x01 0x01
8609
8610 uint8_t *p;
8611 int config = 0;
8612
8613 bool_Bool newl = extra_newl == true1;
8614
8615 if (*end != ']') {
8616 return FAIL0;
8617 }
8618 p = start;
8619 if (*p == '^') {
8620 config |= CLASS_not0x80;
8621 p++;
8622 }
8623
8624 while (p < end) {
8625 if (p + 2 < end && *(p + 1) == '-') {
8626 switch (*p) {
8627 case '0':
8628 if (*(p + 2) == '9') {
8629 config |= CLASS_o90x02;
8630 break;
8631 } else if (*(p + 2) == '7') {
8632 config |= CLASS_o70x04;
8633 break;
8634 }
8635 return FAIL0;
8636 case 'a':
8637 if (*(p + 2) == 'z') {
8638 config |= CLASS_az0x10;
8639 break;
8640 } else if (*(p + 2) == 'f') {
8641 config |= CLASS_af0x40;
8642 break;
8643 }
8644 return FAIL0;
8645 case 'A':
8646 if (*(p + 2) == 'Z') {
8647 config |= CLASS_AZ0x08;
8648 break;
8649 } else if (*(p + 2) == 'F') {
8650 config |= CLASS_AF0x20;
8651 break;
8652 }
8653 return FAIL0;
8654 default:
8655 return FAIL0;
8656 }
8657 p += 3;
8658 } else if (p + 1 < end && *p == '\\' && *(p + 1) == 'n') {
8659 newl = true1;
8660 p += 2;
8661 } else if (*p == '_') {
8662 config |= CLASS_underscore0x01;
8663 p++;
8664 } else if (*p == '\n') {
8665 newl = true1;
8666 p++;
8667 } else {
8668 return FAIL0;
8669 }
8670 } // while (p < end)
8671
8672 if (p != end) {
8673 return FAIL0;
8674 }
8675
8676 if (newl == true1) {
8677 extra_newl = NFA_ADD_NL31;
8678 }
8679
8680 switch (config) {
8681 case CLASS_o90x02:
8682 return extra_newl + NFA_DIGIT;
8683 case CLASS_not0x80 | CLASS_o90x02:
8684 return extra_newl + NFA_NDIGIT;
8685 case CLASS_af0x40 | CLASS_AF0x20 | CLASS_o90x02:
8686 return extra_newl + NFA_HEX;
8687 case CLASS_not0x80 | CLASS_af0x40 | CLASS_AF0x20 | CLASS_o90x02:
8688 return extra_newl + NFA_NHEX;
8689 case CLASS_o70x04:
8690 return extra_newl + NFA_OCTAL;
8691 case CLASS_not0x80 | CLASS_o70x04:
8692 return extra_newl + NFA_NOCTAL;
8693 case CLASS_az0x10 | CLASS_AZ0x08 | CLASS_o90x02 | CLASS_underscore0x01:
8694 return extra_newl + NFA_WORD;
8695 case CLASS_not0x80 | CLASS_az0x10 | CLASS_AZ0x08 | CLASS_o90x02 | CLASS_underscore0x01:
8696 return extra_newl + NFA_NWORD;
8697 case CLASS_az0x10 | CLASS_AZ0x08 | CLASS_underscore0x01:
8698 return extra_newl + NFA_HEAD;
8699 case CLASS_not0x80 | CLASS_az0x10 | CLASS_AZ0x08 | CLASS_underscore0x01:
8700 return extra_newl + NFA_NHEAD;
8701 case CLASS_az0x10 | CLASS_AZ0x08:
8702 return extra_newl + NFA_ALPHA;
8703 case CLASS_not0x80 | CLASS_az0x10 | CLASS_AZ0x08:
8704 return extra_newl + NFA_NALPHA;
8705 case CLASS_az0x10:
8706 return extra_newl + NFA_LOWER_IC;
8707 case CLASS_not0x80 | CLASS_az0x10:
8708 return extra_newl + NFA_NLOWER_IC;
8709 case CLASS_AZ0x08:
8710 return extra_newl + NFA_UPPER_IC;
8711 case CLASS_not0x80 | CLASS_AZ0x08:
8712 return extra_newl + NFA_NUPPER_IC;
8713 }
8714 return FAIL0;
8715}
8716
8717// Produce the bytes for equivalence class "c".
8718// Currently only handles latin1, latin9 and utf-8.
8719// Emits bytes in postfix notation: 'a,b,NFA_OR,c,NFA_OR' is
8720// equivalent to 'a OR b OR c'
8721//
8722// NOTE! When changing this function, also update reg_equi_class()

8724{
8725#define EMIT2(c) EMIT(c)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = c; } while (0); EMIT(NFA_CONCAT)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CONCAT; } while (0);
