9734 case 0x1e81:
9735 case 0x1e83:
9736 case 0x1e85:
9737 case 0x1e87:
9738 case 0x1e89:
9739 case 0x1e98:
9740 EMIT2('w') EMIT2(0x175) EMIT2(0x1e81) EMIT2(0x1e83)
9741 EMIT2(0x1e85) EMIT2(0x1e87) EMIT2(0x1e89) EMIT2(0x1e98)
9742 return;
9743
9744 case 'x':
9745 case 0x1e8b:
9746 case 0x1e8d:
9747 EMIT2('x') EMIT2(0x1e8b) EMIT2(0x1e8d)
9748 return;
9749
9750 case 'y':
9751 case y_acute0xfd:
9752 case y_diaeresis0xff:
9753 case 0x177:
9754 case 0x1b4:
9755 case 0x233:
9756 case 0x24f:
9757 case 0x1e8f:
9758 case 0x1e99:
9759 case 0x1ef3:
9760 case 0x1ef5:
9761 case 0x1ef7:
9762 case 0x1ef9:
9763 EMIT2('y') EMIT2(y_acute0xfd) EMIT2(y_diaeresis0xff)
9764 EMIT2(0x177) EMIT2(0x1b4) EMIT2(0x233) EMIT2(0x24f)
9765 EMIT2(0x1e8f) EMIT2(0x1e99) EMIT2(0x1ef3)
9766 EMIT2(0x1ef5) EMIT2(0x1ef7) EMIT2(0x1ef9)
9767 return;
9768
9769 case 'z':
9770 case 0x17a:
9771 case 0x17c:
9772 case 0x17e:
9773 case 0x1b6:
9774 case 0x1d76:
9775 case 0x1d8e:
9776 case 0x1e91:
9777 case 0x1e93:
9778 case 0x1e95:
9779 case 0x2c6c:
9780 EMIT2('z') EMIT2(0x17a) EMIT2(0x17c) EMIT2(0x17e)
9781 EMIT2(0x1b6) EMIT2(0x1d76) EMIT2(0x1d8e) EMIT2(0x1e91)
9782 EMIT2(0x1e93) EMIT2(0x1e95) EMIT2(0x2c6c)
9783 return;
9784
9785 // default: character itself
9786 }
9787 }
9788
9789 EMIT2(c);
9790#undef EMIT2
9791}
9792
9793// Code to parse regular expression.
9794//
9795// We try to reuse parsing functions in regexp.c to
9796// minimize surprise and keep the syntax consistent.
9797
9798// Parse the lowest level.
9799//
9800// An atom can be one of a long list of items. Many atoms match one character
9801// in the text. It is often an ordinary character or a character class.
9802// Braces can be used to make a pattern into an atom. The "\z(\)" construct
9803// is only for syntax highlighting.
9804//
9805// atom ::= ordinary-atom
9806// or \( pattern \)
9807// or \%( pattern \)
9808// or \z( pattern \)
9809static int nfa_regatom(void)
9810{
9811 int c;
9812 int charclass;
9813 int equiclass;
9814 int collclass;
9815 int got_coll_char;
9816 uint8_t *p;
9817 uint8_t *endp;
9818 uint8_t *old_regparse = (uint8_t *)regparse;
9819 int extra = 0;
9820 int emit_range;
9821 int negated;
9822 int startc = -1;
9823 int save_prev_at_start = prev_at_start;
9824
9825 c = getchr();
9826 switch (c) {
9827 case NUL'\000':
9828 EMSG_RET_FAIL(_(e_nul_found))return (emsg(gettext(e_nul_found)), rc_did_emsg = 1, 0);
9829
9830 case Magic('^')((int)('^') - 256):
9831 EMIT(NFA_BOL)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_BOL; } while (0);
9832 break;
9833
9834 case Magic('$')((int)('$') - 256):
9835 EMIT(NFA_EOL)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_EOL; } while (0);
9836 had_eol = true1;
9837 break;
9838
9839 case Magic('<')((int)('<') - 256):
9840 EMIT(NFA_BOW)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_BOW; } while (0);
9841 break;
9842
9843 case Magic('>')((int)('>') - 256):
9844 EMIT(NFA_EOW)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_EOW; } while (0);
9845 break;
9846
9847 case Magic('_')((int)('_') - 256):
9848 c = no_Magic(getchr());
9849 if (c == NUL'\000') {
9850 EMSG_RET_FAIL(_(e_nul_found))return (emsg(gettext(e_nul_found)), rc_did_emsg = 1, 0);
9851 }
9852
9853 if (c == '^') { // "\_^" is start-of-line
9854 EMIT(NFA_BOL)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_BOL; } while (0);
9855 break;
9856 }
9857 if (c == '$') { // "\_$" is end-of-line
9858 EMIT(NFA_EOL)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_EOL; } while (0);
9859 had_eol = true1;
9860 break;
9861 }
9862
9863 extra = NFA_ADD_NL31;
9864
9865 // "\_[" is collection plus newline
9866 if (c == '[') {
9867 goto collection;
9868 }
9869
9870 // "\_x" is character class plus newline
9871 FALLTHROUGH{} __attribute__((fallthrough));
9872
9873 // Character classes.
9874 case Magic('.')((int)('.') - 256):
9875 case Magic('i')((int)('i') - 256):
9876 case Magic('I')((int)('I') - 256):
9877 case Magic('k')((int)('k') - 256):
9878 case Magic('K')((int)('K') - 256):
9879 case Magic('f')((int)('f') - 256):
9880 case Magic('F')((int)('F') - 256):
9881 case Magic('p')((int)('p') - 256):
9882 case Magic('P')((int)('P') - 256):
9883 case Magic('s')((int)('s') - 256):
9884 case Magic('S')((int)('S') - 256):
9885 case Magic('d')((int)('d') - 256):
9886 case Magic('D')((int)('D') - 256):
9887 case Magic('x')((int)('x') - 256):
9888 case Magic('X')((int)('X') - 256):
9889 case Magic('o')((int)('o') - 256):
9890 case Magic('O')((int)('O') - 256):
9891 case Magic('w')((int)('w') - 256):
9892 case Magic('W')((int)('W') - 256):
9893 case Magic('h')((int)('h') - 256):
9894 case Magic('H')((int)('H') - 256):
9895 case Magic('a')((int)('a') - 256):
9896 case Magic('A')((int)('A') - 256):
9897 case Magic('l')((int)('l') - 256):
9898 case Magic('L')((int)('L') - 256):
9899 case Magic('u')((int)('u') - 256):
9900 case Magic('U')((int)('U') - 256):
9901 p = (uint8_t *)vim_strchr((char *)classchars, no_Magic(c));
9902 if (p == NULL((void*)0)) {
9903 if (extra == NFA_ADD_NL31) {
9904 semsg(_(e_ill_char_class)gettext(e_ill_char_class), (int64_t)c);
9905 rc_did_emsg = true1;
9906 return FAIL0;
9907 }
9908 siemsg("INTERNAL: Unknown character class char: %" PRId64"l" "d", (int64_t)c);
9909 return FAIL0;
9910 }
9911 // When '.' is followed by a composing char ignore the dot, so that
9912 // the composing char is matched here.
9913 if (c == Magic('.')((int)('.') - 256) && utf_iscomposing(peekchr())) {
9914 old_regparse = (uint8_t *)regparse;
9915 c = getchr();
9916 goto nfa_do_multibyte;
9917 }
9918 EMIT(nfa_classcodes[p - classchars])do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = nfa_classcodes[p - classchars]; } while (0);
9919 if (extra == NFA_ADD_NL31) {
9920 EMIT(NFA_NEWL)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_NEWL; } while (0);
9921 EMIT(NFA_OR)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_OR; } while (0);
9922 regflags |= RF_HASNL4;
9923 }
9924 break;
9925
9926 case Magic('n')((int)('n') - 256):
9927 if (reg_string) {
9928 // In a string "\n" matches a newline character.
9929 EMIT(NL)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = '\012'; } while (0);
9930 } else {
9931 // In buffer text "\n" matches the end of a line.
9932 EMIT(NFA_NEWL)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_NEWL; } while (0);
9933 regflags |= RF_HASNL4;
9934 }
9935 break;
9936
9937 case Magic('(')((int)('(') - 256):
9938 if (nfa_reg(REG_PAREN1) == FAIL0) {
9939 return FAIL0; // cascaded error
9940 }
9941 break;
9942
9943 case Magic('|')((int)('|') - 256):
9944 case Magic('&')((int)('&') - 256):
9945 case Magic(')')((int)(')') - 256):
9946 semsg(_(e_misplaced)gettext(e_misplaced), (char)no_Magic(c));
9947 return FAIL0;
9948
9949 case Magic('=')((int)('=') - 256):
9950 case Magic('?')((int)('?') - 256):
9951 case Magic('+')((int)('+') - 256):
9952 case Magic('@')((int)('@') - 256):
9953 case Magic('*')((int)('*') - 256):
9954 case Magic('{')((int)('{') - 256):
9955 // these should follow an atom, not form an atom
9956 semsg(_(e_misplaced)gettext(e_misplaced), (char)no_Magic(c));
9957 return FAIL0;
9958
9959 case Magic('~')((int)('~') - 256): {
9960 uint8_t *lp;
9961
9962 // Previous substitute pattern.
9963 // Generated as "\%(pattern\)".
9964 if (reg_prev_sub == NULL((void*)0)) {
9965 emsg(_(e_nopresub)gettext(e_nopresub));
9966 return FAIL0;
9967 }
9968 for (lp = (uint8_t *)reg_prev_sub; *lp != NUL'\000'; lp += utf_ptr2len((char *)lp)) {
9969 EMIT(utf_ptr2char((char *)lp))do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = utf_ptr2char((char *)lp); } while (0);
9970 if (lp != (uint8_t *)reg_prev_sub) {
9971 EMIT(NFA_CONCAT)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CONCAT; } while (0);
9972 }
9973 }
9974 EMIT(NFA_NOPEN)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_NOPEN; } while (0);
9975 break;
9976 }
9977
9978 case Magic('1')((int)('1') - 256):
9979 case Magic('2')((int)('2') - 256):
9980 case Magic('3')((int)('3') - 256):
9981 case Magic('4')((int)('4') - 256):
9982 case Magic('5')((int)('5') - 256):
9983 case Magic('6')((int)('6') - 256):
9984 case Magic('7')((int)('7') - 256):
9985 case Magic('8')((int)('8') - 256):
9986 case Magic('9')((int)('9') - 256): {
9987 int refnum = no_Magic(c) - '1';
9988
9989 if (!seen_endbrace(refnum + 1)) {
9990 return FAIL0;
9991 }
9992 EMIT(NFA_BACKREF1 + refnum)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_BACKREF1 + refnum; } while (0);
9993 rex.nfa_has_backref = true1;
9994 }
9995 break;
9996
9997 case Magic('z')((int)('z') - 256):
9998 c = no_Magic(getchr());
9999 switch (c) {
10000 case 's':
10001 EMIT(NFA_ZSTART)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_ZSTART; } while (0);
10002 if (!re_mult_next("\\zs")) {
10003 return false0;
10004 }
10005 break;
10006 case 'e':
10007 EMIT(NFA_ZEND)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_ZEND; } while (0);
10008 rex.nfa_has_zend = true1;
10009 if (!re_mult_next("\\zs")) {
10010 return false0;
10011 }
10012 break;
10013 case '1':
10014 case '2':
10015 case '3':
10016 case '4':
10017 case '5':
10018 case '6':
10019 case '7':
10020 case '8':
10021 case '9':
10022 // \z1...\z9
10023 if ((reg_do_extmatch & REX_USE2) == 0) {
10024 EMSG_RET_FAIL(_(e_z1_not_allowed))return (emsg(gettext(e_z1_not_allowed)), rc_did_emsg = 1, 0);
10025 }
10026 EMIT(NFA_ZREF1 + (no_Magic(c) - '1'))do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_ZREF1 + (no_Magic(c) - '1'); } while (0);
10027 // No need to set rex.nfa_has_backref, the sub-matches don't
10028 // change when \z1 .. \z9 matches or not.
10029 re_has_z = REX_USE2;
10030 break;
10031 case '(':
10032 // \z(
10033 if (reg_do_extmatch != REX_SET1) {
10034 EMSG_RET_FAIL(_(e_z_not_allowed))return (emsg(gettext(e_z_not_allowed)), rc_did_emsg = 1, 0);
10035 }
10036 if (nfa_reg(REG_ZPAREN2) == FAIL0) {
10037 return FAIL0; // cascaded error
10038 }
10039 re_has_z = REX_SET1;
10040 break;
10041 default:
10042 semsg(_("E867: (NFA) Unknown operator '\\z%c'")gettext("E867: (NFA) Unknown operator '\\z%c'"),
10043 no_Magic(c));
10044 return FAIL0;
10045 }
10046 break;
10047
10048 case Magic('%')((int)('%') - 256):
10049 c = no_Magic(getchr());
10050 switch (c) {
10051 // () without a back reference
10052 case '(':
10053 if (nfa_reg(REG_NPAREN3) == FAIL0) {
10054 return FAIL0;
10055 }
10056 EMIT(NFA_NOPEN)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_NOPEN; } while (0);
10057 break;
10058
10059 case 'd': // %d123 decimal
10060 case 'o': // %o123 octal
10061 case 'x': // %xab hex 2
10062 case 'u': // %uabcd hex 4
10063 case 'U': // %U1234abcd hex 8
10064 {
10065 int64_t nr;
10066
10067 switch (c) {
10068 case 'd':
10069 nr = getdecchrs(); break;
10070 case 'o':
10071 nr = getoctchrs(); break;
10072 case 'x':
10073 nr = gethexchrs(2); break;
10074 case 'u':
10075 nr = gethexchrs(4); break;
10076 case 'U':
10077 nr = gethexchrs(8); break;
10078 default:
10079 nr = -1; break;
10080 }
10081
10082 if (nr < 0 || nr > INT_MAX2147483647) {
10083 EMSG2_RET_FAIL(_("E678: Invalid character after %s%%[dxouU]"),return (semsg((gettext("E678: Invalid character after %s%%[dxouU]"
)), (reg_magic == MAGIC_ALL) ? "" : "\\"), rc_did_emsg = 1, 0
)
10084 reg_magic == MAGIC_ALL)return (semsg((gettext("E678: Invalid character after %s%%[dxouU]"
)), (reg_magic == MAGIC_ALL) ? "" : "\\"), rc_did_emsg = 1, 0
);
10085 }
10086 // A NUL is stored in the text as NL
10087 // TODO(vim): what if a composing character follows?
10088 EMIT(nr == 0 ? 0x0a : (int)nr)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = nr == 0 ? 0x0a : (int)nr; } while (0);
10089 }
10090 break;
10091
10092 // Catch \%^ and \%$ regardless of where they appear in the
10093 // pattern -- regardless of whether or not it makes sense.
10094 case '^':
10095 EMIT(NFA_BOF)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_BOF; } while (0);
10096 break;
10097
10098 case '$':
10099 EMIT(NFA_EOF)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_EOF; } while (0);
10100 break;
10101
10102 case '#':
10103 if (regparse[0] == '=' && regparse[1] >= 48
10104 && regparse[1] <= 50) {
10105 // misplaced \%#=1
10106 semsg(_(e_atom_engine_must_be_at_start_of_pattern)gettext(e_atom_engine_must_be_at_start_of_pattern), regparse[1]);
10107 return FAIL0;
10108 }
10109 EMIT(NFA_CURSOR)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CURSOR; } while (0);
10110 break;
10111
10112 case 'V':
10113 EMIT(NFA_VISUAL)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_VISUAL; } while (0);
10114 break;
10115
10116 case 'C':
10117 EMIT(NFA_ANY_COMPOSING)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_ANY_COMPOSING; } while (0);
10118 break;
10119
10120 case '[': {
10121 int n;
10122
10123 // \%[abc]
10124 for (n = 0; (c = peekchr()) != ']'; n++) {
10125 if (c == NUL'\000') {
10126 EMSG2_RET_FAIL(_(e_missing_sb),return (semsg((gettext(e_missing_sb)), (reg_magic == MAGIC_ALL
) ? "" : "\\"), rc_did_emsg = 1, 0)
10127 reg_magic == MAGIC_ALL)return (semsg((gettext(e_missing_sb)), (reg_magic == MAGIC_ALL
) ? "" : "\\"), rc_did_emsg = 1, 0);
10128 }
10129 // recursive call!
10130 if (nfa_regatom() == FAIL0) {
10131 return FAIL0;
10132 }
10133 }
10134 (void)getchr(); // get the ]
10135 if (n == 0) {
10136 EMSG2_RET_FAIL(_(e_empty_sb), reg_magic == MAGIC_ALL)return (semsg((gettext(e_empty_sb)), (reg_magic == MAGIC_ALL)
? "" : "\\"), rc_did_emsg = 1, 0);
10137 }
10138 EMIT(NFA_OPT_CHARS)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_OPT_CHARS; } while (0);
10139 EMIT(n)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = n; } while (0);
10140
10141 // Emit as "\%(\%[abc]\)" to be able to handle
10142 // "\%[abc]*" which would cause the empty string to be
10143 // matched an unlimited number of times. NFA_NOPEN is
10144 // added only once at a position, while NFA_SPLIT is
10145 // added multiple times. This is more efficient than
10146 // not allowing NFA_SPLIT multiple times, it is used
10147 // a lot.
10148 EMIT(NFA_NOPEN)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_NOPEN; } while (0);
10149 break;
10150 }
10151
10152 default: {
10153 int64_t n = 0;
10154 const int cmp = c;
10155 bool_Bool cur = false0;
10156 bool_Bool got_digit = false0;
10157
10158 if (c == '<' || c == '>') {
10159 c = getchr();
10160 }
10161 if (no_Magic(c) == '.') {
10162 cur = true1;
10163 c = getchr();
10164 }
10165 while (ascii_isdigit(c)) {
10166 if (cur) {
10167 semsg(_(e_regexp_number_after_dot_pos_search_chr)gettext(e_regexp_number_after_dot_pos_search_chr), no_Magic(c));
10168 return FAIL0;
10169 }
10170 if (n > (INT32_MAX(2147483647) - (c - '0')) / 10) {
10171 // overflow.
10172 emsg(_(e_value_too_large)gettext(e_value_too_large));
10173 return FAIL0;
10174 }
10175 n = n * 10 + (c - '0');
10176 c = getchr();
10177 got_digit = true1;
10178 }
10179 if (c == 'l' || c == 'c' || c == 'v') {
10180 int32_t limit = INT32_MAX(2147483647);
10181
10182 if (!cur && !got_digit) {
10183 semsg(_(e_nfa_regexp_missing_value_in_chr)gettext(e_nfa_regexp_missing_value_in_chr), no_Magic(c));
10184 return FAIL0;
10185 }
10186 if (c == 'l') {
10187 if (cur) {
10188 n = curwin->w_cursor.lnum;
10189 }
10190 // \%{n}l \%{n}<l \%{n}>l
10191 EMIT(cmp == '<' ? NFA_LNUM_LTdo { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = cmp == '<' ? NFA_LNUM_LT : cmp == '>' ? NFA_LNUM_GT
: NFA_LNUM; } while (0)
10192 : cmp == '>' ? NFA_LNUM_GT : NFA_LNUM)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = cmp == '<' ? NFA_LNUM_LT : cmp == '>' ? NFA_LNUM_GT
: NFA_LNUM; } while (0);
10193 if (save_prev_at_start) {
10194 at_start = true1;
10195 }
10196 } else if (c == 'c') {
10197 if (cur) {
10198 n = curwin->w_cursor.col;
10199 n++;
10200 }
10201 // \%{n}c \%{n}<c \%{n}>c
10202 EMIT(cmp == '<' ? NFA_COL_LTdo { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = cmp == '<' ? NFA_COL_LT : cmp == '>' ? NFA_COL_GT :
NFA_COL; } while (0)
10203 : cmp == '>' ? NFA_COL_GT : NFA_COL)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = cmp == '<' ? NFA_COL_LT : cmp == '>' ? NFA_COL_GT :
NFA_COL; } while (0);
10204 } else {
10205 if (cur) {
10206 colnr_T vcol = 0;
10207 getvvcol(curwin, &curwin->w_cursor, NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0), &vcol);
10208 n = ++vcol;
10209 }
10210 // \%{n}v \%{n}<v \%{n}>v
10211 EMIT(cmp == '<' ? NFA_VCOL_LTdo { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = cmp == '<' ? NFA_VCOL_LT : cmp == '>' ? NFA_VCOL_GT
: NFA_VCOL; } while (0)
10212 : cmp == '>' ? NFA_VCOL_GT : NFA_VCOL)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = cmp == '<' ? NFA_VCOL_LT : cmp == '>' ? NFA_VCOL_GT
: NFA_VCOL; } while (0);
10213 limit = INT32_MAX(2147483647) / MB_MAXBYTES;
10214 }
10215 if (n >= limit) {
10216 emsg(_(e_value_too_large)gettext(e_value_too_large));
10217 return FAIL0;
10218 }
10219 EMIT((int)n)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = (int)n; } while (0);
10220 break;
10221 } else if (no_Magic(c) == '\'' && n == 0) {
10222 // \%'m \%<'m \%>'m
10223 EMIT(cmp == '<' ? NFA_MARK_LTdo { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = cmp == '<' ? NFA_MARK_LT : cmp == '>' ? NFA_MARK_GT
: NFA_MARK; } while (0)
10224 : cmp == '>' ? NFA_MARK_GT : NFA_MARK)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = cmp == '<' ? NFA_MARK_LT : cmp == '>' ? NFA_MARK_GT
: NFA_MARK; } while (0);
10225 EMIT(getchr())do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = getchr(); } while (0);
10226 break;
10227 }
10228 }
10229 semsg(_("E867: (NFA) Unknown operator '\\%%%c'")gettext("E867: (NFA) Unknown operator '\\%%%c'"),
10230 no_Magic(c));
10231 return FAIL0;
10232 }
10233 break;
10234
10235 case Magic('[')((int)('[') - 256):
10236collection:
10237 // [abc] uses NFA_START_COLL - NFA_END_COLL
10238 // [^abc] uses NFA_START_NEG_COLL - NFA_END_NEG_COLL
10239 // Each character is produced as a regular state, using
10240 // NFA_CONCAT to bind them together.
10241 // Besides normal characters there can be:
10242 // - character classes NFA_CLASS_*
10243 // - ranges, two characters followed by NFA_RANGE.
10244
10245 p = (uint8_t *)regparse;
10246 endp = (uint8_t *)skip_anyof((char *)p);
10247 if (*endp == ']') {
10248 // Try to reverse engineer character classes. For example,
10249 // recognize that [0-9] stands for \d and [A-Za-z_] for \h,
10250 // and perform the necessary substitutions in the NFA.
10251 int result = nfa_recognize_char_class((uint8_t *)regparse, endp, extra == NFA_ADD_NL31);
10252 if (result != FAIL0) {
10253 if (result >= NFA_FIRST_NL && result <= NFA_LAST_NL) {
10254 EMIT(result - NFA_ADD_NL)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = result - 31; } while (0);
10255 EMIT(NFA_NEWL)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_NEWL; } while (0);
10256 EMIT(NFA_OR)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_OR; } while (0);
10257 } else {
10258 EMIT(result)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = result; } while (0);
10259 }
10260 regparse = (char *)endp;
10261 MB_PTR_ADV(regparse)(regparse += utfc_ptr2len((char *)regparse));
10262 return OK1;
10263 }
10264 // Failed to recognize a character class. Use the simple
10265 // version that turns [abc] into 'a' OR 'b' OR 'c'
10266 negated = false0;
10267 if (*regparse == '^') { // negated range
10268 negated = true1;
10269 MB_PTR_ADV(regparse)(regparse += utfc_ptr2len((char *)regparse));
10270 EMIT(NFA_START_NEG_COLL)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_START_NEG_COLL; } while (0);
10271 } else {
10272 EMIT(NFA_START_COLL)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_START_COLL; } while (0);
10273 }
10274 if (*regparse == '-') {
10275 startc = '-';
10276 EMIT(startc)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = startc; } while (0);
10277 EMIT(NFA_CONCAT)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CONCAT; } while (0);
10278 MB_PTR_ADV(regparse)(regparse += utfc_ptr2len((char *)regparse));
10279 }
10280 // Emit the OR branches for each character in the []
10281 emit_range = false0;
10282 while ((uint8_t *)regparse < endp) {
10283 int oldstartc = startc;
10284 startc = -1;
10285 got_coll_char = false0;
10286 if (*regparse == '[') {
10287 // Check for [: :], [= =], [. .]
10288 equiclass = collclass = 0;
10289 charclass = get_char_class(&regparse);
10290 if (charclass == CLASS_NONE99) {
10291 equiclass = get_equi_class(&regparse);
10292 if (equiclass == 0) {
10293 collclass = get_coll_element(&regparse);
10294 }
10295 }
10296
10297 // Character class like [:alpha:]
10298 if (charclass != CLASS_NONE99) {
10299 switch (charclass) {
10300 case CLASS_ALNUM0:
10301 EMIT(NFA_CLASS_ALNUM)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CLASS_ALNUM; } while (0);
10302 break;
10303 case CLASS_ALPHA1:
10304 EMIT(NFA_CLASS_ALPHA)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CLASS_ALPHA; } while (0);
10305 break;
10306 case CLASS_BLANK2:
10307 EMIT(NFA_CLASS_BLANK)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CLASS_BLANK; } while (0);
10308 break;
10309 case CLASS_CNTRL3:
10310 EMIT(NFA_CLASS_CNTRL)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CLASS_CNTRL; } while (0);
10311 break;
10312 case CLASS_DIGIT4:
10313 EMIT(NFA_CLASS_DIGIT)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CLASS_DIGIT; } while (0);
10314 break;
10315 case CLASS_GRAPH5:
10316 EMIT(NFA_CLASS_GRAPH)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CLASS_GRAPH; } while (0);
10317 break;
10318 case CLASS_LOWER6:
10319 wants_nfa = true1;
10320 EMIT(NFA_CLASS_LOWER)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CLASS_LOWER; } while (0);
10321 break;
10322 case CLASS_PRINT7:
10323 EMIT(NFA_CLASS_PRINT)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CLASS_PRINT; } while (0);
10324 break;
10325 case CLASS_PUNCT8:
10326 EMIT(NFA_CLASS_PUNCT)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CLASS_PUNCT; } while (0);
10327 break;
10328 case CLASS_SPACE9:
10329 EMIT(NFA_CLASS_SPACE)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CLASS_SPACE; } while (0);
10330 break;
10331 case CLASS_UPPER10:
10332 wants_nfa = true1;
10333 EMIT(NFA_CLASS_UPPER)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CLASS_UPPER; } while (0);
10334 break;
10335 case CLASS_XDIGIT11:
10336 EMIT(NFA_CLASS_XDIGIT)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CLASS_XDIGIT; } while (0);
10337 break;
10338 case CLASS_TAB12:
10339 EMIT(NFA_CLASS_TAB)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CLASS_TAB; } while (0);
10340 break;
10341 case CLASS_RETURN13:
10342 EMIT(NFA_CLASS_RETURN)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CLASS_RETURN; } while (0);
10343 break;
10344 case CLASS_BACKSPACE14:
10345 EMIT(NFA_CLASS_BACKSPACE)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CLASS_BACKSPACE; } while (0);
10346 break;
10347 case CLASS_ESCAPE15:
10348 EMIT(NFA_CLASS_ESCAPE)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CLASS_ESCAPE; } while (0);
10349 break;
10350 case CLASS_IDENT16:
10351 EMIT(NFA_CLASS_IDENT)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CLASS_IDENT; } while (0);
10352 break;
10353 case CLASS_KEYWORD17:
10354 EMIT(NFA_CLASS_KEYWORD)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CLASS_KEYWORD; } while (0);
10355 break;
10356 case CLASS_FNAME18:
10357 EMIT(NFA_CLASS_FNAME)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CLASS_FNAME; } while (0);
10358 break;
10359 }
10360 EMIT(NFA_CONCAT)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CONCAT; } while (0);
10361 continue;
10362 }
10363 // Try equivalence class [=a=] and the like
10364 if (equiclass != 0) {
10365 nfa_emit_equi_class(equiclass);
10366 continue;
10367 }
10368 // Try collating class like [. .]
10369 if (collclass != 0) {
10370 startc = collclass; // allow [.a.]-x as a range
10371 // Will emit the proper atom at the end of the
10372 // while loop.
10373 }
10374 }
10375 // Try a range like 'a-x' or '\t-z'. Also allows '-' as a
10376 // start character.
10377 if (*regparse == '-' && oldstartc != -1) {
10378 emit_range = true1;
10379 startc = oldstartc;
10380 MB_PTR_ADV(regparse)(regparse += utfc_ptr2len((char *)regparse));
10381 continue; // reading the end of the range
10382 }
10383
10384 // Now handle simple and escaped characters.
10385 // Only "\]", "\^", "\]" and "\\" are special in Vi. Vim
10386 // accepts "\t", "\e", etc., but only when the 'l' flag in
10387 // 'cpoptions' is not included.
10388 if (*regparse == '\\'
10389 && (uint8_t *)regparse + 1 <= endp
10390 && (vim_strchr(REGEXP_INRANGE, (uint8_t)regparse[1]) != NULL((void*)0)
10391 || (!reg_cpo_lit
10392 && vim_strchr(REGEXP_ABBR, (uint8_t)regparse[1])
10393 != NULL((void*)0)))) {
10394 MB_PTR_ADV(regparse)(regparse += utfc_ptr2len((char *)regparse));
10395
10396 if (*regparse == 'n') {
10397 startc = (reg_string || emit_range || regparse[1] == '-')
10398 ? NL'\012' : NFA_NEWL;
10399 } else if (*regparse == 'd'
10400 || *regparse == 'o'
10401 || *regparse == 'x'
10402 || *regparse == 'u'
10403 || *regparse == 'U') {
10404 // TODO(RE): This needs more testing
10405 startc = coll_get_char();
10406 got_coll_char = true1;
10407 MB_PTR_BACK(old_regparse, regparse)(regparse -= utf_head_off((char *)(old_regparse), (char *)(regparse
) - 1) + 1);
10408 } else {
10409 // \r,\t,\e,\b
10410 startc = backslash_trans(*regparse);
10411 }
10412 }
10413
10414 // Normal printable char
10415 if (startc == -1) {
10416 startc = utf_ptr2char(regparse);
10417 }
10418
10419 // Previous char was '-', so this char is end of range.
10420 if (emit_range) {
10421 int endc = startc;
10422 startc = oldstartc;
10423 if (startc > endc) {
10424 EMSG_RET_FAIL(_(e_reverse_range))return (emsg(gettext(e_reverse_range)), rc_did_emsg = 1, 0);
10425 }
10426
10427 if (endc > startc + 2) {
10428 // Emit a range instead of the sequence of
10429 // individual characters.
10430 if (startc == 0) {
10431 // \x00 is translated to \x0a, start at \x01.
10432 EMIT(1)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = 1; } while (0);
10433 } else {
10434 post_ptr--; // remove NFA_CONCAT
10435 }
10436 EMIT(endc)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = endc; } while (0);
10437 EMIT(NFA_RANGE)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_RANGE; } while (0);
10438 EMIT(NFA_CONCAT)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CONCAT; } while (0);
10439 } else if (utf_char2len(startc) > 1
10440 || utf_char2len(endc) > 1) {
10441 // Emit the characters in the range.
10442 // "startc" was already emitted, so skip it.
10443 for (c = startc + 1; c <= endc; c++) {
10444 EMIT(c)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = c; } while (0);
10445 EMIT(NFA_CONCAT)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CONCAT; } while (0);
10446 }
10447 } else {
10448 // Emit the range. "startc" was already emitted, so
10449 // skip it.
10450 for (c = startc + 1; c <= endc; c++) {
10451 EMIT(c)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = c; } while (0);
10452 EMIT(NFA_CONCAT)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CONCAT; } while (0);
10453 }
10454 }
10455 emit_range = false0;
10456 startc = -1;
10457 } else {
10458 // This char (startc) is not part of a range. Just
10459 // emit it.
10460 // Normally, simply emit startc. But if we get char
10461 // code=0 from a collating char, then replace it with
10462 // 0x0a.
10463 // This is needed to completely mimic the behaviour of
10464 // the backtracking engine.
10465 if (startc == NFA_NEWL) {
10466 // Line break can't be matched as part of the
10467 // collection, add an OR below. But not for negated
10468 // range.
10469 if (!negated) {
10470 extra = NFA_ADD_NL31;
10471 }
10472 } else {
10473 if (got_coll_char == true1 && startc == 0) {
10474 EMIT(0x0a)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = 0x0a; } while (0);
10475 EMIT(NFA_CONCAT)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CONCAT; } while (0);
10476 } else {
10477 EMIT(startc)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = startc; } while (0);
10478 if (utf_ptr2len(regparse) == utfc_ptr2len(regparse)) {
10479 EMIT(NFA_CONCAT)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CONCAT; } while (0);
10480 }
10481 }
10482 }
10483 }
10484
10485 int plen;
10486 if (utf_ptr2len(regparse) != (plen = utfc_ptr2len(regparse))) {
10487 int i = utf_ptr2len(regparse);
10488
10489 c = utf_ptr2char(regparse + i);
10490
10491 // Add composing characters
10492 while (true1) {
10493 if (c == 0) {
10494 // \x00 is translated to \x0a, start at \x01.
10495 EMIT(1)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = 1; } while (0);
10496 } else {
10497 EMIT(c)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = c; } while (0);
10498 }
10499 EMIT(NFA_CONCAT)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CONCAT; } while (0);
10500 if ((i += utf_char2len(c)) >= plen) {
10501 break;
10502 }
10503 c = utf_ptr2char(regparse + i);
10504 }
10505 EMIT(NFA_COMPOSING)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_COMPOSING; } while (0);
10506 EMIT(NFA_CONCAT)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CONCAT; } while (0);
10507 }
10508 MB_PTR_ADV(regparse)(regparse += utfc_ptr2len((char *)regparse));
10509 } // while (p < endp)
10510
10511 MB_PTR_BACK(old_regparse, regparse)(regparse -= utf_head_off((char *)(old_regparse), (char *)(regparse
) - 1) + 1);
10512 if (*regparse == '-') { // if last, '-' is just a char
10513 EMIT('-')do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = '-'; } while (0);
10514 EMIT(NFA_CONCAT)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CONCAT; } while (0);
10515 }
10516
10517 // skip the trailing ]
10518 regparse = (char *)endp;
10519 MB_PTR_ADV(regparse)(regparse += utfc_ptr2len((char *)regparse));
10520
10521 // Mark end of the collection.
10522 if (negated == true1) {
10523 EMIT(NFA_END_NEG_COLL)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_END_NEG_COLL; } while (0);
10524 } else {
10525 EMIT(NFA_END_COLL)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_END_COLL; } while (0);
10526 }
10527
10528 // \_[] also matches \n but it's not negated
10529 if (extra == NFA_ADD_NL31) {
10530 EMIT(reg_string ? NL : NFA_NEWL)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = reg_string ? '\012' : NFA_NEWL; } while (0);
10531 EMIT(NFA_OR)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_OR; } while (0);
10532 }
10533
10534 return OK1;
10535 } // if exists closing ]
10536
10537 if (reg_strict) {
10538 EMSG_RET_FAIL(_(e_missingbracket))return (emsg(gettext(e_missingbracket)), rc_did_emsg = 1, 0);
10539 }
10540 FALLTHROUGH{} __attribute__((fallthrough));
10541
10542 default: {
10543 int plen;
10544
10545nfa_do_multibyte:
10546 // plen is length of current char with composing chars
10547 if (utf_char2len(c) != (plen = utfc_ptr2len((char *)old_regparse))
10548 || utf_iscomposing(c)) {
10549 int i = 0;
10550
10551 // A base character plus composing characters, or just one
10552 // or more composing characters.
10553 // This requires creating a separate atom as if enclosing
10554 // the characters in (), where NFA_COMPOSING is the ( and
10555 // NFA_END_COMPOSING is the ). Note that right now we are
10556 // building the postfix form, not the NFA itself;
10557 // a composing char could be: a, b, c, NFA_COMPOSING
10558 // where 'b' and 'c' are chars with codes > 256. */
10559 while (true1) {
10560 EMIT(c)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = c; } while (0);
10561 if (i > 0) {
10562 EMIT(NFA_CONCAT)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CONCAT; } while (0);
10563 }
10564 if ((i += utf_char2len(c)) >= plen) {
10565 break;
10566 }
10567 c = utf_ptr2char((char *)old_regparse + i);
10568 }
10569 EMIT(NFA_COMPOSING)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_COMPOSING; } while (0);
10570 regparse = (char *)old_regparse + plen;
10571 } else {
10572 c = no_Magic(c);
10573 EMIT(c)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = c; } while (0);
10574 }
10575 return OK1;
10576 }
10577 }
10578
10579 return OK1;
10580}
10581
10582// Parse something followed by possible [*+=].
10583//
10584// A piece is an atom, possibly followed by a multi, an indication of how many
10585// times the atom can be matched. Example: "a*" matches any sequence of "a"
10586// characters: "", "a", "aa", etc.
10587//
10588// piece ::= atom
10589// or atom multi
10590static int nfa_regpiece(void)
10591{
10592 int i;
10593 int op;
10594 int ret;
10595 int minval, maxval;
10596 bool_Bool greedy = true1; // Braces are prefixed with '-' ?
10597 parse_state_T old_state;
10598 parse_state_T new_state;
10599 int64_t c2;
10600 int old_post_pos;
10601 int my_post_start;
10602 int quest;
10603
10604 // Save the current parse state, so that we can use it if <atom>{m,n} is
10605 // next.
10606 save_parse_state(&old_state);
10607
10608 // store current pos in the postfix form, for \{m,n} involving 0s
10609 my_post_start = (int)(post_ptr - post_start);
10610
10611 ret = nfa_regatom();
10612 if (ret == FAIL0) {
10613 return FAIL0; // cascaded error
10614 }
10615 op = peekchr();
10616 if (re_multi_type(op) == NOT_MULTI0) {
10617 return OK1;
10618 }
10619
10620 skipchr();
10621 switch (op) {
10622 case Magic('*')((int)('*') - 256):
10623 EMIT(NFA_STAR)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_STAR; } while (0);
10624 break;
10625
10626 case Magic('+')((int)('+') - 256):
10627 // Trick: Normally, (a*)\+ would match the whole input "aaa". The
10628 // first and only submatch would be "aaa". But the backtracking
10629 // engine interprets the plus as "try matching one more time", and
10630 // a* matches a second time at the end of the input, the empty
10631 // string.
10632 // The submatch will be the empty string.
10633 //
10634 // In order to be consistent with the old engine, we replace
10635 // <atom>+ with <atom><atom>*
10636 restore_parse_state(&old_state);
10637 curchr = -1;
10638 if (nfa_regatom() == FAIL0) {
10639 return FAIL0;
10640 }
10641 EMIT(NFA_STAR)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_STAR; } while (0);
10642 EMIT(NFA_CONCAT)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CONCAT; } while (0);
10643 skipchr(); // skip the \+
10644 break;
10645
10646 case Magic('@')((int)('@') - 256):
10647 c2 = getdecchrs();
10648 op = no_Magic(getchr());
10649 i = 0;
10650 switch (op) {
10651 case '=':
10652 // \@=
10653 i = NFA_PREV_ATOM_NO_WIDTH;
10654 break;
10655 case '!':
10656 // \@!
10657 i = NFA_PREV_ATOM_NO_WIDTH_NEG;
10658 break;
10659 case '<':
10660 op = no_Magic(getchr());
10661 if (op == '=') {
10662 // \@<=
10663 i = NFA_PREV_ATOM_JUST_BEFORE;
10664 } else if (op == '!') {
10665 // \@<!
10666 i = NFA_PREV_ATOM_JUST_BEFORE_NEG;
10667 }
10668 break;
10669 case '>':
10670 // \@>
10671 i = NFA_PREV_ATOM_LIKE_PATTERN;
10672 break;
10673 }
10674 if (i == 0) {
10675 semsg(_("E869: (NFA) Unknown operator '\\@%c'")gettext("E869: (NFA) Unknown operator '\\@%c'"), op);
10676 return FAIL0;
10677 }
10678 EMIT(i)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = i; } while (0);
10679 if (i == NFA_PREV_ATOM_JUST_BEFORE
10680 || i == NFA_PREV_ATOM_JUST_BEFORE_NEG) {
10681 EMIT((int)c2)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = (int)c2; } while (0);
10682 }
10683 break;
10684
10685 case Magic('?')((int)('?') - 256):
10686 case Magic('=')((int)('=') - 256):
10687 EMIT(NFA_QUEST)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_QUEST; } while (0);
10688 break;
10689
10690 case Magic('{')((int)('{') - 256):
10691 // a{2,5} will expand to 'aaa?a?a?'
10692 // a{-1,3} will expand to 'aa??a??', where ?? is the nongreedy
10693 // version of '?'
10694 // \v(ab){2,3} will expand to '(ab)(ab)(ab)?', where all the
10695 // parenthesis have the same id
10696
10697 greedy = true1;
10698 c2 = peekchr();
10699 if (c2 == '-' || c2 == Magic('-')((int)('-') - 256)) {
10700 skipchr();
10701 greedy = false0;
10702 }
10703 if (!read_limits(&minval, &maxval)) {
10704 EMSG_RET_FAIL(_("E870: (NFA regexp) Error reading repetition limits"))return (emsg(gettext("E870: (NFA regexp) Error reading repetition limits"
)), rc_did_emsg = 1, 0);
10705 }
10706
10707 // <atom>{0,inf}, <atom>{0,} and <atom>{} are equivalent to
10708 // <atom>*
10709 if (minval == 0 && maxval == MAX_LIMIT(32767 << 16)) {
10710 if (greedy) {
10711 // \{}, \{0,}
10712 EMIT(NFA_STAR)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_STAR; } while (0);
10713 } else {
10714 // \{-}, \{-0,}
10715 EMIT(NFA_STAR_NONGREEDY)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_STAR_NONGREEDY; } while (0);
10716 }
10717 break;
10718 }
10719
10720 // Special case: x{0} or x{-0}
10721 if (maxval == 0) {
10722 // Ignore result of previous call to nfa_regatom()
10723 post_ptr = post_start + my_post_start;
10724 // NFA_EMPTY is 0-length and works everywhere
10725 EMIT(NFA_EMPTY)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_EMPTY; } while (0);
10726 return OK1;
10727 }
10728
10729 // The engine is very inefficient (uses too many states) when the
10730 // maximum is much larger than the minimum and when the maximum is
10731 // large. However, when maxval is MAX_LIMIT, it is okay, as this
10732 // will emit NFA_STAR.
10733 // Bail out if we can use the other engine, but only, when the
10734 // pattern does not need the NFA engine like (e.g. [[:upper:]]\{2,\}
10735 // does not work with characters > 8 bit with the BT engine)
10736 if ((nfa_re_flags & RE_AUTO8)
10737 && (maxval > 500 || maxval > minval + 200)
10738 && (maxval != MAX_LIMIT(32767 << 16) && minval < 200)
10739 && !wants_nfa) {
10740 return FAIL0;
10741 }
10742
10743 // Ignore previous call to nfa_regatom()
10744 post_ptr = post_start + my_post_start;
10745 // Save parse state after the repeated atom and the \{}
10746 save_parse_state(&new_state);
10747
10748 quest = (greedy == true1 ? NFA_QUEST : NFA_QUEST_NONGREEDY);
10749 for (i = 0; i < maxval; i++) {
10750 // Goto beginning of the repeated atom
10751 restore_parse_state(&old_state);
10752 old_post_pos = (int)(post_ptr - post_start);
10753 if (nfa_regatom() == FAIL0) {
10754 return FAIL0;
10755 }
10756 // after "minval" times, atoms are optional
10757 if (i + 1 > minval) {
10758 if (maxval == MAX_LIMIT(32767 << 16)) {
10759 if (greedy) {
10760 EMIT(NFA_STAR)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_STAR; } while (0);
10761 } else {
10762 EMIT(NFA_STAR_NONGREEDY)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_STAR_NONGREEDY; } while (0);
10763 }
10764 } else {
10765 EMIT(quest)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = quest; } while (0);
10766 }
10767 }
10768 if (old_post_pos != my_post_start) {
10769 EMIT(NFA_CONCAT)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CONCAT; } while (0);
10770 }
10771 if (i + 1 > minval && maxval == MAX_LIMIT(32767 << 16)) {
10772 break;
10773 }
10774 }
10775
10776 // Go to just after the repeated atom and the \{}
10777 restore_parse_state(&new_state);
10778 curchr = -1;
10779
10780 break;
10781
10782 default:
10783 break;
10784 } // end switch
10785
10786 if (re_multi_type(peekchr()) != NOT_MULTI0) {
10787 // Can't have a multi follow a multi.
10788 EMSG_RET_FAIL(_("E871: (NFA regexp) Can't have a multi follow a multi"))return (emsg(gettext("E871: (NFA regexp) Can't have a multi follow a multi"
)), rc_did_emsg = 1, 0);
10789 }
10790
10791 return OK1;
10792}
10793
10794// Parse one or more pieces, concatenated. It matches a match for the
10795// first piece, followed by a match for the second piece, etc. Example:
10796// "f[0-9]b", first matches "f", then a digit and then "b".
10797//
10798// concat ::= piece
10799// or piece piece
10800// or piece piece piece
10801// etc.
10802static int nfa_regconcat(void)
10803{
10804 bool_Bool cont = true1;
10805 bool_Bool first = true1;
10806
10807 while (cont) {
10808 switch (peekchr()) {
10809 case NUL'\000':
10810 case Magic('|')((int)('|') - 256):
10811 case Magic('&')((int)('&') - 256):
10812 case Magic(')')((int)(')') - 256):
10813 cont = false0;
10814 break;
10815
10816 case Magic('Z')((int)('Z') - 256):
10817 regflags |= RF_ICOMBINE8;
10818 skipchr_keepstart();
10819 break;
10820 case Magic('c')((int)('c') - 256):
10821 regflags |= RF_ICASE1;
10822 skipchr_keepstart();
10823 break;
10824 case Magic('C')((int)('C') - 256):
10825 regflags |= RF_NOICASE2;
10826 skipchr_keepstart();
10827 break;
10828 case Magic('v')((int)('v') - 256):
10829 reg_magic = MAGIC_ALL;
10830 skipchr_keepstart();
10831 curchr = -1;
10832 break;
10833 case Magic('m')((int)('m') - 256):
10834 reg_magic = MAGIC_ON;
10835 skipchr_keepstart();
10836 curchr = -1;
10837 break;
10838 case Magic('M')((int)('M') - 256):
10839 reg_magic = MAGIC_OFF;
10840 skipchr_keepstart();
10841 curchr = -1;
10842 break;
10843 case Magic('V')((int)('V') - 256):
10844 reg_magic = MAGIC_NONE;
10845 skipchr_keepstart();
10846 curchr = -1;
10847 break;
10848
10849 default:
10850 if (nfa_regpiece() == FAIL0) {
10851 return FAIL0;
10852 }
10853 if (first == false0) {
10854 EMIT(NFA_CONCAT)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CONCAT; } while (0);
10855 } else {
10856 first = false0;
10857 }
10858 break;
10859 }
10860 }
10861
10862 return OK1;
10863}
10864
10865// Parse a branch, one or more concats, separated by "\&". It matches the
10866// last concat, but only if all the preceding concats also match at the same
10867// position. Examples:
10868// "foobeep\&..." matches "foo" in "foobeep".
10869// ".*Peter\&.*Bob" matches in a line containing both "Peter" and "Bob"
10870//
10871// branch ::= concat
10872// or concat \& concat
10873// or concat \& concat \& concat
10874// etc.
10875static int nfa_regbranch(void)
10876{
10877 int old_post_pos;
10878
10879 old_post_pos = (int)(post_ptr - post_start);
10880
10881 // First branch, possibly the only one
10882 if (nfa_regconcat() == FAIL0) {
10883 return FAIL0;
10884 }
10885
10886 // Try next concats
10887 while (peekchr() == Magic('&')((int)('&') - 256)) {
10888 skipchr();
10889 // if concat is empty do emit a node
10890 if (old_post_pos == (int)(post_ptr - post_start)) {
10891 EMIT(NFA_EMPTY)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_EMPTY; } while (0);
10892 }
10893 EMIT(NFA_NOPEN)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_NOPEN; } while (0);
10894 EMIT(NFA_PREV_ATOM_NO_WIDTH)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_PREV_ATOM_NO_WIDTH; } while (0);
10895 old_post_pos = (int)(post_ptr - post_start);
10896 if (nfa_regconcat() == FAIL0) {
10897 return FAIL0;
10898 }
10899 // if concat is empty do emit a node
10900 if (old_post_pos == (int)(post_ptr - post_start)) {
10901 EMIT(NFA_EMPTY)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_EMPTY; } while (0);
10902 }
10903 EMIT(NFA_CONCAT)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_CONCAT; } while (0);
10904 }
10905
10906 // if a branch is empty, emit one node for it
10907 if (old_post_pos == (int)(post_ptr - post_start)) {
10908 EMIT(NFA_EMPTY)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_EMPTY; } while (0);
10909 }
10910
10911 return OK1;
10912}
10913
10914/// Parse a pattern, one or more branches, separated by "\|". It matches
10915/// anything that matches one of the branches. Example: "foo\|beep" matches
10916/// "foo" and matches "beep". If more than one branch matches, the first one
10917/// is used.
10918///
10919/// pattern ::= branch
10920/// or branch \| branch
10921/// or branch \| branch \| branch
10922/// etc.
10923///
10924/// @param paren REG_NOPAREN, REG_PAREN, REG_NPAREN or REG_ZPAREN
10925static int nfa_reg(int paren)
10926{
10927 int parno = 0;
10928
10929 if (paren == REG_PAREN1) {
10930 if (regnpar >= NSUBEXP) { // Too many `('
10931 EMSG_RET_FAIL(_("E872: (NFA regexp) Too many '('"))return (emsg(gettext("E872: (NFA regexp) Too many '('")), rc_did_emsg
= 1, 0);
10932 }
10933 parno = regnpar++;
10934 } else if (paren == REG_ZPAREN2) {
10935 // Make a ZOPEN node.
10936 if (regnzpar >= NSUBEXP) {
10937 EMSG_RET_FAIL(_("E879: (NFA regexp) Too many \\z("))return (emsg(gettext("E879: (NFA regexp) Too many \\z(")), rc_did_emsg
= 1, 0);
10938 }
10939 parno = regnzpar++;
10940 }
10941
10942 if (nfa_regbranch() == FAIL0) {
10943 return FAIL0; // cascaded error
10944 }
10945 while (peekchr() == Magic('|')((int)('|') - 256)) {
10946 skipchr();
10947 if (nfa_regbranch() == FAIL0) {
10948 return FAIL0; // cascaded error
10949 }
10950 EMIT(NFA_OR)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_OR; } while (0);
10951 }
10952
10953 // Check for proper termination.
10954 if (paren != REG_NOPAREN0 && getchr() != Magic(')')((int)(')') - 256)) {
10955 if (paren == REG_NPAREN3) {
10956 EMSG2_RET_FAIL(_(e_unmatchedpp), reg_magic == MAGIC_ALL)return (semsg((gettext(e_unmatchedpp)), (reg_magic == MAGIC_ALL
) ? "" : "\\"), rc_did_emsg = 1, 0);
10957 } else {
10958 EMSG2_RET_FAIL(_(e_unmatchedp), reg_magic == MAGIC_ALL)return (semsg((gettext(e_unmatchedp)), (reg_magic == MAGIC_ALL
) ? "" : "\\"), rc_did_emsg = 1, 0);
10959 }
10960 } else if (paren == REG_NOPAREN0 && peekchr() != NUL'\000') {
10961 if (peekchr() == Magic(')')((int)(')') - 256)) {
10962 EMSG2_RET_FAIL(_(e_unmatchedpar), reg_magic == MAGIC_ALL)return (semsg((gettext(e_unmatchedpar)), (reg_magic == MAGIC_ALL
) ? "" : "\\"), rc_did_emsg = 1, 0);
10963 } else {
10964 EMSG_RET_FAIL(_("E873: (NFA regexp) proper termination error"))return (emsg(gettext("E873: (NFA regexp) proper termination error"
)), rc_did_emsg = 1, 0);
10965 }
10966 }
10967 // Here we set the flag allowing back references to this set of
10968 // parentheses.
10969 if (paren == REG_PAREN1) {
10970 had_endbrace[parno] = true1; // have seen the close paren
10971 EMIT(NFA_MOPEN + parno)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_MOPEN + parno; } while (0);
10972 } else if (paren == REG_ZPAREN2) {
10973 EMIT(NFA_ZOPEN + parno)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_ZOPEN + parno; } while (0);
10974 }
10975
10976 return OK1;
10977}

11118 case NFA_ZOPEN:

11331// Print the postfix notation of the current regexp.
11332static void nfa_postfix_dump(uint8_t *expr, int retval)
11333{
11334 int *p;
11335 FILE *f;
11336
11337 f = fopen(NFA_REGEXP_DUMP_LOG, "a");
11338 if (f == NULL((void*)0)) {
11339 return;
11340 }
11341
11342 fprintf(f, "\n-------------------------\n");
11343 if (retval == FAIL0) {
11344 fprintf(f, ">>> NFA engine failed... \n");
11345 } else if (retval == OK1) {
11346 fprintf(f, ">>> NFA engine succeeded !\n");
11347 }
11348 fprintf(f, "Regexp: \"%s\"\nPostfix notation (char): \"", expr);
11349 for (p = post_start; *p && p < post_ptr; p++) {
11350 nfa_set_code(*p);
11351 fprintf(f, "%s, ", code);
11352 }
11353 fprintf(f, "\"\nPostfix notation (int): ");
11354 for (p = post_start; *p && p < post_ptr; p++) {
11355 fprintf(f, "%d ", *p);
11356 }
11357 fprintf(f, "\n\n");
11358 fclose(f);
11359}
11360
11361// Print the NFA starting with a root node "state".
11362static void nfa_print_state(FILE *debugf, nfa_state_T *state)
11363{
11364 garray_T indent;
11365
11366 ga_init(&indent, 1, 64);
11367 ga_append(&indent, '\0');
11368 nfa_print_state2(debugf, state, &indent);
11369 ga_clear(&indent);
11370}
11371
11372static void nfa_print_state2(FILE *debugf, nfa_state_T *state, garray_T *indent)
11373{
11374 uint8_t *p;
11375
11376 if (state == NULL((void*)0)) {
11377 return;
11378 }
11379
11380 fprintf(debugf, "(%2d)", abs(state->id));
11381
11382 // Output indent
11383 p = (uint8_t *)indent->ga_data;
11384 if (indent->ga_len >= 3) {
11385 int last = indent->ga_len - 3;
11386 uint8_t save[2];
11387
11388 strncpy(save, &p[last], 2); // NOLINT(runtime/printf)
11389 memcpy(&p[last], "+-", 2);
11390 fprintf(debugf, " %s", p);
11391 strncpy(&p[last], save, 2); // NOLINT(runtime/printf)
11392 } else {
11393 fprintf(debugf, " %s", p);
11394 }
11395
11396 nfa_set_code(state->c);
11397 fprintf(debugf, "%s (%d) (id=%d) val=%d\n",
11398 code,
11399 state->c,
11400 abs(state->id),
11401 state->val);
11402 if (state->id < 0) {
11403 return;
11404 }
11405
11406 state->id = abs(state->id) * -1;
11407
11408 // grow indent for state->out
11409 indent->ga_len -= 1;
11410 if (state->out1) {
11411 ga_concat(indent, (uint8_t *)"| ");
11412 } else {
11413 ga_concat(indent, (uint8_t *)" ");
11414 }
11415 ga_append(indent, NUL'\000');
11416
11417 nfa_print_state2(debugf, state->out, indent);
11418
11419 // replace last part of indent for state->out1
11420 indent->ga_len -= 3;
11421 ga_concat(indent, (uint8_t *)" ");
11422 ga_append(indent, NUL'\000');
11423
11424 nfa_print_state2(debugf, state->out1, indent);
11425
11426 // shrink indent
11427 indent->ga_len -= 3;
11428 ga_append(indent, NUL'\000');
11429}

11431// Print the NFA state machine.
11432static void nfa_dump(nfa_regprog_T *prog)
11433{
11434 FILE *debugf = fopen(NFA_REGEXP_DUMP_LOG, "a");
11435
11436 if (debugf == NULL((void*)0)) {
11437 return;
11438 }
11439
11440 nfa_print_state(debugf, prog->start);
11441
11442 if (prog->reganch) {
11443 fprintf(debugf, "reganch: %d\n", prog->reganch);
11444 }
11445 if (prog->regstart != NUL'\000') {
11446 fprintf(debugf, "regstart: %c (decimal: %d)\n",
11447 prog->regstart, prog->regstart);
11448 }
11449 if (prog->match_text != NULL((void*)0)) {
11450 fprintf(debugf, "match_text: \"%s\"\n", prog->match_text);
11451 }
11452
11453 fclose(debugf);
11454}

11457// Parse r.e. @expr and convert it into postfix form.
11458// Return the postfix string on success, NULL otherwise.
11459static int *re2post(void)
11460{
11461 if (nfa_reg(REG_NOPAREN0) == FAIL0) {
11462 return NULL((void*)0);
11463 }
11464 EMIT(NFA_MOPEN)do { if (post_ptr >= post_end) { realloc_post_list(); } *post_ptr
++ = NFA_MOPEN; } while (0);
11465 return post_start;
11466}
11467
11468// NB. Some of the code below is inspired by Russ's.
11469
11470// Represents an NFA state plus zero or one or two arrows exiting.
11471// if c == MATCH, no arrows out; matching state.
11472// If c == SPLIT, unlabeled arrows to out and out1 (if != NULL).
11473// If c < 256, labeled arrow with character c to out.
11474
11475static nfa_state_T *state_ptr; // points to nfa_prog->state
11476
11477// Allocate and initialize nfa_state_T.
11478static nfa_state_T *alloc_state(int c, nfa_state_T *out, nfa_state_T *out1)
11479{
11480 nfa_state_T *s;
11481
11482 if (istate >= nstate) {
11483 return NULL((void*)0);
11484 }
11485
11486 s = &state_ptr[istate++];
11487
11488 s->c = c;
11489 s->out = out;
11490 s->out1 = out1;
11491 s->val = 0;
11492
11493 s->id = istate;
11494 s->lastlist[0] = 0;
11495 s->lastlist[1] = 0;
11496
11497 return s;
11498}
11499
11500// A partially built NFA without the matching state filled in.
11501// Frag_T.start points at the start state.
11502// Frag_T.out is a list of places that need to be set to the
11503// next state for this fragment.
11504
11505// Initialize a Frag_T struct and return it.
11506static Frag_T frag(nfa_state_T *start, Ptrlist *out)
11507{
11508 Frag_T n;
11509
11510 n.start = start;
11511 n.out = out;
11512 return n;
11513}
11514
11515// Create singleton list containing just outp.
11516static Ptrlist *list1(nfa_state_T **outp)
11517{
11518 Ptrlist *l;
11519
11520 l = (Ptrlist *)outp;
11521 l->next = NULL((void*)0);
11522 return l;
11523}
11524
11525// Patch the list of states at out to point to start.
11526static void patch(Ptrlist *l, nfa_state_T *s)
11527{
11528 Ptrlist *next;
11529
11530 for (; l; l = next) {
11531 next = l->next;
11532 l->s = s;
11533 }
11534}
11535
11536// Join the two lists l1 and l2, returning the combination.
11537static Ptrlist *append(Ptrlist *l1, Ptrlist *l2)
11538{
11539 Ptrlist *oldl1;
11540
11541 oldl1 = l1;
11542 while (l1->next) {
11543 l1 = l1->next;
11544 }
11545 l1->next = l2;
11546 return oldl1;
11547}

11549// Stack used for transforming postfix form into NFA.
11550static Frag_T empty;
11551
11552static void st_error(int *postfix, int *end, int *p)
11553{
11554#ifdef NFA_REGEXP_ERROR_LOG
11555 FILE *df;
11556 int *p2;
11557
11558 df = fopen(NFA_REGEXP_ERROR_LOG, "a");
11559 if (df) {
11560 fprintf(df, "Error popping the stack!\n");
11561# ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
11562 fprintf(df, "Current regexp is \"%s\"\n", nfa_regengine.expr);
11563# endif
11564 fprintf(df, "Postfix form is: ");
11565# ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
11566 for (p2 = postfix; p2 < end; p2++) {
11567 nfa_set_code(*p2);
11568 fprintf(df, "%s, ", code);
11569 }
11570 nfa_set_code(*p);
11571 fprintf(df, "\nCurrent position is: ");
11572 for (p2 = postfix; p2 <= p; p2++) {
11573 nfa_set_code(*p2);
11574 fprintf(df, "%s, ", code);
11575 }
11576# else
11577 for (p2 = postfix; p2 < end; p2++) {
11578 fprintf(df, "%d, ", *p2);
11579 }
11580 fprintf(df, "\nCurrent position is: ");
11581 for (p2 = postfix; p2 <= p; p2++) {
11582 fprintf(df, "%d, ", *p2);
11583 }
11584# endif
11585 fprintf(df, "\n--------------------------\n");
11586 fclose(df);
11587 }
11588#endif
11589 emsg(_("E874: (NFA) Could not pop the stack!")gettext("E874: (NFA) Could not pop the stack!"));
11590}
11591
11592// Push an item onto the stack.
11593static void st_push(Frag_T s, Frag_T **p, Frag_T *stack_end)
11594{
11595 Frag_T *stackp = *p;
11596
11597 if (stackp >= stack_end) {
11598 return;
11599 }
11600 *stackp = s;
11601 *p = *p + 1;
11602}
11603
11604// Pop an item from the stack.
11605static Frag_T st_pop(Frag_T **p, Frag_T *stack)
11606{
11607 Frag_T *stackp;
11608
11609 *p = *p - 1;
10

11617// Estimate the maximum byte length of anything matching "state".
11618// When unknown or unlimited return -1.
11619static int nfa_max_width(nfa_state_T *startstate, int depth)
11620{
11621 int l, r;
11622 nfa_state_T *state = startstate;
11623 int len = 0;
11624
11625 // detect looping in a NFA_SPLIT
11626 if (depth > 4) {
11627 return -1;
11628 }
11629
11630 while (state != NULL((void*)0)) {
11631 switch (state->c) {
11632 case NFA_END_INVISIBLE:
11633 case NFA_END_INVISIBLE_NEG:
11634 // the end, return what we have
11635 return len;
11636
11637 case NFA_SPLIT:
11638 // two alternatives, use the maximum
11639 l = nfa_max_width(state->out, depth + 1);
11640 r = nfa_max_width(state->out1, depth + 1);
11641 if (l < 0 || r < 0) {
11642 return -1;
11643 }
11644 return len + (l > r ? l : r);
11645
11646 case NFA_ANY:
11647 case NFA_START_COLL:
11648 case NFA_START_NEG_COLL:
11649 // Matches some character, including composing chars.
11650 len += MB_MAXBYTES;
11651 if (state->c != NFA_ANY) {
11652 // Skip over the characters.
11653 state = state->out1->out;
11654 continue;
11655 }
11656 break;
11657
11658 case NFA_DIGIT:
11659 case NFA_WHITE:
11660 case NFA_HEX:
11661 case NFA_OCTAL:
11662 // ascii
11663 len++;
11664 break;
11665
11666 case NFA_IDENT:
11667 case NFA_SIDENT:
11668 case NFA_KWORD:
11669 case NFA_SKWORD:
11670 case NFA_FNAME:
11671 case NFA_SFNAME:
11672 case NFA_PRINT:
11673 case NFA_SPRINT:
11674 case NFA_NWHITE:
11675 case NFA_NDIGIT:
11676 case NFA_NHEX:
11677 case NFA_NOCTAL:
11678 case NFA_WORD:
11679 case NFA_NWORD:
11680 case NFA_HEAD:
11681 case NFA_NHEAD:
11682 case NFA_ALPHA:
11683 case NFA_NALPHA:
11684 case NFA_LOWER:
11685 case NFA_NLOWER:
11686 case NFA_UPPER:
11687 case NFA_NUPPER:
11688 case NFA_LOWER_IC:
11689 case NFA_NLOWER_IC:
11690 case NFA_UPPER_IC:
11691 case NFA_NUPPER_IC:
11692 case NFA_ANY_COMPOSING:
11693 // possibly non-ascii
11694 len += 3;
11695 break;
11696
11697 case NFA_START_INVISIBLE:
11698 case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_NEG:
11699 case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE:
11700 case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_NEG:
11701 // zero-width, out1 points to the END state
11702 state = state->out1->out;
11703 continue;
11704
11705 case NFA_BACKREF1:
11706 case NFA_BACKREF2:
11707 case NFA_BACKREF3:
11708 case NFA_BACKREF4:
11709 case NFA_BACKREF5:

11712 case NFA_BACKREF8:
11713 case NFA_BACKREF9:

11719 case NFA_ZREF6:

11721 case NFA_ZREF8:
11722 case NFA_ZREF9:
11723 case NFA_NEWL:
11724 case NFA_SKIP:
11725 // unknown width
11726 return -1;
11727
11728 case NFA_BOL:
11729 case NFA_EOL:
11730 case NFA_BOF:
11731 case NFA_EOF:
11732 case NFA_BOW:
11733 case NFA_EOW:
11734 case NFA_MOPEN:
11735 case NFA_MOPEN1:
11736 case NFA_MOPEN2:
11737 case NFA_MOPEN3:
11738 case NFA_MOPEN4:
11739 case NFA_MOPEN5:
11740 case NFA_MOPEN6:
11741 case NFA_MOPEN7:
11742 case NFA_MOPEN8:
11743 case NFA_MOPEN9:
11744 case NFA_ZOPEN:
11745 case NFA_ZOPEN1:
11746 case NFA_ZOPEN2:
11747 case NFA_ZOPEN3:
11748 case NFA_ZOPEN4:
11749 case NFA_ZOPEN5:
11750 case NFA_ZOPEN6:

11756 case NFA_ZCLOSE2:

11758 case NFA_ZCLOSE4:

11760 case NFA_ZCLOSE6:

11769 case NFA_MCLOSE5:
11770 case NFA_MCLOSE6:
11771 case NFA_MCLOSE7:
11772 case NFA_MCLOSE8:
11773 case NFA_MCLOSE9:
11774 case NFA_NOPEN:
11775 case NFA_NCLOSE:
11776
11777 case NFA_LNUM_GT:
11778 case NFA_LNUM_LT:
11779 case NFA_COL_GT:
11780 case NFA_COL_LT:
11781 case NFA_VCOL_GT:
11782 case NFA_VCOL_LT:

11798 case NFA_COMPOSING:
11799 case NFA_END_COMPOSING:
11800 // zero-width
11801 break;
11802
11803 default:
11804 if (state->c < 0) {
11805 // don't know what this is
11806 return -1;
11807 }
11808 // normal character
11809 len += utf_char2len(state->c);
11810 break;
11811 }
11812
11813 // normal way to continue
11814 state = state->out;
11815 }
11816
11817 // unrecognized, "cannot happen"
11818 return -1;
11819}

12284 break;
12285 }
12286

12288 case NFA_ZEND:
12289 default:
12290 // Operands
12291 if (nfa_calc_size == true1) {
12292 nstate++;
12293 break;
12294 }
12295 s = alloc_state(*p, NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0));
12296 if (s == NULL((void*)0)) {
12297 goto theend;
12298 }
12299 PUSH(frag(s, list1(&s->out)));
12300 break;
12301 } // switch(*p)
12302 } // for(p = postfix; *p; ++p)
12303

12341
12342// After building the NFA program, inspect it to add optimization hints.
12343static void nfa_postprocess(nfa_regprog_T *prog)
12344{
12345 int i;
12346 int c;
12347
12348 for (i = 0; i < prog->nstate; i++) {
12349 c = prog->state[i].c;
12350 if (c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE
12351 || c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_NEG
12352 || c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE
12353 || c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_NEG) {
12354 int directly;
12355
12356 // Do it directly when what follows is possibly the end of the
12357 // match.
12358 if (match_follows(prog->state[i].out1->out, 0)) {
12359 directly = true1;
12360 } else {
12361 int ch_invisible = failure_chance(prog->state[i].out, 0);
12362 int ch_follows = failure_chance(prog->state[i].out1->out, 0);
12363
12364 // Postpone when the invisible match is expensive or has a
12365 // lower chance of failing.
12366 if (c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE
12367 || c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_NEG) {
12368 // "before" matches are very expensive when
12369 // unbounded, always prefer what follows then,
12370 // unless what follows will always match.
12371 // Otherwise strongly prefer what follows.
12372 if (prog->state[i].val <= 0 && ch_follows > 0) {
12373 directly = false0;
12374 } else {
12375 directly = ch_follows * 10 < ch_invisible;
12376 }
12377 } else {
12378 // normal invisible, first do the one with the
12379 // highest failure chance
12380 directly = ch_follows < ch_invisible;
12381 }
12382 }
12383 if (directly) {
12384 // switch to the _FIRST state
12385 prog->state[i].c++;
12386 }
12387 }
12388 }
12389}

12457// Copy postponed invisible match info from "from" to "to".
12458static void copy_pim(nfa_pim_T *to, nfa_pim_T *from)
12459{
12460 to->result = from->result;
12461 to->state = from->state;
12462 copy_sub(&to->subs.norm, &from->subs.norm);
12463 if (rex.nfa_has_zsubexpr) {
12464 copy_sub(&to->subs.synt, &from->subs.synt);

12469static void clear_sub(regsub_T *sub)
12470{
12471 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
12472 // Use 0xff to set lnum to -1
12473 memset(sub->list.multi, 0xff, sizeof(struct multipos) * (size_t)rex.nfa_nsubexpr);
12474 } else {
12475 memset(sub->list.line, 0, sizeof(struct linepos) * (size_t)rex.nfa_nsubexpr);
12476 }
12477 sub->in_use = 0;
12478}
12479
12480// Copy the submatches from "from" to "to".
12481static void copy_sub(regsub_T *to, regsub_T *from)
12482{
12483 to->in_use = from->in_use;
12484 if (from->in_use <= 0) {
12485 return;
12486 }
12487
12488 // Copy the match start and end positions.
12489 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
12490 memmove(&to->list.multi[0], &from->list.multi[0],
12491 sizeof(struct multipos) * (size_t)from->in_use);
12492 to->orig_start_col = from->orig_start_col;
12493 } else {
12494 memmove(&to->list.line[0], &from->list.line[0],
12495 sizeof(struct linepos) * (size_t)from->in_use);
12496 }
12497}
12498
12499// Like copy_sub() but exclude the main match.
12500static void copy_sub_off(regsub_T *to, regsub_T *from)
12501{
12502 if (to->in_use < from->in_use) {
12503 to->in_use = from->in_use;
12504 }
12505 if (from->in_use <= 1) {
12506 return;
12507 }
12508
12509 // Copy the match start and end positions.
12510 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
12511 memmove(&to->list.multi[1], &from->list.multi[1],
12512 sizeof(struct multipos) * (size_t)(from->in_use - 1));
12513 } else {
12514 memmove(&to->list.line[1], &from->list.line[1],
12515 sizeof(struct linepos) * (size_t)(from->in_use - 1));
12516 }
12517}
12518
12519// Like copy_sub() but only do the end of the main match if \ze is present.
12520static void copy_ze_off(regsub_T *to, regsub_T *from)
12521{
12522 if (!rex.nfa_has_zend) {
12523 return;
12524 }
12525
12526 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
12527 if (from->list.multi[0].end_lnum >= 0) {
12528 to->list.multi[0].end_lnum = from->list.multi[0].end_lnum;
12529 to->list.multi[0].end_col = from->list.multi[0].end_col;
12530 }
12531 } else {
12532 if (from->list.line[0].end != NULL((void*)0)) {
12533 to->list.line[0].end = from->list.line[0].end;
12534 }
12535 }
12536}

12538// Return true if "sub1" and "sub2" have the same start positions.
12539// When using back-references also check the end position.
12540static bool_Bool sub_equal(regsub_T *sub1, regsub_T *sub2)
12541{
12542 int i;
12543 int todo;
12544 linenr_T s1;
12545 linenr_T s2;
12546 uint8_t *sp1;
12547 uint8_t *sp2;
12548
12549 todo = sub1->in_use > sub2->in_use ? sub1->in_use : sub2->in_use;
12550 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
12551 for (i = 0; i < todo; i++) {
12552 if (i < sub1->in_use) {
12553 s1 = sub1->list.multi[i].start_lnum;
12554 } else {
12555 s1 = -1;
12556 }
12557 if (i < sub2->in_use) {
12558 s2 = sub2->list.multi[i].start_lnum;
12559 } else {
12560 s2 = -1;
12561 }
12562 if (s1 != s2) {
12563 return false0;
12564 }
12565 if (s1 != -1 && sub1->list.multi[i].start_col
12566 != sub2->list.multi[i].start_col) {
12567 return false0;
12568 }
12569 if (rex.nfa_has_backref) {
12570 if (i < sub1->in_use) {
12571 s1 = sub1->list.multi[i].end_lnum;
12572 } else {
12573 s1 = -1;
12574 }
12575 if (i < sub2->in_use) {
12576 s2 = sub2->list.multi[i].end_lnum;
12577 } else {
12578 s2 = -1;
12579 }
12580 if (s1 != s2) {
12581 return false0;
12582 }
12583 if (s1 != -1
12584 && sub1->list.multi[i].end_col != sub2->list.multi[i].end_col) {
12585 return false0;
12586 }
12587 }
12588 }
12589 } else {
12590 for (i = 0; i < todo; i++) {
12591 if (i < sub1->in_use) {
12592 sp1 = sub1->list.line[i].start;
12593 } else {
12594 sp1 = NULL((void*)0);
12595 }
12596 if (i < sub2->in_use) {
12597 sp2 = sub2->list.line[i].start;
12598 } else {
12599 sp2 = NULL((void*)0);
12600 }
12601 if (sp1 != sp2) {
12602 return false0;
12603 }
12604 if (rex.nfa_has_backref) {
12605 if (i < sub1->in_use) {
12606 sp1 = sub1->list.line[i].end;
12607 } else {
12608 sp1 = NULL((void*)0);
12609 }
12610 if (i < sub2->in_use) {
12611 sp2 = sub2->list.line[i].end;
12612 } else {
12613 sp2 = NULL((void*)0);
12614 }
12615 if (sp1 != sp2) {
12616 return false0;
12617 }
12618 }
12619 }
12620 }
12621
12622 return true1;
12623}

12640static void report_state(char *action, regsub_T *sub, nfa_state_T *state, int lid, nfa_pim_T *pim)
12641{
12642 int col;
12643
12644 if (sub->in_use <= 0) {
12645 col = -1;
12646 } else if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
12647 col = sub->list.multi[0].start_col;
12648 } else {
12649 col = (int)(sub->list.line[0].start - rex.line);
12650 }
12651 nfa_set_code(state->c);
12652 if (log_fd == NULL((void*)0)) {
12653 open_debug_log(kNone);
12654 }
12655 fprintf(log_fd, "> %s state %d to list %d. char %d: %s (start col %d)%s\n",
12656 action, abs(state->id), lid, state->c, code, col,
12657 pim_info(pim));
12658}

12662/// @param l runtime state list
12663/// @param state state to update
12664/// @param subs pointers to subexpressions
12665/// @param pim postponed match or NULL
12666///
12667/// @return true if the same state is already in list "l" with the same
12668/// positions as "subs".
12669static bool_Bool has_state_with_pos(nfa_list_T *l, nfa_state_T *state, regsubs_T *subs, nfa_pim_T *pim)
12670 FUNC_ATTR_NONNULL_ARG(1, 2, 3)
12671{
12672 for (int i = 0; i < l->n; i++) {
12673 nfa_thread_T *thread = &l->t[i];
12674 if (thread->state->id == state->id
12675 && sub_equal(&thread->subs.norm, &subs->norm)
12676 && (!rex.nfa_has_zsubexpr
12677 || sub_equal(&thread->subs.synt, &subs->synt))
12678 && pim_equal(&thread->pim, pim)) {
12679 return true1;
12680 }
12681 }
12682 return false0;
12683}
12684
12685// Return true if "one" and "two" are equal. That includes when both are not
12686// set.
12687static bool_Bool pim_equal(const nfa_pim_T *one, const nfa_pim_T *two)
12688{
12689 const bool_Bool one_unused = (one == NULL((void*)0) || one->result == NFA_PIM_UNUSED0);
12690 const bool_Bool two_unused = (two == NULL((void*)0) || two->result == NFA_PIM_UNUSED0);
12691
12692 if (one_unused) {
12693 // one is unused: equal when two is also unused
12694 return two_unused;
12695 }
12696 if (two_unused) {
12697 // one is used and two is not: not equal
12698 return false0;
12699 }
12700 // compare the state id
12701 if (one->state->id != two->state->id) {
12702 return false0;
12703 }
12704 // compare the position
12705 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
12706 return one->end.pos.lnum == two->end.pos.lnum
12707 && one->end.pos.col == two->end.pos.col;
12708 }
12709 return one->end.ptr == two->end.ptr;
12710}
12711
12712// Return true if "state" leads to a NFA_MATCH without advancing the input.
12713static bool_Bool match_follows(const nfa_state_T *startstate, int depth)
12714 FUNC_ATTR_NONNULL_ALL
12715{
12716 const nfa_state_T *state = startstate;
12717
12718 // avoid too much recursion
12719 if (depth > 10) {
12720 return false0;
12721 }
12722 while (state != NULL((void*)0)) {
12723 switch (state->c) {
12724 case NFA_MATCH:
12725 case NFA_MCLOSE:
12726 case NFA_END_INVISIBLE:
12727 case NFA_END_INVISIBLE_NEG:
12728 case NFA_END_PATTERN:
12729 return true1;
12730
12731 case NFA_SPLIT:
12732 return match_follows(state->out, depth + 1)
12733 || match_follows(state->out1, depth + 1);
12734
12735 case NFA_START_INVISIBLE:
12736 case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_FIRST:
12737 case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE:
12738 case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_FIRST:
12739 case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_NEG:
12740 case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_NEG_FIRST:
12741 case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_NEG:
12742 case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_NEG_FIRST:
12743 case NFA_COMPOSING:
12744 // skip ahead to next state
12745 state = state->out1->out;
12746 continue;
12747
12748 case NFA_ANY:
12749 case NFA_ANY_COMPOSING:
12750 case NFA_IDENT:
12751 case NFA_SIDENT:
12752 case NFA_KWORD:
12753 case NFA_SKWORD:
12754 case NFA_FNAME:
12755 case NFA_SFNAME:
12756 case NFA_PRINT:
12757 case NFA_SPRINT:
12758 case NFA_WHITE:
12759 case NFA_NWHITE:
12760 case NFA_DIGIT:
12761 case NFA_NDIGIT:
12762 case NFA_HEX:
12763 case NFA_NHEX:
12764 case NFA_OCTAL:
12765 case NFA_NOCTAL:
12766 case NFA_WORD:
12767 case NFA_NWORD:
12768 case NFA_HEAD:
12769 case NFA_NHEAD:
12770 case NFA_ALPHA:
12771 case NFA_NALPHA:
12772 case NFA_LOWER:
12773 case NFA_NLOWER:
12774 case NFA_UPPER:
12775 case NFA_NUPPER:
12776 case NFA_LOWER_IC:
12777 case NFA_NLOWER_IC:
12778 case NFA_UPPER_IC:
12779 case NFA_NUPPER_IC:
12780 case NFA_START_COLL:
12781 case NFA_START_NEG_COLL:
12782 case NFA_NEWL:
12783 // state will advance input
12784 return false0;
12785
12786 default:
12787 if (state->c > 0) {
12788 // state will advance input
12789 return false0;
12790 }
12791 // Others: zero-width or possibly zero-width, might still find
12792 // a match at the same position, keep looking.
12793 break;
12794 }
12795 state = state->out;
12796 }
12797 return false0;
12798}
