12800/// @param l runtime state list
12801/// @param state state to update
12802/// @param subs pointers to subexpressions
12803///
12804/// @return true if "state" is already in list "l".
12805static bool_Bool state_in_list(nfa_list_T *l, nfa_state_T *state, regsubs_T *subs)
12806 FUNC_ATTR_NONNULL_ALL
12807{
12808 if (state->lastlist[nfa_ll_index] == l->id) {
12809 if (!rex.nfa_has_backref || has_state_with_pos(l, state, subs, NULL((void*)0))) {
12810 return true1;
12811 }
12812 }
12813 return false0;
12814}
12815
12816// Offset used for "off" by addstate_here().
12817#define ADDSTATE_HERE_OFFSET10 10
12818
12819/// Add "state" and possibly what follows to state list ".".
12820///
12821/// @param l runtime state list
12822/// @param state state to update
12823/// @param subs_arg pointers to subexpressions
12824/// @param pim postponed look-behind match
12825/// @param off_arg byte offset, when -1 go to next line
12826///
12827/// @return "subs_arg", possibly copied into temp_subs.
12828/// NULL when recursiveness is too deep.
12829static regsubs_T *addstate(nfa_list_T *l, nfa_state_T *state, regsubs_T *subs_arg, nfa_pim_T *pim,
12830 int off_arg)
12831 FUNC_ATTR_NONNULL_ARG(1, 2) FUNC_ATTR_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT
12832{
12833 int subidx;
12834 int off = off_arg;
12835 int add_here = false0;
12836 int listindex = 0;
12837 int k;
12838 int found = false0;
12839 nfa_thread_T *thread;
12840 struct multipos save_multipos;
12841 int save_in_use;
12842 uint8_t *save_ptr;
12843 int i;
12844 regsub_T *sub;
12845 regsubs_T *subs = subs_arg;
12846 static regsubs_T temp_subs;
12847#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
12848 int did_print = false0;
12849#endif
12850 static int depth = 0;
12851
12852 // This function is called recursively. When the depth is too much we run
12853 // out of stack and crash, limit recursiveness here.
12854 if (++depth >= 5000 || subs == NULL((void*)0)) {
12855 depth--;
12856 return NULL((void*)0);
12857 }
12858
12859 if (off_arg <= -ADDSTATE_HERE_OFFSET10) {
12860 add_here = true1;
12861 off = 0;
12862 listindex = -(off_arg + ADDSTATE_HERE_OFFSET10);
12863 }
12864
12865 switch (state->c) {
12866 case NFA_NCLOSE:
12867 case NFA_MCLOSE:
12868 case NFA_MCLOSE1:
12869 case NFA_MCLOSE2:
12870 case NFA_MCLOSE3:
12871 case NFA_MCLOSE4:
12872 case NFA_MCLOSE5:
12873 case NFA_MCLOSE6:
12874 case NFA_MCLOSE7:
12875 case NFA_MCLOSE8:
12876 case NFA_MCLOSE9:
12877 case NFA_ZCLOSE:
12878 case NFA_ZCLOSE1:
12879 case NFA_ZCLOSE2:
12880 case NFA_ZCLOSE3:
12881 case NFA_ZCLOSE4:
12882 case NFA_ZCLOSE5:
12883 case NFA_ZCLOSE6:
12884 case NFA_ZCLOSE7:
12885 case NFA_ZCLOSE8:
12886 case NFA_ZCLOSE9:
12887 case NFA_MOPEN:
12888 case NFA_ZEND:
12889 case NFA_SPLIT:
12890 case NFA_EMPTY:
12891 // These nodes are not added themselves but their "out" and/or
12892 // "out1" may be added below.
12893 break;
12894
12895 case NFA_BOL:
12896 case NFA_BOF:
12897 // "^" won't match past end-of-line, don't bother trying.
12898 // Except when at the end of the line, or when we are going to the
12899 // next line for a look-behind match.
12900 if (rex.input > rex.line
12901 && *rex.input != NUL'\000'
12902 && (nfa_endp == NULL((void*)0)
12903 || !REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))
12904 || rex.lnum == nfa_endp->se_u.pos.lnum)) {
12905 goto skip_add;
12906 }
12907 FALLTHROUGH{} __attribute__((fallthrough));
12908
12909 case NFA_MOPEN1:
12910 case NFA_MOPEN2:
12911 case NFA_MOPEN3:
12912 case NFA_MOPEN4:
12913 case NFA_MOPEN5:
12914 case NFA_MOPEN6:
12915 case NFA_MOPEN7:
12916 case NFA_MOPEN8:
12917 case NFA_MOPEN9:
12918 case NFA_ZOPEN:
12919 case NFA_ZOPEN1:
12920 case NFA_ZOPEN2:
12921 case NFA_ZOPEN3:
12922 case NFA_ZOPEN4:
12923 case NFA_ZOPEN5:
12924 case NFA_ZOPEN6:
12925 case NFA_ZOPEN7:
12926 case NFA_ZOPEN8:
12927 case NFA_ZOPEN9:
12928 case NFA_NOPEN:
12929 case NFA_ZSTART:
12930 // These nodes need to be added so that we can bail out when it
12931 // was added to this list before at the same position to avoid an
12932 // endless loop for "\(\)*"
12933
12934 default:
12935 if (state->lastlist[nfa_ll_index] == l->id && state->c != NFA_SKIP) {
12936 // This state is already in the list, don't add it again,
12937 // unless it is an MOPEN that is used for a backreference or
12938 // when there is a PIM. For NFA_MATCH check the position,
12939 // lower position is preferred.
12940 if (!rex.nfa_has_backref && pim == NULL((void*)0) && !l->has_pim
12941 && state->c != NFA_MATCH) {
12942 // When called from addstate_here() do insert before
12943 // existing states.
12944 if (add_here) {
12945 for (k = 0; k < l->n && k < listindex; k++) {
12946 if (l->t[k].state->id == state->id) {
12947 found = true1;
12948 break;
12949 }
12950 }
12951 }
12952
12953 if (!add_here || found) {
12954skip_add:
12955#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
12956 nfa_set_code(state->c);
12957 fprintf(log_fd,
12958 "> Not adding state %d to list %d. char %d: %s pim: %s has_pim: %d found: %d\n",
12959 abs(state->id), l->id, state->c, code,
12960 pim == NULL((void*)0) ? "NULL" : "yes", l->has_pim, found);
12961#endif
12962 depth--;
12963 return subs;
12964 }
12965 }
12966
12967 // Do not add the state again when it exists with the same
12968 // positions.
12969 if (has_state_with_pos(l, state, subs, pim)) {
12970 goto skip_add;
12971 }
12972 }
12973
12974 // When there are backreferences or PIMs the number of states may
12975 // be (a lot) bigger than anticipated.
12976 if (l->n == l->len) {
12977 const int newlen = l->len * 3 / 2 + 50;
12978 const size_t newsize = (size_t)newlen * sizeof(nfa_thread_T);
12979
12980 if ((int64_t)(newsize >> 10) >= p_mmp) {
12981 emsg(_(e_pattern_uses_more_memory_than_maxmempattern)gettext(e_pattern_uses_more_memory_than_maxmempattern));
12982 depth--;
12983 return NULL((void*)0);
12984 }
12985 if (subs != &temp_subs) {
12986 // "subs" may point into the current array, need to make a
12987 // copy before it becomes invalid.
12988 copy_sub(&temp_subs.norm, &subs->norm);
12989 if (rex.nfa_has_zsubexpr) {
12990 copy_sub(&temp_subs.synt, &subs->synt);
12991 }
12992 subs = &temp_subs;
12993 }
12994
12995 nfa_thread_T *const newt = xrealloc(l->t, newsize);
12996 l->t = newt;
12997 l->len = newlen;
12998 }
12999
13000 // add the state to the list
13001 state->lastlist[nfa_ll_index] = l->id;
13002 thread = &l->t[l->n++];
13003 thread->state = state;
13004 if (pim == NULL((void*)0)) {
13005 thread->pim.result = NFA_PIM_UNUSED0;
13006 } else {
13007 copy_pim(&thread->pim, pim);
13008 l->has_pim = true1;
13009 }
13010 copy_sub(&thread->subs.norm, &subs->norm);
13011 if (rex.nfa_has_zsubexpr) {
13012 copy_sub(&thread->subs.synt, &subs->synt);
13013 }
13014#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
13015 report_state("Adding", &thread->subs.norm, state, l->id, pim);
13016 did_print = true1;
13017#endif
13018 }
13019
13020#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
13021 if (!did_print) {
13022 report_state("Processing", &subs->norm, state, l->id, pim);
13023 }
13024#endif
13025 switch (state->c) {
13026 case NFA_MATCH:
13027 break;
13028
13029 case NFA_SPLIT:
13030 // order matters here
13031 subs = addstate(l, state->out, subs, pim, off_arg);
13032 subs = addstate(l, state->out1, subs, pim, off_arg);
13033 break;
13034
13035 case NFA_EMPTY:
13036 case NFA_NOPEN:
13037 case NFA_NCLOSE:
13038 subs = addstate(l, state->out, subs, pim, off_arg);
13039 break;
13040
13041 case NFA_MOPEN:
13042 case NFA_MOPEN1:
13043 case NFA_MOPEN2:
13044 case NFA_MOPEN3:
13045 case NFA_MOPEN4:
13046 case NFA_MOPEN5:
13047 case NFA_MOPEN6:
13048 case NFA_MOPEN7:
13049 case NFA_MOPEN8:
13050 case NFA_MOPEN9:
13051 case NFA_ZOPEN:
13052 case NFA_ZOPEN1:
13053 case NFA_ZOPEN2:
13054 case NFA_ZOPEN3:
13055 case NFA_ZOPEN4:
13056 case NFA_ZOPEN5:
13057 case NFA_ZOPEN6:
13058 case NFA_ZOPEN7:
13059 case NFA_ZOPEN8:
13060 case NFA_ZOPEN9:
13061 case NFA_ZSTART:
13062 if (state->c == NFA_ZSTART) {
13063 subidx = 0;
13064 sub = &subs->norm;
13065 } else if (state->c >= NFA_ZOPEN && state->c <= NFA_ZOPEN9) {
13066 subidx = state->c - NFA_ZOPEN;
13067 sub = &subs->synt;
13068 } else {
13069 subidx = state->c - NFA_MOPEN;
13070 sub = &subs->norm;
13071 }
13072
13073 // avoid compiler warnings
13074 save_ptr = NULL((void*)0);
13075 CLEAR_FIELD(save_multipos)memset(&(save_multipos), 0, sizeof(save_multipos));
13076
13077 // Set the position (with "off" added) in the subexpression. Save
13078 // and restore it when it was in use. Otherwise fill any gap.
13079 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
13080 if (subidx < sub->in_use) {
13081 save_multipos = sub->list.multi[subidx];
13082 save_in_use = -1;
13083 } else {
13084 save_in_use = sub->in_use;
13085 for (i = sub->in_use; i < subidx; i++) {
13086 sub->list.multi[i].start_lnum = -1;
13087 sub->list.multi[i].end_lnum = -1;
13088 }
13089 sub->in_use = subidx + 1;
13090 }
13091 if (off == -1) {
13092 sub->list.multi[subidx].start_lnum = rex.lnum + 1;
13093 sub->list.multi[subidx].start_col = 0;
13094 } else {
13095 sub->list.multi[subidx].start_lnum = rex.lnum;
13096 sub->list.multi[subidx].start_col =
13097 (colnr_T)(rex.input - rex.line + off);
13098 }
13099 sub->list.multi[subidx].end_lnum = -1;
13100 } else {
13101 if (subidx < sub->in_use) {
13102 save_ptr = sub->list.line[subidx].start;
13103 save_in_use = -1;
13104 } else {
13105 save_in_use = sub->in_use;
13106 for (i = sub->in_use; i < subidx; i++) {
13107 sub->list.line[i].start = NULL((void*)0);
13108 sub->list.line[i].end = NULL((void*)0);
13109 }
13110 sub->in_use = subidx + 1;
13111 }
13112 sub->list.line[subidx].start = rex.input + off;
13113 }
13114
13115 subs = addstate(l, state->out, subs, pim, off_arg);
13116 if (subs == NULL((void*)0)) {
13117 break;
13118 }
13119 // "subs" may have changed, need to set "sub" again.
13120 if (state->c >= NFA_ZOPEN && state->c <= NFA_ZOPEN9) {
13121 sub = &subs->synt;
13122 } else {
13123 sub = &subs->norm;
13124 }
13125
13126 if (save_in_use == -1) {
13127 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
13128 sub->list.multi[subidx] = save_multipos;
13129 } else {
13130 sub->list.line[subidx].start = save_ptr;
13131 }
13132 } else {
13133 sub->in_use = save_in_use;
13134 }
13135 break;
13136
13137 case NFA_MCLOSE:
13138 if (rex.nfa_has_zend
13139 && (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))
13140 ? subs->norm.list.multi[0].end_lnum >= 0
13141 : subs->norm.list.line[0].end != NULL((void*)0))) {
13142 // Do not overwrite the position set by \ze.
13143 subs = addstate(l, state->out, subs, pim, off_arg);
13144 break;
13145 }
13146 FALLTHROUGH{} __attribute__((fallthrough));
13147 case NFA_MCLOSE1:
13148 case NFA_MCLOSE2:
13149 case NFA_MCLOSE3:
13150 case NFA_MCLOSE4:
13151 case NFA_MCLOSE5:
13152 case NFA_MCLOSE6:
13153 case NFA_MCLOSE7:
13154 case NFA_MCLOSE8:
13155 case NFA_MCLOSE9:
13156 case NFA_ZCLOSE:
13157 case NFA_ZCLOSE1:
13158 case NFA_ZCLOSE2:
13159 case NFA_ZCLOSE3:
13160 case NFA_ZCLOSE4:
13161 case NFA_ZCLOSE5:
13162 case NFA_ZCLOSE6:
13163 case NFA_ZCLOSE7:
13164 case NFA_ZCLOSE8:
13165 case NFA_ZCLOSE9:
13166 case NFA_ZEND:
13167 if (state->c == NFA_ZEND) {
13168 subidx = 0;
13169 sub = &subs->norm;
13170 } else if (state->c >= NFA_ZCLOSE && state->c <= NFA_ZCLOSE9) {
13171 subidx = state->c - NFA_ZCLOSE;
13172 sub = &subs->synt;
13173 } else {
13174 subidx = state->c - NFA_MCLOSE;
13175 sub = &subs->norm;
13176 }
13177
13178 // We don't fill in gaps here, there must have been an MOPEN that
13179 // has done that.
13180 save_in_use = sub->in_use;
13181 if (sub->in_use <= subidx) {
13182 sub->in_use = subidx + 1;
13183 }
13184 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
13185 save_multipos = sub->list.multi[subidx];
13186 if (off == -1) {
13187 sub->list.multi[subidx].end_lnum = rex.lnum + 1;
13188 sub->list.multi[subidx].end_col = 0;
13189 } else {
13190 sub->list.multi[subidx].end_lnum = rex.lnum;
13191 sub->list.multi[subidx].end_col =
13192 (colnr_T)(rex.input - rex.line + off);
13193 }
13194 // avoid compiler warnings
13195 save_ptr = NULL((void*)0);
13196 } else {
13197 save_ptr = sub->list.line[subidx].end;
13198 sub->list.line[subidx].end = rex.input + off;
13199 // avoid compiler warnings
13200 CLEAR_FIELD(save_multipos)memset(&(save_multipos), 0, sizeof(save_multipos));
13201 }
13202
13203 subs = addstate(l, state->out, subs, pim, off_arg);
13204 if (subs == NULL((void*)0)) {
13205 break;
13206 }
13207 // "subs" may have changed, need to set "sub" again.
13208 if (state->c >= NFA_ZCLOSE && state->c <= NFA_ZCLOSE9) {
13209 sub = &subs->synt;
13210 } else {
13211 sub = &subs->norm;
13212 }
13213
13214 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
13215 sub->list.multi[subidx] = save_multipos;
13216 } else {
13217 sub->list.line[subidx].end = save_ptr;
13218 }
13219 sub->in_use = save_in_use;
13220 break;
13221 }
13222 depth--;
13223 return subs;
13224}
13225
13226/// Like addstate(), but the new state(s) are put at position "*ip".
13227/// Used for zero-width matches, next state to use is the added one.
13228/// This makes sure the order of states to be tried does not change, which
13229/// matters for alternatives.
13230///
13231/// @param l runtime state list
13232/// @param state state to update
13233/// @param subs pointers to subexpressions
13234/// @param pim postponed look-behind match
13235static regsubs_T *addstate_here(nfa_list_T *l, nfa_state_T *state, regsubs_T *subs, nfa_pim_T *pim,
13236 int *ip)
13237 FUNC_ATTR_NONNULL_ARG(1, 2, 5) FUNC_ATTR_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT
13238{
13239 int tlen = l->n;
13240 int count;
13241 int listidx = *ip;
13242
13243 // First add the state(s) at the end, so that we know how many there are.
13244 // Pass the listidx as offset (avoids adding another argument to
13245 // addstate()).
13246 regsubs_T *r = addstate(l, state, subs, pim, -listidx - ADDSTATE_HERE_OFFSET10);
13247 if (r == NULL((void*)0)) {
13248 return NULL((void*)0);
13249 }
13250
13251 // when "*ip" was at the end of the list, nothing to do
13252 if (listidx + 1 == tlen) {
13253 return r;
13254 }
13255
13256 // re-order to put the new state at the current position
13257 count = l->n - tlen;
13258 if (count == 0) {
13259 return r; // no state got added
13260 }
13261 if (count == 1) {
13262 // overwrite the current state
13263 l->t[listidx] = l->t[l->n - 1];
13264 } else if (count > 1) {
13265 if (l->n + count - 1 >= l->len) {
13266 // not enough space to move the new states, reallocate the list
13267 // and move the states to the right position
13268 const int newlen = l->len * 3 / 2 + 50;
13269 const size_t newsize = (size_t)newlen * sizeof(nfa_thread_T);
13270
13271 if ((int64_t)(newsize >> 10) >= p_mmp) {
13272 emsg(_(e_pattern_uses_more_memory_than_maxmempattern)gettext(e_pattern_uses_more_memory_than_maxmempattern));
13273 return NULL((void*)0);
13274 }
13275 nfa_thread_T *const newl = xmalloc(newsize);
13276 l->len = newlen;
13277 memmove(&(newl[0]),
13278 &(l->t[0]),
13279 sizeof(nfa_thread_T) * (size_t)listidx);
13280 memmove(&(newl[listidx]),
13281 &(l->t[l->n - count]),
13282 sizeof(nfa_thread_T) * (size_t)count);
13283 memmove(&(newl[listidx + count]),
13284 &(l->t[listidx + 1]),
13285 sizeof(nfa_thread_T) * (size_t)(l->n - count - listidx - 1));
13286 xfree(l->t);
13287 l->t = newl;
13288 } else {
13289 // make space for new states, then move them from the
13290 // end to the current position
13291 memmove(&(l->t[listidx + count]),
13292 &(l->t[listidx + 1]),
13293 sizeof(nfa_thread_T) * (size_t)(l->n - listidx - 1));
13294 memmove(&(l->t[listidx]),
13295 &(l->t[l->n - 1]),
13296 sizeof(nfa_thread_T) * (size_t)count);
13297 }
13298 }
13299 l->n--;
13300 *ip = listidx - 1;
13301
13302 return r;
13303}
13304
13305// Check character class "class" against current character c.
13306static int check_char_class(int cls, int c)
13307{
13308 switch (cls) {
13309 case NFA_CLASS_ALNUM:
13310 if (c >= 1 && c < 128 && isalnum(c)((*__ctype_b_loc ())[(int) ((c))] & (unsigned short int) _ISalnum
)) {
13311 return OK1;
13312 }
13313 break;
13314 case NFA_CLASS_ALPHA:
13315 if (c >= 1 && c < 128 && isalpha(c)((*__ctype_b_loc ())[(int) ((c))] & (unsigned short int) _ISalpha
)) {
13316 return OK1;
13317 }
13318 break;
13319 case NFA_CLASS_BLANK:
13320 if (c == ' ' || c == '\t') {
13321 return OK1;
13322 }
13323 break;
13324 case NFA_CLASS_CNTRL:
13325 if (c >= 1 && c <= 127 && iscntrl(c)((*__ctype_b_loc ())[(int) ((c))] & (unsigned short int) _IScntrl
)) {
13326 return OK1;
13327 }
13328 break;
13329 case NFA_CLASS_DIGIT:
13330 if (ascii_isdigit(c)) {
13331 return OK1;
13332 }
13333 break;
13334 case NFA_CLASS_GRAPH:
13335 if (c >= 1 && c <= 127 && isgraph(c)((*__ctype_b_loc ())[(int) ((c))] & (unsigned short int) _ISgraph
)) {
13336 return OK1;
13337 }
13338 break;
13339 case NFA_CLASS_LOWER:
13340 if (mb_islower(c) && c != 170 && c != 186) {
13341 return OK1;
13342 }
13343 break;
13344 case NFA_CLASS_PRINT:
13345 if (vim_isprintc(c)) {
13346 return OK1;
13347 }
13348 break;
13349 case NFA_CLASS_PUNCT:
13350 if (c >= 1 && c < 128 && ispunct(c)((*__ctype_b_loc ())[(int) ((c))] & (unsigned short int) _ISpunct
)) {
13351 return OK1;
13352 }
13353 break;
13354 case NFA_CLASS_SPACE:
13355 if ((c >= 9 && c <= 13) || (c == ' ')) {
13356 return OK1;
13357 }
13358 break;
13359 case NFA_CLASS_UPPER:
13360 if (mb_isupper(c)) {
13361 return OK1;
13362 }
13363 break;
13364 case NFA_CLASS_XDIGIT:
13365 if (ascii_isxdigit(c)) {
13366 return OK1;
13367 }
13368 break;
13369 case NFA_CLASS_TAB:
13370 if (c == '\t') {
13371 return OK1;
13372 }
13373 break;
13374 case NFA_CLASS_RETURN:
13375 if (c == '\r') {
13376 return OK1;
13377 }
13378 break;
13379 case NFA_CLASS_BACKSPACE:
13380 if (c == '\b') {
13381 return OK1;
13382 }
13383 break;
13384 case NFA_CLASS_ESCAPE:
13385 if (c == ESC'\033') {
13386 return OK1;
13387 }
13388 break;
13389 case NFA_CLASS_IDENT:
13390 if (vim_isIDc(c)) {
13391 return OK1;
13392 }
13393 break;
13394 case NFA_CLASS_KEYWORD:
13395 if (reg_iswordc(c)) {
13396 return OK1;
13397 }
13398 break;
13399 case NFA_CLASS_FNAME:
13400 if (vim_isfilec(c)) {
13401 return OK1;
13402 }
13403 break;
13404
13405 default:
13406 // should not be here :P
13407 siemsg(_(e_ill_char_class)gettext(e_ill_char_class), (int64_t)cls);
13408 return FAIL0;
13409 }
13410 return FAIL0;
13411}
13412
13413/// Check for a match with subexpression "subidx".
13414///
13415/// @param sub pointers to subexpressions
13416/// @param bytelen out: length of match in bytes
13417///
13418/// @return true if it matches.
13419static int match_backref(regsub_T *sub, int subidx, int *bytelen)
13420{
13421 int len;
13422
13423 if (sub->in_use <= subidx) {
13424retempty:
13425 // backref was not set, match an empty string
13426 *bytelen = 0;
13427 return true1;
13428 }
13429
13430 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
13431 if (sub->list.multi[subidx].start_lnum < 0
13432 || sub->list.multi[subidx].end_lnum < 0) {
13433 goto retempty;
13434 }
13435 if (sub->list.multi[subidx].start_lnum == rex.lnum
13436 && sub->list.multi[subidx].end_lnum == rex.lnum) {
13437 len = sub->list.multi[subidx].end_col
13438 - sub->list.multi[subidx].start_col;
13439 if (cstrncmp((char *)rex.line + sub->list.multi[subidx].start_col,
13440 (char *)rex.input, &len) == 0) {
13441 *bytelen = len;
13442 return true1;
13443 }
13444 } else {
13445 if (match_with_backref(sub->list.multi[subidx].start_lnum,
13446 sub->list.multi[subidx].start_col,
13447 sub->list.multi[subidx].end_lnum,
13448 sub->list.multi[subidx].end_col,
13449 bytelen) == RA_MATCH4) {
13450 return true1;
13451 }
13452 }
13453 } else {
13454 if (sub->list.line[subidx].start == NULL((void*)0)
13455 || sub->list.line[subidx].end == NULL((void*)0)) {
13456 goto retempty;
13457 }
13458 len = (int)(sub->list.line[subidx].end - sub->list.line[subidx].start);
13459 if (cstrncmp((char *)sub->list.line[subidx].start, (char *)rex.input, &len) == 0) {
13460 *bytelen = len;
13461 return true1;
13462 }
13463 }
13464 return false0;
13465}
13466
13467/// Check for a match with \z subexpression "subidx".
13468///
13469/// @param bytelen out: length of match in bytes
13470///
13471/// @return true if it matches.
13472static int match_zref(int subidx, int *bytelen)
13473{
13474 int len;
13475
13476 cleanup_zsubexpr();
13477 if (re_extmatch_in == NULL((void*)0) || re_extmatch_in->matches[subidx] == NULL((void*)0)) {
13478 // backref was not set, match an empty string
13479 *bytelen = 0;
13480 return true1;
13481 }
13482
13483 len = (int)strlen((char *)re_extmatch_in->matches[subidx]);
13484 if (cstrncmp((char *)re_extmatch_in->matches[subidx], (char *)rex.input, &len) == 0) {
13485 *bytelen = len;
13486 return true1;
13487 }
13488 return false0;
13489}
13490
13491// Save list IDs for all NFA states of "prog" into "list".
13492// Also reset the IDs to zero.
13493// Only used for the recursive value lastlist[1].
13494static void nfa_save_listids(nfa_regprog_T *prog, int *list)
13495{
13496 int i;
13497 nfa_state_T *p;
13498
13499 // Order in the list is reverse, it's a bit faster that way.
13500 p = &prog->state[0];
13501 for (i = prog->nstate; --i >= 0;) {
13502 list[i] = p->lastlist[1];
13503 p->lastlist[1] = 0;
13504 p++;
13505 }
13506}
13507
13508// Restore list IDs from "list" to all NFA states.
13509static void nfa_restore_listids(nfa_regprog_T *prog, const int *list)
13510{
13511 int i;
13512 nfa_state_T *p;
13513
13514 p = &prog->state[0];
13515 for (i = prog->nstate; --i >= 0;) {
13516 p->lastlist[1] = list[i];
13517 p++;
13518 }
13519}
13520
13521static bool_Bool nfa_re_num_cmp(uintmax_t val, int op, uintmax_t pos)
13522{
13523 if (op == 1) {
13524 return pos > val;
13525 }
13526 if (op == 2) {
13527 return pos < val;
13528 }
13529 return val == pos;
13530}
13531
13532// Recursively call nfa_regmatch()
13533// "pim" is NULL or contains info about a Postponed Invisible Match (start
13534// position).
13535static int recursive_regmatch(nfa_state_T *state, nfa_pim_T *pim, nfa_regprog_T *prog,
13536 regsubs_T *submatch, regsubs_T *m, int **listids, int *listids_len)
13537 FUNC_ATTR_NONNULL_ARG(1, 3, 5, 6, 7)
13538{
13539 const int save_reginput_col = (int)(rex.input - rex.line);
13540 const int save_reglnum = rex.lnum;
13541 const int save_nfa_match = nfa_match;
13542 const int save_nfa_listid = rex.nfa_listid;
13543 save_se_T *const save_nfa_endp = nfa_endp;
13544 save_se_T endpos;
13545 save_se_T *endposp = NULL((void*)0);
13546 int need_restore = false0;
13547
13548 if (pim != NULL((void*)0)) {
13549 // start at the position where the postponed match was
13550 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
13551 rex.input = rex.line + pim->end.pos.col;
13552 } else {
13553 rex.input = pim->end.ptr;
13554 }
13555 }
13556
13557 if (state->c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE
13558 || state->c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_FIRST
13559 || state->c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_NEG
13560 || state->c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_NEG_FIRST) {
13561 // The recursive match must end at the current position. When "pim" is
13562 // not NULL it specifies the current position.
13563 endposp = &endpos;
13564 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
13565 if (pim == NULL((void*)0)) {
13566 endpos.se_u.pos.col = (int)(rex.input - rex.line);
13567 endpos.se_u.pos.lnum = rex.lnum;
13568 } else {
13569 endpos.se_u.pos = pim->end.pos;
13570 }
13571 } else {
13572 if (pim == NULL((void*)0)) {
13573 endpos.se_u.ptr = rex.input;
13574 } else {
13575 endpos.se_u.ptr = pim->end.ptr;
13576 }
13577 }
13578
13579 // Go back the specified number of bytes, or as far as the
13580 // start of the previous line, to try matching "\@<=" or
13581 // not matching "\@<!". This is very inefficient, limit the number of
13582 // bytes if possible.
13583 if (state->val <= 0) {
13584 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
13585 rex.line = (uint8_t *)reg_getline(--rex.lnum);
13586 if (rex.line == NULL((void*)0)) {
13587 // can't go before the first line
13588 rex.line = (uint8_t *)reg_getline(++rex.lnum);
13589 }
13590 }
13591 rex.input = rex.line;
13592 } else {
13593 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0)) && (int)(rex.input - rex.line) < state->val) {
13594 // Not enough bytes in this line, go to end of
13595 // previous line.
13596 rex.line = (uint8_t *)reg_getline(--rex.lnum);
13597 if (rex.line == NULL((void*)0)) {
13598 // can't go before the first line
13599 rex.line = (uint8_t *)reg_getline(++rex.lnum);
13600 rex.input = rex.line;
13601 } else {
13602 rex.input = rex.line + strlen((char *)rex.line);
13603 }
13604 }
13605 if ((int)(rex.input - rex.line) >= state->val) {
13606 rex.input -= state->val;
13607 rex.input -= utf_head_off((char *)rex.line, (char *)rex.input);
13608 } else {
13609 rex.input = rex.line;
13610 }
13611 }
13612 }
13613
13614#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
13615 if (log_fd != stderrstderr) {
13616 fclose(log_fd);
13617 }
13618 log_fd = NULL((void*)0);
13619#endif
13620 // Have to clear the lastlist field of the NFA nodes, so that
13621 // nfa_regmatch() and addstate() can run properly after recursion.
13622 if (nfa_ll_index == 1) {
13623 // Already calling nfa_regmatch() recursively. Save the lastlist[1]
13624 // values and clear them.
13625 if (*listids == NULL((void*)0) || *listids_len < prog->nstate) {
13626 xfree(*listids);
13627 *listids = xmalloc(sizeof(**listids) * (size_t)prog->nstate);
13628 *listids_len = prog->nstate;
13629 }
13630 nfa_save_listids(prog, *listids);
13631 need_restore = true1;
13632 // any value of rex.nfa_listid will do
13633 } else {
13634 // First recursive nfa_regmatch() call, switch to the second lastlist
13635 // entry. Make sure rex.nfa_listid is different from a previous
13636 // recursive call, because some states may still have this ID.
13637 nfa_ll_index++;
13638 if (rex.nfa_listid <= rex.nfa_alt_listid) {
13639 rex.nfa_listid = rex.nfa_alt_listid;
13640 }
13641 }
13642
13643 // Call nfa_regmatch() to check if the current concat matches at this
13644 // position. The concat ends with the node NFA_END_INVISIBLE
13645 nfa_endp = endposp;
13646 const int result = nfa_regmatch(prog, state->out, submatch, m);
13647
13648 if (need_restore) {
13649 nfa_restore_listids(prog, *listids);
13650 } else {
13651 nfa_ll_index--;
13652 rex.nfa_alt_listid = rex.nfa_listid;
13653 }
13654
13655 // restore position in input text
13656 rex.lnum = save_reglnum;
13657 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
13658 rex.line = (uint8_t *)reg_getline(rex.lnum);
13659 }
13660 rex.input = rex.line + save_reginput_col;
13661 if (result != NFA_TOO_EXPENSIVE) {
13662 nfa_match = save_nfa_match;
13663 rex.nfa_listid = save_nfa_listid;
13664 }
13665 nfa_endp = save_nfa_endp;
13666
13667#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
13668 open_debug_log(result);
13669#endif
13670
13671 return result;
13672}
13673
13674// Estimate the chance of a match with "state" failing.
13675// empty match: 0
13676// NFA_ANY: 1
13677// specific character: 99
13678static int failure_chance(nfa_state_T *state, int depth)
13679{
13680 int c = state->c;
13681 int l, r;
13682
13683 // detect looping
13684 if (depth > 4) {
13685 return 1;
13686 }
13687
13688 switch (c) {
13689 case NFA_SPLIT:
13690 if (state->out->c == NFA_SPLIT || state->out1->c == NFA_SPLIT) {
13691 // avoid recursive stuff
13692 return 1;
13693 }
13694 // two alternatives, use the lowest failure chance
13695 l = failure_chance(state->out, depth + 1);
13696 r = failure_chance(state->out1, depth + 1);
13697 return l < r ? l : r;
13698
13699 case NFA_ANY:
13700 // matches anything, unlikely to fail
13701 return 1;
13702
13703 case NFA_MATCH:
13704 case NFA_MCLOSE:
13705 case NFA_ANY_COMPOSING:
13706 // empty match works always
13707 return 0;
13708
13709 case NFA_START_INVISIBLE:
13710 case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_FIRST:
13711 case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_NEG:
13712 case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_NEG_FIRST:
13713 case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE:
13714 case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_FIRST:
13715 case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_NEG:
13716 case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_NEG_FIRST:
13717 case NFA_START_PATTERN:
13718 // recursive regmatch is expensive, use low failure chance
13719 return 5;
13720
13721 case NFA_BOL:
13722 case NFA_EOL:
13723 case NFA_BOF:
13724 case NFA_EOF:
13725 case NFA_NEWL:
13726 return 99;
13727
13728 case NFA_BOW:
13729 case NFA_EOW:
13730 return 90;
13731
13732 case NFA_MOPEN:
13733 case NFA_MOPEN1:
13734 case NFA_MOPEN2:
13735 case NFA_MOPEN3:
13736 case NFA_MOPEN4:
13737 case NFA_MOPEN5:
13738 case NFA_MOPEN6:
13739 case NFA_MOPEN7:
13740 case NFA_MOPEN8:
13741 case NFA_MOPEN9:
13742 case NFA_ZOPEN:
13743 case NFA_ZOPEN1:
13744 case NFA_ZOPEN2:
13745 case NFA_ZOPEN3:
13746 case NFA_ZOPEN4:
13747 case NFA_ZOPEN5:
13748 case NFA_ZOPEN6:
13749 case NFA_ZOPEN7:
13750 case NFA_ZOPEN8:
13751 case NFA_ZOPEN9:
13752 case NFA_ZCLOSE:
13753 case NFA_ZCLOSE1:
13754 case NFA_ZCLOSE2:
13755 case NFA_ZCLOSE3:
13756 case NFA_ZCLOSE4:
13757 case NFA_ZCLOSE5:
13758 case NFA_ZCLOSE6:
13759 case NFA_ZCLOSE7:
13760 case NFA_ZCLOSE8:
13761 case NFA_ZCLOSE9:
13762 case NFA_NOPEN:
13763 case NFA_MCLOSE1:
13764 case NFA_MCLOSE2:
13765 case NFA_MCLOSE3:
13766 case NFA_MCLOSE4:
13767 case NFA_MCLOSE5:
13768 case NFA_MCLOSE6:
13769 case NFA_MCLOSE7:
13770 case NFA_MCLOSE8:
13771 case NFA_MCLOSE9:
13772 case NFA_NCLOSE:
13773 return failure_chance(state->out, depth + 1);
13774
13775 case NFA_BACKREF1:
13776 case NFA_BACKREF2:
13777 case NFA_BACKREF3:
13778 case NFA_BACKREF4:
13779 case NFA_BACKREF5:
13780 case NFA_BACKREF6:
13781 case NFA_BACKREF7:
13782 case NFA_BACKREF8:
13783 case NFA_BACKREF9:
13784 case NFA_ZREF1:
13785 case NFA_ZREF2:
13786 case NFA_ZREF3:
13787 case NFA_ZREF4:
13788 case NFA_ZREF5:
13789 case NFA_ZREF6:
13790 case NFA_ZREF7:
13791 case NFA_ZREF8:
13792 case NFA_ZREF9:
13793 // backreferences don't match in many places
13794 return 94;
13795
13796 case NFA_LNUM_GT:
13797 case NFA_LNUM_LT:
13798 case NFA_COL_GT:
13799 case NFA_COL_LT:
13800 case NFA_VCOL_GT:
13801 case NFA_VCOL_LT:
13802 case NFA_MARK_GT:
13803 case NFA_MARK_LT:
13804 case NFA_VISUAL:
13805 // before/after positions don't match very often
13806 return 85;
13807
13808 case NFA_LNUM:
13809 return 90;
13810
13811 case NFA_CURSOR:
13812 case NFA_COL:
13813 case NFA_VCOL:
13814 case NFA_MARK:
13815 // specific positions rarely match
13816 return 98;
13817
13818 case NFA_COMPOSING:
13819 return 95;
13820
13821 default:
13822 if (c > 0) {
13823 // character match fails often
13824 return 95;
13825 }
13826 }
13827
13828 // something else, includes character classes
13829 return 50;
13830}
13831
13832// Skip until the char "c" we know a match must start with.
13833static int skip_to_start(int c, colnr_T *colp)
13834{
13835 const uint8_t *const s = (uint8_t *)cstrchr((char *)rex.line + *colp, c);
13836 if (s == NULL((void*)0)) {
13837 return FAIL0;
13838 }
13839 *colp = (int)(s - rex.line);
13840 return OK1;
13841}
13842
13843// Check for a match with match_text.
13844// Called after skip_to_start() has found regstart.
13845// Returns zero for no match, 1 for a match.
13846static int find_match_text(colnr_T *startcol, int regstart, uint8_t *match_text)
13847{
13848#define PTR2LEN(x) utf_ptr2len(x)
13849
13850 colnr_T col = *startcol;
13851 int regstart_len = PTR2LEN((char *)rex.line + col);
13852
13853 while (true1) {
13854 bool_Bool match = true1;
13855 uint8_t *s1 = match_text;
13856 uint8_t *s2 = rex.line + col + regstart_len; // skip regstart
13857 while (*s1) {
13858 int c1_len = PTR2LEN((char *)s1);
13859 int c1 = utf_ptr2char((char *)s1);
13860 int c2_len = PTR2LEN((char *)s2);
13861 int c2 = utf_ptr2char((char *)s2);
13862
13863 if ((c1 != c2 && (!rex.reg_ic || utf_fold(c1) != utf_fold(c2)))
13864 || c1_len != c2_len) {
13865 match = false0;
13866 break;
13867 }
13868 s1 += c1_len;
13869 s2 += c2_len;
13870 }
13871 if (match
13872 // check that no composing char follows
13873 && !utf_iscomposing(utf_ptr2char((char *)s2))) {
13874 cleanup_subexpr();
13875 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
13876 rex.reg_startpos[0].lnum = rex.lnum;
13877 rex.reg_startpos[0].col = col;
13878 rex.reg_endpos[0].lnum = rex.lnum;
13879 rex.reg_endpos[0].col = (colnr_T)(s2 - rex.line);
13880 } else {
13881 rex.reg_startp[0] = rex.line + col;
13882 rex.reg_endp[0] = s2;
13883 }
13884 *startcol = col;
13885 return 1L;
13886 }
13887
13888 // Try finding regstart after the current match.
13889 col += regstart_len; // skip regstart
13890 if (skip_to_start(regstart, &col) == FAIL0) {
13891 break;
13892 }
13893 }
13894
13895 *startcol = col;
13896 return 0L;
13897
13898#undef PTR2LEN
13899}
13900
13901static int nfa_did_time_out(void)
13902{
13903 if (nfa_time_limit != NULL((void*)0) && profile_passed_limit(*nfa_time_limit)) {
13904 if (nfa_timed_out != NULL((void*)0)) {
13905 *nfa_timed_out = true1;
13906 }
13907 return true1;
13908 }
13909 return false0;
13910}
13911
13912/// Main matching routine.
13913///
13914/// Run NFA to determine whether it matches rex.input.
13915///
13916/// When "nfa_endp" is not NULL it is a required end-of-match position.
13917///
13918/// Return true if there is a match, false if there is no match,
13919/// NFA_TOO_EXPENSIVE if we end up with too many states.
13920/// When there is a match "submatch" contains the positions.
13921///
13922/// Note: Caller must ensure that: start != NULL.
13923static int nfa_regmatch(nfa_regprog_T *prog, nfa_state_T *start, regsubs_T *submatch, regsubs_T *m)
13924 FUNC_ATTR_NONNULL_ARG(1, 2, 4)
13925{
13926 int result = false0;
13927 int flag = 0;
13928 bool_Bool go_to_nextline = false0;
13929 nfa_thread_T *t;
13930 nfa_list_T list[2];
13931 int listidx;
13932 nfa_list_T *thislist;
13933 nfa_list_T *nextlist;
13934 int *listids = NULL((void*)0);
13935 int listids_len = 0;
13936 nfa_state_T *add_state;
13937 bool_Bool add_here;
13938 int add_count;
13939 int add_off = 0;
13940 int toplevel = start->c == NFA_MOPEN;
13941 regsubs_T *r;
13942 // Some patterns may take a long time to match, especially when using
13943 // recursive_regmatch(). Allow interrupting them with CTRL-C.
13944 reg_breakcheck();
13945 if (got_int) {
13946 return false0;
13947 }
13948 if (nfa_did_time_out()) {
13949 return false0;
13950 }
13951
13952#ifdef NFA_REGEXP_DEBUG_LOG
13953 FILE *debug = fopen(NFA_REGEXP_DEBUG_LOG, "a");
13954
13955 if (debug == NULL((void*)0)) {
13956 semsg("(NFA) COULD NOT OPEN %s!", NFA_REGEXP_DEBUG_LOG);
13957 return false0;
13958 }
13959#endif
13960 nfa_match = false0;
13961
13962 // Allocate memory for the lists of nodes.
13963 size_t size = (size_t)(prog->nstate + 1) * sizeof(nfa_thread_T);
13964 list[0].t = xmalloc(size);
13965 list[0].len = prog->nstate + 1;
13966 list[1].t = xmalloc(size);
13967 list[1].len = prog->nstate + 1;
13968
13969#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
13970 log_fd = fopen(NFA_REGEXP_RUN_LOG, "a");
13971 if (log_fd == NULL((void*)0)) {
13972 emsg(_(e_log_open_failed)gettext(e_log_open_failed));
13973 log_fd = stderrstderr;
13974 }
13975 fprintf(log_fd, "**********************************\n");
13976 nfa_set_code(start->c);
13977 fprintf(log_fd, " RUNNING nfa_regmatch() starting with state %d, code %s\n",
13978 abs(start->id), code);
13979 fprintf(log_fd, "**********************************\n");
13980#endif
13981
13982 thislist = &list[0];
13983 thislist->n = 0;
13984 thislist->has_pim = false0;
13985 nextlist = &list[1];
13986 nextlist->n = 0;
13987 nextlist->has_pim = false0;
13988#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
13989 fprintf(log_fd, "(---) STARTSTATE first\n");
13990#endif
13991 thislist->id = rex.nfa_listid + 1;
13992
13993 // Inline optimized code for addstate(thislist, start, m, 0) if we know
13994 // it's the first MOPEN.
13995 if (toplevel) {
13996 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
13997 m->norm.list.multi[0].start_lnum = rex.lnum;
13998 m->norm.list.multi[0].start_col = (colnr_T)(rex.input - rex.line);
13999 m->norm.orig_start_col = m->norm.list.multi[0].start_col;
14000 } else {
14001 m->norm.list.line[0].start = rex.input;
14002 }
14003 m->norm.in_use = 1;
14004 r = addstate(thislist, start->out, m, NULL((void*)0), 0);
14005 } else {
14006 r = addstate(thislist, start, m, NULL((void*)0), 0);
14007 }
14008 if (r == NULL((void*)0)) {
14009 nfa_match = NFA_TOO_EXPENSIVE;
14010 goto theend;
14011 }
14012
14013#define ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(state) \
14014 if (result) { \
14015 add_state = (state)->out; \
14016 add_off = clen; \
14017 }
14018
14019 // Run for each character.
14020 while (true1) {
14021 int curc = utf_ptr2char((char *)rex.input);
14022 int clen = utfc_ptr2len((char *)rex.input);
14023 if (curc == NUL'\000') {
14024 clen = 0;
14025 go_to_nextline = false0;
14026 }
14027
14028 // swap lists
14029 thislist = &list[flag];
14030 nextlist = &list[flag ^= 1];
14031 nextlist->n = 0; // clear nextlist
14032 nextlist->has_pim = false0;
14033 rex.nfa_listid++;
14034 if (prog->re_engine == AUTOMATIC_ENGINE
14035 && (rex.nfa_listid >= NFA_MAX_STATES)) {
14036 // Too many states, retry with old engine.
14037 nfa_match = NFA_TOO_EXPENSIVE;
14038 goto theend;
14039 }
14040
14041 thislist->id = rex.nfa_listid;
14042 nextlist->id = rex.nfa_listid + 1;
14043
14044#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
14045 fprintf(log_fd, "------------------------------------------\n");
14046 fprintf(log_fd, ">>> Reginput is \"%s\"\n", rex.input);
14047 fprintf(log_fd,
14048 ">>> Advanced one character... Current char is %c (code %d) \n",
14049 curc,
14050 (int)curc);
14051 fprintf(log_fd, ">>> Thislist has %d states available: ", thislist->n);
14052 {
14053 int i;
14054
14055 for (i = 0; i < thislist->n; i++) {
14056 fprintf(log_fd, "%d ", abs(thislist->t[i].state->id));
14057 }
14058 }
14059 fprintf(log_fd, "\n");
14060#endif
14061
14062#ifdef NFA_REGEXP_DEBUG_LOG
14063 fprintf(debug, "\n-------------------\n");
14064#endif
14065 // If the state lists are empty we can stop.
14066 if (thislist->n == 0) {
14067 break;
14068 }
14069
14070 // compute nextlist
14071 for (listidx = 0; listidx < thislist->n; listidx++) {
14072 // If the list gets very long there probably is something wrong.
14073 // At least allow interrupting with CTRL-C.
14074 reg_breakcheck();
14075 if (got_int) {
14076 break;
14077 }
14078 if (nfa_time_limit != NULL((void*)0) && ++nfa_time_count == 20) {
14079 nfa_time_count = 0;
14080 if (nfa_did_time_out()) {
14081 break;
14082 }
14083 }
14084 t = &thislist->t[listidx];
14085
14086#ifdef NFA_REGEXP_DEBUG_LOG
14087 nfa_set_code(t->state->c);
14088 fprintf(debug, "%s, ", code);
14089#endif
14090#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
14091 {
14092 int col;
14093
14094 if (t->subs.norm.in_use <= 0) {
14095 col = -1;
14096 } else if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
14097 col = t->subs.norm.list.multi[0].start_col;
14098 } else {
14099 col = (int)(t->subs.norm.list.line[0].start - rex.line);
14100 }
14101 nfa_set_code(t->state->c);
14102 fprintf(log_fd, "(%d) char %d %s (start col %d)%s... \n",
14103 abs(t->state->id), (int)t->state->c, code, col,
14104 pim_info(&t->pim));
14105 }
14106#endif
14107
14108 // Handle the possible codes of the current state.
14109 // The most important is NFA_MATCH.
14110 add_state = NULL((void*)0);
14111 add_here = false0;
14112 add_count = 0;
14113 switch (t->state->c) {
14114 case NFA_MATCH:
14115 // If the match is not at the start of the line, ends before a
14116 // composing characters and rex.reg_icombine is not set, that
14117 // is not really a match.
14118 if (!rex.reg_icombine
14119 && rex.input != rex.line
14120 && utf_iscomposing(curc)) {
14121 break;
14122 }
14123 nfa_match = true1;
14124 copy_sub(&submatch->norm, &t->subs.norm);
14125 if (rex.nfa_has_zsubexpr) {
14126 copy_sub(&submatch->synt, &t->subs.synt);
14127 }
14128#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
14129 log_subsexpr(&t->subs);
14130#endif
14131 // Found the left-most longest match, do not look at any other
14132 // states at this position. When the list of states is going
14133 // to be empty quit without advancing, so that "rex.input" is
14134 // correct.
14135 if (nextlist->n == 0) {
14136 clen = 0;
14137 }
14138 goto nextchar;
14139
14140 case NFA_END_INVISIBLE:
14141 case NFA_END_INVISIBLE_NEG:
14142 case NFA_END_PATTERN:
14143 // This is only encountered after a NFA_START_INVISIBLE or
14144 // NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE node.
14145 // They surround a zero-width group, used with "\@=", "\&",
14146 // "\@!", "\@<=" and "\@<!".
14147 // If we got here, it means that the current "invisible" group
14148 // finished successfully, so return control to the parent
14149 // nfa_regmatch(). For a look-behind match only when it ends
14150 // in the position in "nfa_endp".
14151 // Submatches are stored in *m, and used in the parent call.
14152#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
14153 if (nfa_endp != NULL((void*)0)) {
14154 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
14155 fprintf(log_fd,
14156 "Current lnum: %d, endp lnum: %d;"
14157 " current col: %d, endp col: %d\n",
14158 (int)rex.lnum,
14159 (int)nfa_endp->se_u.pos.lnum,
14160 (int)(rex.input - rex.line),
14161 nfa_endp->se_u.pos.col);
14162 } else {
14163 fprintf(log_fd, "Current col: %d, endp col: %d\n",
14164 (int)(rex.input - rex.line),
14165 (int)(nfa_endp->se_u.ptr - rex.input));
14166 }
14167 }
14168#endif
14169 // If "nfa_endp" is set it's only a match if it ends at
14170 // "nfa_endp"
14171 if (nfa_endp != NULL((void*)0)
14172 && (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))
14173 ? (rex.lnum != nfa_endp->se_u.pos.lnum
14174 || (int)(rex.input - rex.line) != nfa_endp->se_u.pos.col)
14175 : rex.input != nfa_endp->se_u.ptr)) {
14176 break;
14177 }
14178 // do not set submatches for \@!
14179 if (t->state->c != NFA_END_INVISIBLE_NEG) {
14180 copy_sub(&m->norm, &t->subs.norm);
14181 if (rex.nfa_has_zsubexpr) {
14182 copy_sub(&m->synt, &t->subs.synt);
14183 }
14184 }
14185#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
14186 fprintf(log_fd, "Match found:\n");
14187 log_subsexpr(m);
14188#endif
14189 nfa_match = true1;
14190 // See comment above at "goto nextchar".
14191 if (nextlist->n == 0) {
14192 clen = 0;
14193 }
14194 goto nextchar;
14195
14196 case NFA_START_INVISIBLE:
14197 case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_FIRST:
14198 case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_NEG:
14199 case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_NEG_FIRST:
14200 case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE:
14201 case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_FIRST:
14202 case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_NEG:
14203 case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_NEG_FIRST:
14204#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
14205 fprintf(log_fd, "Failure chance invisible: %d, what follows: %d\n",
14206 failure_chance(t->state->out, 0),
14207 failure_chance(t->state->out1->out, 0));
14208#endif
14209 // Do it directly if there already is a PIM or when
14210 // nfa_postprocess() detected it will work better.
14211 if (t->pim.result != NFA_PIM_UNUSED0
14212 || t->state->c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_FIRST
14213 || t->state->c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_NEG_FIRST
14214 || t->state->c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_FIRST
14215 || t->state->c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_NEG_FIRST) {
14216 int in_use = m->norm.in_use;
14217
14218 // Copy submatch info for the recursive call, opposite
14219 // of what happens on success below.
14220 copy_sub_off(&m->norm, &t->subs.norm);
14221 if (rex.nfa_has_zsubexpr) {
14222 copy_sub_off(&m->synt, &t->subs.synt);
14223 }
14224 // First try matching the invisible match, then what
14225 // follows.
14226 result = recursive_regmatch(t->state, NULL((void*)0), prog, submatch, m,
14227 &listids, &listids_len);
14228 if (result == NFA_TOO_EXPENSIVE) {
14229 nfa_match = result;
14230 goto theend;
14231 }
14232
14233 // for \@! and \@<! it is a match when the result is
14234 // false
14235 if (result != (t->state->c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_NEG
14236 || t->state->c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_NEG_FIRST
14237 || t->state->c
14238 == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_NEG
14239 || t->state->c
14240 == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_NEG_FIRST)) {
14241 // Copy submatch info from the recursive call
14242 copy_sub_off(&t->subs.norm, &m->norm);
14243 if (rex.nfa_has_zsubexpr) {
14244 copy_sub_off(&t->subs.synt, &m->synt);
14245 }
14246 // If the pattern has \ze and it matched in the
14247 // sub pattern, use it.
14248 copy_ze_off(&t->subs.norm, &m->norm);
14249
14250 // t->state->out1 is the corresponding
14251 // END_INVISIBLE node; Add its out to the current
14252 // list (zero-width match).
14253 add_here = true1;
14254 add_state = t->state->out1->out;
14255 }
14256 m->norm.in_use = in_use;
14257 } else {
14258 nfa_pim_T pim;
14259
14260 // First try matching what follows. Only if a match
14261 // is found verify the invisible match matches. Add a
14262 // nfa_pim_T to the following states, it contains info
14263 // about the invisible match.
14264 pim.state = t->state;
14265 pim.result = NFA_PIM_TODO1;
14266 pim.subs.norm.in_use = 0;
14267 pim.subs.synt.in_use = 0;
14268 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
14269 pim.end.pos.col = (int)(rex.input - rex.line);
14270 pim.end.pos.lnum = rex.lnum;
14271 } else {
14272 pim.end.ptr = rex.input;
14273 }
14274 // t->state->out1 is the corresponding END_INVISIBLE
14275 // node; Add its out to the current list (zero-width
14276 // match).
14277 if (addstate_here(thislist, t->state->out1->out, &t->subs,
14278 &pim, &listidx) == NULL((void*)0)) {
14279 nfa_match = NFA_TOO_EXPENSIVE;
14280 goto theend;
14281 }
14282 }
14283 break;
14284
14285 case NFA_START_PATTERN: {
14286 nfa_state_T *skip = NULL((void*)0);
14287#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
14288 int skip_lid = 0;
14289#endif
14290
14291 // There is no point in trying to match the pattern if the
14292 // output state is not going to be added to the list.
14293 if (state_in_list(nextlist, t->state->out1->out, &t->subs)) {
14294 skip = t->state->out1->out;
14295#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
14296 skip_lid = nextlist->id;
14297#endif
14298 } else if (state_in_list(nextlist,
14299 t->state->out1->out->out, &t->subs)) {
14300 skip = t->state->out1->out->out;
14301#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
14302 skip_lid = nextlist->id;
14303#endif
14304 } else if (state_in_list(thislist,
14305 t->state->out1->out->out, &t->subs)) {
14306 skip = t->state->out1->out->out;
14307#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
14308 skip_lid = thislist->id;
14309#endif
14310 }
14311 if (skip != NULL((void*)0)) {
14312#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
14313 nfa_set_code(skip->c);
14314 fprintf(log_fd,
14315 "> Not trying to match pattern, output state %d is already in list %d. char %d: %s\n",
14316 abs(skip->id), skip_lid, skip->c, code);
14317#endif
14318 break;
14319 }
14320 // Copy submatch info to the recursive call, opposite of what
14321 // happens afterwards.
14322 copy_sub_off(&m->norm, &t->subs.norm);
14323 if (rex.nfa_has_zsubexpr) {
14324 copy_sub_off(&m->synt, &t->subs.synt);
14325 }
14326
14327 // First try matching the pattern.
14328 result = recursive_regmatch(t->state, NULL((void*)0), prog, submatch, m,
14329 &listids, &listids_len);
14330 if (result == NFA_TOO_EXPENSIVE) {
14331 nfa_match = result;
14332 goto theend;
14333 }
14334 if (result) {
14335 int bytelen;
14336
14337#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
14338 fprintf(log_fd, "NFA_START_PATTERN matches:\n");
14339 log_subsexpr(m);
14340#endif
14341 // Copy submatch info from the recursive call
14342 copy_sub_off(&t->subs.norm, &m->norm);
14343 if (rex.nfa_has_zsubexpr) {
14344 copy_sub_off(&t->subs.synt, &m->synt);
14345 }
14346 // Now we need to skip over the matched text and then
14347 // continue with what follows.
14348 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
14349 // TODO(RE): multi-line match
14350 bytelen = m->norm.list.multi[0].end_col
14351 - (int)(rex.input - rex.line);
14352 } else {
14353 bytelen = (int)(m->norm.list.line[0].end - rex.input);
14354 }
14355
14356#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
14357 fprintf(log_fd, "NFA_START_PATTERN length: %d\n", bytelen);
14358#endif
14359 if (bytelen == 0) {
14360 // empty match, output of corresponding
14361 // NFA_END_PATTERN/NFA_SKIP to be used at current
14362 // position
14363 add_here = true1;
14364 add_state = t->state->out1->out->out;
14365 } else if (bytelen <= clen) {
14366 // match current character, output of corresponding
14367 // NFA_END_PATTERN to be used at next position.
14368 add_state = t->state->out1->out->out;
14369 add_off = clen;
14370 } else {
14371 // skip over the matched characters, set character
14372 // count in NFA_SKIP
14373 add_state = t->state->out1->out;
14374 add_off = bytelen;
14375 add_count = bytelen - clen;
14376 }
14377 }
14378 break;
14379 }
14380
14381 case NFA_BOL:
14382 if (rex.input == rex.line) {
14383 add_here = true1;
14384 add_state = t->state->out;
14385 }
14386 break;
14387
14388 case NFA_EOL:
14389 if (curc == NUL'\000') {
14390 add_here = true1;
14391 add_state = t->state->out;
14392 }
14393 break;
14394
14395 case NFA_BOW:
14396 result = true1;
14397
14398 if (curc == NUL'\000') {
14399 result = false0;
14400 } else {
14401 int this_class;
14402
14403 // Get class of current and previous char (if it exists).
14404 this_class = mb_get_class_tab((char *)rex.input, rex.reg_buf->b_chartab);
14405 if (this_class <= 1) {
14406 result = false0;
14407 } else if (reg_prev_class() == this_class) {
14408 result = false0;
14409 }
14410 }
14411 if (result) {
14412 add_here = true1;
14413 add_state = t->state->out;
14414 }
14415 break;
14416
14417 case NFA_EOW:
14418 result = true1;
14419 if (rex.input == rex.line) {
14420 result = false0;
14421 } else {
14422 int this_class, prev_class;
14423
14424 // Get class of current and previous char (if it exists).
14425 this_class = mb_get_class_tab((char *)rex.input, rex.reg_buf->b_chartab);
14426 prev_class = reg_prev_class();
14427 if (this_class == prev_class
14428 || prev_class == 0 || prev_class == 1) {
14429 result = false0;
14430 }
14431 }
14432 if (result) {
14433 add_here = true1;
14434 add_state = t->state->out;
14435 }
14436 break;
14437
14438 case NFA_BOF:
14439 if (rex.lnum == 0 && rex.input == rex.line
14440 && (!REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0)) || rex.reg_firstlnum == 1)) {
14441 add_here = true1;
14442 add_state = t->state->out;
14443 }
14444 break;
14445
14446 case NFA_EOF:
14447 if (rex.lnum == rex.reg_maxline && curc == NUL'\000') {
14448 add_here = true1;
14449 add_state = t->state->out;
14450 }
14451 break;
14452
14453 case NFA_COMPOSING: {
14454 int mc = curc;
14455 int len = 0;
14456 nfa_state_T *end;
14457 nfa_state_T *sta;
14458 int cchars[MAX_MCO6];
14459 int ccount = 0;
14460 int j;
14461
14462 sta = t->state->out;
14463 len = 0;
14464 if (utf_iscomposing(sta->c)) {
14465 // Only match composing character(s), ignore base
14466 // character. Used for ".{composing}" and "{composing}"
14467 // (no preceding character).
14468 len += utf_char2len(mc);
14469 }
14470 if (rex.reg_icombine && len == 0) {
14471 // If \Z was present, then ignore composing characters.
14472 // When ignoring the base character this always matches.
14473 if (sta->c != curc) {
14474 result = FAIL0;
14475 } else {
14476 result = OK1;
14477 }
14478 while (sta->c != NFA_END_COMPOSING) {
14479 sta = sta->out;
14480 }
14481 } else if (len > 0 || mc == sta->c) {
14482 // Check base character matches first, unless ignored.
14483 if (len == 0) {
14484 len += utf_char2len(mc);
14485 sta = sta->out;
14486 }
14487
14488 // We don't care about the order of composing characters.
14489 // Get them into cchars[] first.
14490 while (len < clen) {
14491 mc = utf_ptr2char((char *)rex.input + len);
14492 cchars[ccount++] = mc;
14493 len += utf_char2len(mc);
14494 if (ccount == MAX_MCO6) {
14495 break;
14496 }
14497 }
14498
14499 // Check that each composing char in the pattern matches a
14500 // composing char in the text. We do not check if all
14501 // composing chars are matched.
14502 result = OK1;
14503 while (sta->c != NFA_END_COMPOSING) {
14504 for (j = 0; j < ccount; j++) {
14505 if (cchars[j] == sta->c) {
14506 break;
14507 }
14508 }
14509 if (j == ccount) {
14510 result = FAIL0;
14511 break;
14512 }
14513 sta = sta->out;
14514 }
14515 } else {
14516 result = FAIL0;
14517 }
14518
14519 end = t->state->out1; // NFA_END_COMPOSING
14520 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(end);
14521 break;
14522 }
14523
14524 case NFA_NEWL:
14525 if (curc == NUL'\000' && !rex.reg_line_lbr && REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))
14526 && rex.lnum <= rex.reg_maxline) {
14527 go_to_nextline = true1;
14528 // Pass -1 for the offset, which means taking the position
14529 // at the start of the next line.
14530 add_state = t->state->out;
14531 add_off = -1;
14532 } else if (curc == '\n' && rex.reg_line_lbr) {
14533 // match \n as if it is an ordinary character
14534 add_state = t->state->out;
14535 add_off = 1;
14536 }
14537 break;
14538
14539 case NFA_START_COLL:
14540 case NFA_START_NEG_COLL: {
14541 // What follows is a list of characters, until NFA_END_COLL.
14542 // One of them must match or none of them must match.
14543 nfa_state_T *state;
14544 int result_if_matched;
14545 int c1, c2;
14546
14547 // Never match EOL. If it's part of the collection it is added
14548 // as a separate state with an OR.
14549 if (curc == NUL'\000') {
14550 break;
14551 }
14552
14553 state = t->state->out;
14554 result_if_matched = (t->state->c == NFA_START_COLL);
14555 while (true1) {
14556 if (state->c == NFA_COMPOSING) {
14557 int mc = curc;
14558 int len = 0;
14559 nfa_state_T *end;
14560 nfa_state_T *sta;
14561 int cchars[MAX_MCO6];
14562 int ccount = 0;
14563 int j;
14564
14565 sta = t->state->out->out;
14566 if (utf_iscomposing(sta->c)) {
14567 // Only match composing character(s), ignore base
14568 // character. Used for ".{composing}" and "{composing}"
14569 // (no preceding character).
14570 len += utf_char2len(mc);
14571 }
14572 if (rex.reg_icombine && len == 0) {
14573 // If \Z was present, then ignore composing characters.
14574 // When ignoring the base character this always matches.
14575 if (sta->c != curc) {
14576 result = FAIL0;
14577 } else {
14578 result = OK1;
14579 }
14580 while (sta->c != NFA_END_COMPOSING) {
14581 sta = sta->out;
14582 }
14583 }
14584 // Check base character matches first, unless ignored.
14585 else if (len > 0 || mc == sta->c) {
14586 if (len == 0) {
14587 len += utf_char2len(mc);
14588 sta = sta->out;
14589 }
14590
14591 // We don't care about the order of composing characters.
14592 // Get them into cchars[] first.
14593 while (len < clen) {
14594 mc = utf_ptr2char((char *)rex.input + len);
14595 cchars[ccount++] = mc;
14596 len += utf_char2len(mc);
14597 if (ccount == MAX_MCO6) {
14598 break;
14599 }
14600 }
14601
14602 // Check that each composing char in the pattern matches a
14603 // composing char in the text. We do not check if all
14604 // composing chars are matched.
14605 result = OK1;
14606 while (sta->c != NFA_END_COMPOSING) {
14607 for (j = 0; j < ccount; j++) {
14608 if (cchars[j] == sta->c) {
14609 break;
14610 }
14611 }
14612 if (j == ccount) {
14613 result = FAIL0;
14614 break;
14615 }
14616 sta = sta->out;
14617 }
14618 } else {
14619 result = FAIL0;
14620 }
14621
14622 if (t->state->out->out1->c == NFA_END_COMPOSING) {
14623 end = t->state->out->out1;
14624 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(end);
14625 }
14626 break;
14627 }
14628 if (state->c == NFA_END_COLL) {
14629 result = !result_if_matched;
14630 break;
14631 }
14632 if (state->c == NFA_RANGE_MIN) {
14633 c1 = state->val;
14634 state = state->out; // advance to NFA_RANGE_MAX
14635 c2 = state->val;
14636#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
14637 fprintf(log_fd, "NFA_RANGE_MIN curc=%d c1=%d c2=%d\n",
14638 curc, c1, c2);
14639#endif
14640 if (curc >= c1 && curc <= c2) {
14641 result = result_if_matched;
14642 break;
14643 }
14644 if (rex.reg_ic) {
14645 int curc_low = utf_fold(curc);
14646 int done = false0;
14647
14648 for (; c1 <= c2; c1++) {
14649 if (utf_fold(c1) == curc_low) {
14650 result = result_if_matched;
14651 done = true1;
14652 break;
14653 }
14654 }
14655 if (done) {
14656 break;
14657 }
14658 }
14659 } else if (state->c < 0 ? check_char_class(state->c, curc)
14660 : (curc == state->c
14661 || (rex.reg_ic
14662 && utf_fold(curc) == utf_fold(state->c)))) {
14663 result = result_if_matched;
14664 break;
14665 }
14666 state = state->out;
14667 }
14668 if (result) {
14669 // next state is in out of the NFA_END_COLL, out1 of
14670 // START points to the END state
14671 add_state = t->state->out1->out;
14672 add_off = clen;
14673 }
14674 break;
14675 }
14676
14677 case NFA_ANY:
14678 // Any char except '\0', (end of input) does not match.
14679 if (curc > 0) {
14680 add_state = t->state->out;
14681 add_off = clen;
14682 }
14683 break;
14684
14685 case NFA_ANY_COMPOSING:
14686 // On a composing character skip over it. Otherwise do
14687 // nothing. Always matches.
14688 if (utf_iscomposing(curc)) {
14689 add_off = clen;
14690 } else {
14691 add_here = true1;
14692 add_off = 0;
14693 }
14694 add_state = t->state->out;
14695 break;
14696
14697 // Character classes like \a for alpha, \d for digit etc.
14698 case NFA_IDENT: // \i
14699 result = vim_isIDc(curc);
14700 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14701 break;
14702
14703 case NFA_SIDENT: // \I
14704 result = !ascii_isdigit(curc) && vim_isIDc(curc);
14705 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14706 break;
14707
14708 case NFA_KWORD: // \k
14709 result = vim_iswordp_buf((char *)rex.input, rex.reg_buf);
14710 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14711 break;
14712
14713 case NFA_SKWORD: // \K
14714 result = !ascii_isdigit(curc)
14715 && vim_iswordp_buf((char *)rex.input, rex.reg_buf);
14716 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14717 break;
14718
14719 case NFA_FNAME: // \f
14720 result = vim_isfilec(curc);
14721 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14722 break;
14723
14724 case NFA_SFNAME: // \F
14725 result = !ascii_isdigit(curc) && vim_isfilec(curc);
14726 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14727 break;
14728
14729 case NFA_PRINT: // \p
14730 result = vim_isprintc(utf_ptr2char((char *)rex.input));
14731 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14732 break;
14733
14734 case NFA_SPRINT: // \P
14735 result = !ascii_isdigit(curc) && vim_isprintc(utf_ptr2char((char *)rex.input));
14736 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14737 break;
14738
14739 case NFA_WHITE: // \s
14740 result = ascii_iswhite(curc);
14741 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14742 break;
14743
14744 case NFA_NWHITE: // \S
14745 result = curc != NUL'\000' && !ascii_iswhite(curc);
14746 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14747 break;
14748
14749 case NFA_DIGIT: // \d
14750 result = ri_digit(curc)((curc) < 0x100 && (class_tab[curc] & 0x01));
14751 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14752 break;
14753
14754 case NFA_NDIGIT: // \D
14755 result = curc != NUL'\000' && !ri_digit(curc)((curc) < 0x100 && (class_tab[curc] & 0x01));
14756 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14757 break;
14758
14759 case NFA_HEX: // \x
14760 result = ri_hex(curc)((curc) < 0x100 && (class_tab[curc] & 0x02));
14761 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14762 break;
14763
14764 case NFA_NHEX: // \X
14765 result = curc != NUL'\000' && !ri_hex(curc)((curc) < 0x100 && (class_tab[curc] & 0x02));
14766 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14767 break;
14768
14769 case NFA_OCTAL: // \o
14770 result = ri_octal(curc)((curc) < 0x100 && (class_tab[curc] & 0x04));
14771 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14772 break;
14773
14774 case NFA_NOCTAL: // \O
14775 result = curc != NUL'\000' && !ri_octal(curc)((curc) < 0x100 && (class_tab[curc] & 0x04));
14776 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14777 break;
14778
14779 case NFA_WORD: // \w
14780 result = ri_word(curc)((curc) < 0x100 && (class_tab[curc] & 0x08));
14781 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14782 break;
14783
14784 case NFA_NWORD: // \W
14785 result = curc != NUL'\000' && !ri_word(curc)((curc) < 0x100 && (class_tab[curc] & 0x08));
14786 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14787 break;
14788
14789 case NFA_HEAD: // \h
14790 result = ri_head(curc)((curc) < 0x100 && (class_tab[curc] & 0x10));
14791 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14792 break;
14793
14794 case NFA_NHEAD: // \H
14795 result = curc != NUL'\000' && !ri_head(curc)((curc) < 0x100 && (class_tab[curc] & 0x10));
14796 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14797 break;
14798
14799 case NFA_ALPHA: // \a
14800 result = ri_alpha(curc)((curc) < 0x100 && (class_tab[curc] & 0x20));
14801 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14802 break;
14803
14804 case NFA_NALPHA: // \A
14805 result = curc != NUL'\000' && !ri_alpha(curc)((curc) < 0x100 && (class_tab[curc] & 0x20));
14806 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14807 break;
14808
14809 case NFA_LOWER: // \l
14810 result = ri_lower(curc)((curc) < 0x100 && (class_tab[curc] & 0x40));
14811 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14812 break;
14813
14814 case NFA_NLOWER: // \L
14815 result = curc != NUL'\000' && !ri_lower(curc)((curc) < 0x100 && (class_tab[curc] & 0x40));
14816 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14817 break;
14818
14819 case NFA_UPPER: // \u
14820 result = ri_upper(curc)((curc) < 0x100 && (class_tab[curc] & 0x80));
14821 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14822 break;
14823
14824 case NFA_NUPPER: // \U
14825 result = curc != NUL'\000' && !ri_upper(curc)((curc) < 0x100 && (class_tab[curc] & 0x80));
14826 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14827 break;
14828
14829 case NFA_LOWER_IC: // [a-z]
14830 result = ri_lower(curc)((curc) < 0x100 && (class_tab[curc] & 0x40)) || (rex.reg_ic && ri_upper(curc)((curc) < 0x100 && (class_tab[curc] & 0x80)));
14831 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14832 break;
14833
14834 case NFA_NLOWER_IC: // [^a-z]
14835 result = curc != NUL'\000'
14836 && !(ri_lower(curc)((curc) < 0x100 && (class_tab[curc] & 0x40)) || (rex.reg_ic && ri_upper(curc)((curc) < 0x100 && (class_tab[curc] & 0x80))));
14837 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14838 break;
14839
14840 case NFA_UPPER_IC: // [A-Z]
14841 result = ri_upper(curc)((curc) < 0x100 && (class_tab[curc] & 0x80)) || (rex.reg_ic && ri_lower(curc)((curc) < 0x100 && (class_tab[curc] & 0x40)));
14842 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14843 break;
14844
14845 case NFA_NUPPER_IC: // [^A-Z]
14846 result = curc != NUL'\000'
14847 && !(ri_upper(curc)((curc) < 0x100 && (class_tab[curc] & 0x80)) || (rex.reg_ic && ri_lower(curc)((curc) < 0x100 && (class_tab[curc] & 0x40))));
14848 ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
14849 break;
14850
14851 case NFA_BACKREF1:
14852 case NFA_BACKREF2:
14853 case NFA_BACKREF3:
14854 case NFA_BACKREF4:
14855 case NFA_BACKREF5:
14856 case NFA_BACKREF6:
14857 case NFA_BACKREF7:
14858 case NFA_BACKREF8:
14859 case NFA_BACKREF9:
14860 case NFA_ZREF1:
14861 case NFA_ZREF2:
14862 case NFA_ZREF3:
14863 case NFA_ZREF4:
14864 case NFA_ZREF5:
14865 case NFA_ZREF6:
14866 case NFA_ZREF7:
14867 case NFA_ZREF8:
14868 case NFA_ZREF9:
14869 // \1 .. \9 \z1 .. \z9
14870 {
14871 int subidx;
14872 int bytelen;
14873
14874 if (t->state->c <= NFA_BACKREF9) {
14875 subidx = t->state->c - NFA_BACKREF1 + 1;
14876 result = match_backref(&t->subs.norm, subidx, &bytelen);
14877 } else {
14878 subidx = t->state->c - NFA_ZREF1 + 1;
14879 result = match_zref(subidx, &bytelen);
14880 }
14881
14882 if (result) {
14883 if (bytelen == 0) {
14884 // empty match always works, output of NFA_SKIP to be
14885 // used next
14886 add_here = true1;
14887 add_state = t->state->out->out;
14888 } else if (bytelen <= clen) {
14889 // match current character, jump ahead to out of
14890 // NFA_SKIP
14891 add_state = t->state->out->out;
14892 add_off = clen;
14893 } else {
14894 // skip over the matched characters, set character
14895 // count in NFA_SKIP
14896 add_state = t->state->out;
14897 add_off = bytelen;
14898 add_count = bytelen - clen;
14899 }
14900 }
14901 break;
14902 }
14903 case NFA_SKIP:
14904 // character of previous matching \1 .. \9 or \@>
14905 if (t->count - clen <= 0) {
14906 // end of match, go to what follows
14907 add_state = t->state->out;
14908 add_off = clen;
14909 } else {
14910 // add state again with decremented count
14911 add_state = t->state;
14912 add_off = 0;
14913 add_count = t->count - clen;
14914 }
14915 break;
14916

15139 fprintf(log_fd, "\n");

15144 if (result != (pim->state->c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_NEG

15148 || pim->state->c
