15152 if (rex.nfa_has_zsubexpr) {
15153 copy_sub_off(&t->subs.synt, &pim->subs.synt);
15154 }
15155 } else {
15156 // look-behind match failed, don't add the state
15157 continue;
15158 }
15159
15160 // Postponed invisible match was handled, don't add it to
15161 // following states.
15162 pim = NULL((void*)0);
15163 }
15164
15165 // If "pim" points into l->t it will become invalid when
15166 // adding the state causes the list to be reallocated. Make a
15167 // local copy to avoid that.
15168 if (pim == &t->pim) {
15169 copy_pim(&pim_copy, pim);
15170 pim = &pim_copy;
15171 }
15172
15173 if (add_here) {
15174 r = addstate_here(thislist, add_state, &t->subs, pim, &listidx);
15175 } else {
15176 r = addstate(nextlist, add_state, &t->subs, pim, add_off);
15177 if (add_count > 0) {
15178 nextlist->t[nextlist->n - 1].count = add_count;
15179 }
15180 }
15181 if (r == NULL((void*)0)) {
15182 nfa_match = NFA_TOO_EXPENSIVE;
15183 goto theend;
15184 }
15185 }
15186 } // for (thislist = thislist; thislist->state; thislist++)
15187
15188 // Look for the start of a match in the current position by adding the
15189 // start state to the list of states.
15190 // The first found match is the leftmost one, thus the order of states
15191 // matters!
15192 // Do not add the start state in recursive calls of nfa_regmatch(),
15193 // because recursive calls should only start in the first position.
15194 // Unless "nfa_endp" is not NULL, then we match the end position.
15195 // Also don't start a match past the first line.
15196 if (!nfa_match
15197 && ((toplevel
15198 && rex.lnum == 0
15199 && clen != 0
15200 && (rex.reg_maxcol == 0
15201 || (colnr_T)(rex.input - rex.line) < rex.reg_maxcol))
15202 || (nfa_endp != NULL((void*)0)
15203 && (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))
15204 ? (rex.lnum < nfa_endp->se_u.pos.lnum
15205 || (rex.lnum == nfa_endp->se_u.pos.lnum
15206 && (int)(rex.input - rex.line)
15207 < nfa_endp->se_u.pos.col))
15208 : rex.input < nfa_endp->se_u.ptr)))) {
15209#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
15210 fprintf(log_fd, "(---) STARTSTATE\n");
15211#endif
15212 // Inline optimized code for addstate() if we know the state is
15213 // the first MOPEN.
15214 if (toplevel) {
15215 int add = true1;
15216
15217 if (prog->regstart != NUL'\000' && clen != 0) {
15218 if (nextlist->n == 0) {
15219 colnr_T col = (colnr_T)(rex.input - rex.line) + clen;
15220
15221 // Nextlist is empty, we can skip ahead to the
15222 // character that must appear at the start.
15223 if (skip_to_start(prog->regstart, &col) == FAIL0) {
15224 break;
15225 }
15226#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
15227 fprintf(log_fd, " Skipping ahead %d bytes to regstart\n",
15228 col - ((colnr_T)(rex.input - rex.line) + clen));
15229#endif
15230 rex.input = rex.line + col - clen;
15231 } else {
15232 // Checking if the required start character matches is
15233 // cheaper than adding a state that won't match.
15234 const int c = utf_ptr2char((char *)rex.input + clen);
15235 if (c != prog->regstart
15236 && (!rex.reg_ic
15237 || utf_fold(c) != utf_fold(prog->regstart))) {
15238#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
15239 fprintf(log_fd,
15240 " Skipping start state, regstart does not match\n");
15241#endif
15242 add = false0;
15243 }
15244 }
15245 }
15246
15247 if (add) {
15248 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
15249 m->norm.list.multi[0].start_col =
15250 (colnr_T)(rex.input - rex.line) + clen;
15251 m->norm.orig_start_col =
15252 m->norm.list.multi[0].start_col;
15253 } else {
15254 m->norm.list.line[0].start = rex.input + clen;
15255 }
15256 if (addstate(nextlist, start->out, m, NULL((void*)0), clen) == NULL((void*)0)) {
15257 nfa_match = NFA_TOO_EXPENSIVE;
15258 goto theend;
15259 }
15260 }
15261 } else {
15262 if (addstate(nextlist, start, m, NULL((void*)0), clen) == NULL((void*)0)) {
15263 nfa_match = NFA_TOO_EXPENSIVE;
15264 goto theend;
15265 }
15266 }
15267 }
15268
15269#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
15270 fprintf(log_fd, ">>> Thislist had %d states available: ", thislist->n);
15271 {
15272 int i;
15273
15274 for (i = 0; i < thislist->n; i++) {
15275 fprintf(log_fd, "%d ", abs(thislist->t[i].state->id));
15276 }
15277 }
15278 fprintf(log_fd, "\n");
15279#endif
15280
15281nextchar:
15282 // Advance to the next character, or advance to the next line, or
15283 // finish.
15284 if (clen != 0) {
15285 rex.input += clen;
15286 } else if (go_to_nextline || (nfa_endp != NULL((void*)0) && REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))
15287 && rex.lnum < nfa_endp->se_u.pos.lnum)) {
15288 reg_nextline();
15289 } else {
15290 break;
15291 }
15292
15293 // Allow interrupting with CTRL-C.
15294 reg_breakcheck();
15295 if (got_int) {
15296 break;
15297 }
15298 // Check for timeout once every twenty times to avoid overhead.
15299 if (nfa_time_limit != NULL((void*)0) && ++nfa_time_count == 20) {
15300 nfa_time_count = 0;
15301 if (nfa_did_time_out()) {
15302 break;
15303 }
15304 }
15305 }
15306
15307#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
15308 if (log_fd != stderrstderr) {
15309 fclose(log_fd);
15310 }
15311 log_fd = NULL((void*)0);
15312#endif
15313
15314theend:
15315 // Free memory
15316 xfree(list[0].t);
15317 xfree(list[1].t);
15318 xfree(listids);
15319#undef ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH
15320#ifdef NFA_REGEXP_DEBUG_LOG
15321 fclose(debug);
15322#endif
15323
15324 return nfa_match;
15325}
15326
15327/// Try match of "prog" with at rex.line["col"].
15328///
15329/// @param tm timeout limit or NULL
15330/// @param timed_out flag set on timeout or NULL
15331///
15332/// @return <= 0 for failure, number of lines contained in the match otherwise.
15333static int nfa_regtry(nfa_regprog_T *prog, colnr_T col, proftime_T *tm, int *timed_out)
15334{
15335 int i;
15336 regsubs_T subs, m;
15337 nfa_state_T *start = prog->start;
15338#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
15339 FILE *f;
15340#endif
15341
15342 rex.input = rex.line + col;
15343 nfa_time_limit = tm;
15344 nfa_timed_out = timed_out;
15345 nfa_time_count = 0;
15346
15347#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
15348 f = fopen(NFA_REGEXP_RUN_LOG, "a");
15349 if (f != NULL((void*)0)) {
15350 fprintf(f,
15351 "\n\n\t=======================================================\n");
15352# ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
15353 fprintf(f, "\tRegexp is \"%s\"\n", nfa_regengine.expr);
15354# endif
15355 fprintf(f, "\tInput text is \"%s\" \n", rex.input);
15356 fprintf(f, "\t=======================================================\n\n");
15357 nfa_print_state(f, start);
15358 fprintf(f, "\n\n");
15359 fclose(f);
15360 } else {
15361 emsg("Could not open temporary log file for writing");
15362 }
15363#endif
15364
15365 clear_sub(&subs.norm);
15366 clear_sub(&m.norm);
15367 clear_sub(&subs.synt);
15368 clear_sub(&m.synt);
15369
15370 int result = nfa_regmatch(prog, start, &subs, &m);
15371 if (!result) {
15372 return 0;
15373 } else if (result == NFA_TOO_EXPENSIVE) {
15374 return result;
15375 }
15376
15377 cleanup_subexpr();
15378 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
15379 for (i = 0; i < subs.norm.in_use; i++) {
15380 rex.reg_startpos[i].lnum = subs.norm.list.multi[i].start_lnum;
15381 rex.reg_startpos[i].col = subs.norm.list.multi[i].start_col;
15382
15383 rex.reg_endpos[i].lnum = subs.norm.list.multi[i].end_lnum;
15384 rex.reg_endpos[i].col = subs.norm.list.multi[i].end_col;
15385 }
15386 if (rex.reg_mmatch != NULL((void*)0)) {
15387 rex.reg_mmatch->rmm_matchcol = subs.norm.orig_start_col;
15388 }
15389
15390 if (rex.reg_startpos[0].lnum < 0) {
15391 rex.reg_startpos[0].lnum = 0;
15392 rex.reg_startpos[0].col = col;
15393 }
15394 if (rex.reg_endpos[0].lnum < 0) {
15395 // pattern has a \ze but it didn't match, use current end
15396 rex.reg_endpos[0].lnum = rex.lnum;
15397 rex.reg_endpos[0].col = (int)(rex.input - rex.line);
15398 } else {
15399 // Use line number of "\ze".
15400 rex.lnum = rex.reg_endpos[0].lnum;
15401 }
15402 } else {
15403 for (i = 0; i < subs.norm.in_use; i++) {
15404 rex.reg_startp[i] = subs.norm.list.line[i].start;
15405 rex.reg_endp[i] = subs.norm.list.line[i].end;
15406 }
15407
15408 if (rex.reg_startp[0] == NULL((void*)0)) {
15409 rex.reg_startp[0] = rex.line + col;
15410 }
15411 if (rex.reg_endp[0] == NULL((void*)0)) {
15412 rex.reg_endp[0] = rex.input;
15413 }
15414 }
15415
15416 // Package any found \z(...\) matches for export. Default is none.
15417 unref_extmatch(re_extmatch_out);
15418 re_extmatch_out = NULL((void*)0);
15419
15420 if (prog->reghasz == REX_SET1) {
15421 cleanup_zsubexpr();
15422 re_extmatch_out = make_extmatch();
15423 // Loop over \z1, \z2, etc. There is no \z0.
15424 for (i = 1; i < subs.synt.in_use; i++) {
15425 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
15426 struct multipos *mpos = &subs.synt.list.multi[i];
15427
15428 // Only accept single line matches that are valid.
15429 if (mpos->start_lnum >= 0
15430 && mpos->start_lnum == mpos->end_lnum
15431 && mpos->end_col >= mpos->start_col) {
15432 re_extmatch_out->matches[i] =
15433 (uint8_t *)xstrnsave(reg_getline(mpos->start_lnum) + mpos->start_col,
15434 (size_t)(mpos->end_col - mpos->start_col));
15435 }
15436 } else {
15437 struct linepos *lpos = &subs.synt.list.line[i];
15438
15439 if (lpos->start != NULL((void*)0) && lpos->end != NULL((void*)0)) {
15440 re_extmatch_out->matches[i] =
15441 (uint8_t *)xstrnsave((char *)lpos->start, (size_t)(lpos->end - lpos->start));
15442 }
15443 }
15444 }
15445 }
15446
15447 return 1 + rex.lnum;
15448}
15449
15450/// Match a regexp against a string ("line" points to the string) or multiple
15451/// lines (if "line" is NULL, use reg_getline()).
15452///
15453/// @param line String in which to search or NULL
15454/// @param startcol Column to start looking for match
15455/// @param tm Timeout limit or NULL
15456/// @param timed_out Flag set on timeout or NULL
15457///
15458/// @return <= 0 if there is no match and number of lines contained in the
15459/// match otherwise.
15460static int nfa_regexec_both(uint8_t *line, colnr_T startcol, proftime_T *tm, int *timed_out)
15461{
15462 nfa_regprog_T *prog;
15463 int retval = 0;
15464 colnr_T col = startcol;
15465
15466 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
15467 prog = (nfa_regprog_T *)rex.reg_mmatch->regprog;
15468 line = (uint8_t *)reg_getline(0); // relative to the cursor
15469 rex.reg_startpos = rex.reg_mmatch->startpos;
15470 rex.reg_endpos = rex.reg_mmatch->endpos;
15471 } else {
15472 prog = (nfa_regprog_T *)rex.reg_match->regprog;
15473 rex.reg_startp = (uint8_t **)rex.reg_match->startp;
15474 rex.reg_endp = (uint8_t **)rex.reg_match->endp;
15475 }
15476
15477 // Be paranoid...
15478 if (prog == NULL((void*)0) || line == NULL((void*)0)) {
15479 iemsg(_(e_null)gettext(e_null));
15480 goto theend;
15481 }
15482
15483 // If pattern contains "\c" or "\C": overrule value of rex.reg_ic
15484 if (prog->regflags & RF_ICASE1) {
15485 rex.reg_ic = true1;
15486 } else if (prog->regflags & RF_NOICASE2) {
15487 rex.reg_ic = false0;
15488 }
15489
15490 // If pattern contains "\Z" overrule value of rex.reg_icombine
15491 if (prog->regflags & RF_ICOMBINE8) {
15492 rex.reg_icombine = true1;
15493 }
15494
15495 rex.line = line;
15496 rex.lnum = 0; // relative to line
15497
15498 rex.nfa_has_zend = prog->has_zend;
15499 rex.nfa_has_backref = prog->has_backref;
15500 rex.nfa_nsubexpr = prog->nsubexp;
15501 rex.nfa_listid = 1;
15502 rex.nfa_alt_listid = 2;
15503#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
15504 nfa_regengine.expr = prog->pattern;
15505#endif
15506
15507 if (prog->reganch && col > 0) {
15508 return 0L;
15509 }
15510
15511 rex.need_clear_subexpr = true1;
15512 // Clear the external match subpointers if necessary.
15513 if (prog->reghasz == REX_SET1) {
15514 rex.nfa_has_zsubexpr = true1;
15515 rex.need_clear_zsubexpr = true1;
15516 } else {
15517 rex.nfa_has_zsubexpr = false0;
15518 rex.need_clear_zsubexpr = false0;
15519 }
15520
15521 if (prog->regstart != NUL'\000') {
15522 // Skip ahead until a character we know the match must start with.
15523 // When there is none there is no match.
15524 if (skip_to_start(prog->regstart, &col) == FAIL0) {
15525 return 0L;
15526 }
15527
15528 // If match_text is set it contains the full text that must match.
15529 // Nothing else to try. Doesn't handle combining chars well.
15530 if (prog->match_text != NULL((void*)0) && !rex.reg_icombine) {
15531 retval = find_match_text(&col, prog->regstart, prog->match_text);
15532 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
15533 rex.reg_mmatch->rmm_matchcol = col;
15534 } else {
15535 rex.reg_match->rm_matchcol = col;
15536 }
15537 return retval;
15538 }
15539 }
15540
15541 // If the start column is past the maximum column: no need to try.
15542 if (rex.reg_maxcol > 0 && col >= rex.reg_maxcol) {
15543 goto theend;
15544 }
15545
15546 // Set the "nstate" used by nfa_regcomp() to zero to trigger an error when
15547 // it's accidentally used during execution.
15548 nstate = 0;
15549 for (int i = 0; i < prog->nstate; i++) {
15550 prog->state[i].id = i;
15551 prog->state[i].lastlist[0] = 0;
15552 prog->state[i].lastlist[1] = 0;
15553 }
15554
15555 retval = nfa_regtry(prog, col, tm, timed_out);
15556
15557#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
15558 nfa_regengine.expr = NULL((void*)0);
15559#endif
15560
15561theend:
15562 if (retval > 0) {
15563 // Make sure the end is never before the start. Can happen when \zs and
15564 // \ze are used.
15565 if (REG_MULTI(rex.reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
15566 const lpos_T *const start = &rex.reg_mmatch->startpos[0];
15567 const lpos_T *const end = &rex.reg_mmatch->endpos[0];
15568
15569 if (end->lnum < start->lnum
15570 || (end->lnum == start->lnum && end->col < start->col)) {
15571 rex.reg_mmatch->endpos[0] = rex.reg_mmatch->startpos[0];
15572 }
15573 } else {
15574 if (rex.reg_match->endp[0] < rex.reg_match->startp[0]) {
15575 rex.reg_match->endp[0] = rex.reg_match->startp[0];
15576 }
15577
15578 // startpos[0] may be set by "\zs", also return the column where
15579 // the whole pattern matched.
15580 rex.reg_match->rm_matchcol = col;
15581 }
15582 }
15583
15584 return retval;
15585}
15586
15587// Compile a regular expression into internal code for the NFA matcher.
15588// Returns the program in allocated space. Returns NULL for an error.
15589static regprog_T *nfa_regcomp(uint8_t *expr, int re_flags)
15590{
15591 nfa_regprog_T *prog = NULL((void*)0);
15592 int *postfix;
15593
15594 if (expr == NULL((void*)0)) {
15595 return NULL((void*)0);
15596 }
15597
15598#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
15599 nfa_regengine.expr = expr;
15600#endif
15601 nfa_re_flags = re_flags;
15602
15603 init_class_tab();
15604
15605 nfa_regcomp_start(expr, re_flags);
15606
15607 // Build postfix form of the regexp. Needed to build the NFA
15608 // (and count its size).
15609 postfix = re2post();
15610 if (postfix == NULL((void*)0)) {
15611 goto fail; // Cascaded (syntax?) error
15612 }
15613
15614 // In order to build the NFA, we parse the input regexp twice:
15615 // 1. first pass to count size (so we can allocate space)
15616 // 2. second to emit code
15617#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
15618 {
15619 FILE *f = fopen(NFA_REGEXP_RUN_LOG, "a");
15620
15621 if (f != NULL((void*)0)) {
15622 fprintf(f,
15623 "\n*****************************\n\n\n\n\t"
15624 "Compiling regexp \"%s\"... hold on !\n",
15625 expr);
15626 fclose(f);
15627 }
15628 }
15629#endif
15630
15631 // PASS 1
15632 // Count number of NFA states in "nstate". Do not build the NFA.
15633 post2nfa(postfix, post_ptr, true1);
15634
15635 // allocate the regprog with space for the compiled regexp
15636 size_t prog_size = offsetof(nfa_regprog_T, state)__builtin_offsetof(nfa_regprog_T, state) + sizeof(nfa_state_T) * (size_t)nstate;
15637 prog = xmalloc(prog_size);
15638 state_ptr = prog->state;
15639 prog->re_in_use = false0;
15640
15641 // PASS 2
15642 // Build the NFA
15643 prog->start = post2nfa(postfix, post_ptr, false0);
15644 if (prog->start == NULL((void*)0)) {
15645 goto fail;
15646 }
15647 prog->regflags = regflags;
15648 prog->engine = &nfa_regengine;
15649 prog->nstate = nstate;
15650 prog->has_zend = rex.nfa_has_zend;
15651 prog->has_backref = rex.nfa_has_backref;
15652 prog->nsubexp = regnpar;
15653
15654 nfa_postprocess(prog);
15655
15656 prog->reganch = nfa_get_reganch(prog->start, 0);
15657 prog->regstart = nfa_get_regstart(prog->start, 0);
15658 prog->match_text = nfa_get_match_text(prog->start);
15659
15660#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
15661 nfa_postfix_dump(expr, OK1);
15662 nfa_dump(prog);
15663#endif
15664 // Remember whether this pattern has any \z specials in it.
15665 prog->reghasz = re_has_z;
15666 prog->pattern = xstrdup((char *)expr);
15667#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
15668 nfa_regengine.expr = NULL((void*)0);
15669#endif
15670
15671out:
15672 xfree(post_start);
15673 post_start = post_ptr = post_end = NULL((void*)0);
15674 state_ptr = NULL((void*)0);
15675 return (regprog_T *)prog;
15676
15677fail:
15678 XFREE_CLEAR(prog)do { void **ptr_ = (void **)&(prog); xfree(*ptr_); *ptr_ =
((void*)0); (void)(*ptr_); } while (0);
15679#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
15680 nfa_postfix_dump(expr, FAIL0);
15681 nfa_regengine.expr = NULL((void*)0);
15682#endif
15683 goto out;
15684}
15685
15686// Free a compiled regexp program, returned by nfa_regcomp().
15687static void nfa_regfree(regprog_T *prog)
15688{
15689 if (prog == NULL((void*)0)) {
15690 return;
15691 }
15692
15693 xfree(((nfa_regprog_T *)prog)->match_text);
15694 xfree(((nfa_regprog_T *)prog)->pattern);
15695 xfree(prog);
15696}
15697
15698/// Match a regexp against a string.
15699/// "rmp->regprog" is a compiled regexp as returned by nfa_regcomp().
15700/// Uses curbuf for line count and 'iskeyword'.
15701/// If "line_lbr" is true, consider a "\n" in "line" to be a line break.
15702///
15703/// @param line string to match against
15704/// @param col column to start looking for match
15705///
15706/// @return <= 0 for failure, number of lines contained in the match otherwise.
15707static int nfa_regexec_nl(regmatch_T *rmp, uint8_t *line, colnr_T col, bool_Bool line_lbr)
15708{
15709 rex.reg_match = rmp;
15710 rex.reg_mmatch = NULL((void*)0);
15711 rex.reg_maxline = 0;
15712 rex.reg_line_lbr = line_lbr;
15713 rex.reg_buf = curbuf;
15714 rex.reg_win = NULL((void*)0);
15715 rex.reg_ic = rmp->rm_ic;
15716 rex.reg_icombine = false0;
15717 rex.reg_nobreak = rmp->regprog->re_flags & RE_NOBREAK16;
15718 rex.reg_maxcol = 0;
15719 return nfa_regexec_both(line, col, NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0));
15720}
15721
15722/// Matches a regexp against multiple lines.
15723/// "rmp->regprog" is a compiled regexp as returned by vim_regcomp().
15724/// Uses curbuf for line count and 'iskeyword'.
15725///
15726/// @param win Window in which to search or NULL
15727/// @param buf Buffer in which to search
15728/// @param lnum Number of line to start looking for match
15729/// @param col Column to start looking for match
15730/// @param tm Timeout limit or NULL
15731/// @param timed_out Flag set on timeout or NULL
15732///
15733/// @return <= 0 if there is no match and number of lines contained in the match
15734/// otherwise.
15735///
15736/// @note The body is the same as bt_regexec() except for nfa_regexec_both()
15737///
15738/// @warning
15739/// Match may actually be in another line. e.g.:
15740/// when r.e. is \nc, cursor is at 'a' and the text buffer looks like
15741///
15742/// @par
15743///
15744/// +-------------------------+
15745/// |a |
15746/// |b |
15747/// |c |
15748/// | |
15749/// +-------------------------+
15750///
15751/// @par
15752/// then nfa_regexec_multi() returns 3. while the original vim_regexec_multi()
15753/// returns 0 and a second call at line 2 will return 2.
15754///
15755/// @par
15756/// FIXME if this behavior is not compatible.
15757static int nfa_regexec_multi(regmmatch_T *rmp, win_T *win, buf_T *buf, linenr_T lnum, colnr_T col,
15758 proftime_T *tm, int *timed_out)
15759{
15760 init_regexec_multi(rmp, win, buf, lnum);
15761 return nfa_regexec_both(NULL((void*)0), col, tm, timed_out);
15762}
15763// }}}1
15764
15765static regengine_T bt_regengine = {
15766 bt_regcomp,
15767 bt_regfree,
15768 bt_regexec_nl,
15769 bt_regexec_multi,
15770#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
15771 "",
15772#endif
15773};
15774
15775static regengine_T nfa_regengine = {
15776 nfa_regcomp,
15777 nfa_regfree,
15778 nfa_regexec_nl,
15779 nfa_regexec_multi,
15780#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
15781 "",
15782#endif
15783};
15784
15785// Which regexp engine to use? Needed for vim_regcomp().
15786// Must match with 'regexpengine'.
15787static int regexp_engine = 0;
15788
15789#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
15790static uint8_t regname[][30] = {
15791 "AUTOMATIC Regexp Engine",
15792 "BACKTRACKING Regexp Engine",
15793 "NFA Regexp Engine"
15794};
15795#endif
15796
15797// Compile a regular expression into internal code.
15798// Returns the program in allocated memory.
15799// Use vim_regfree() to free the memory.
15800// Returns NULL for an error.
15801regprog_T *vim_regcomp(const char *expr_arg, int re_flags)
15802{
15803 regprog_T *prog = NULL((void*)0);
15804 const char *expr = expr_arg;
15805
15806 regexp_engine = (int)p_re;
15807
15808 // Check for prefix "\%#=", that sets the regexp engine
15809 if (strncmp(expr, "\\%#=", 4) == 0) {
15810 int newengine = expr[4] - '0';
15811
15812 if (newengine == AUTOMATIC_ENGINE
15813 || newengine == BACKTRACKING_ENGINE
15814 || newengine == NFA_ENGINE) {
15815 regexp_engine = expr[4] - '0';
15816 expr += 5;
15817#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
15818 smsg(0, "New regexp mode selected (%d): %s",
15819 regexp_engine,
15820 regname[newengine]);
15821#endif
15822 } else {
15823 emsg(_("E864: \\%#= can only be followed by 0, 1, or 2. The automatic engine will be used ")gettext("E864: \\%#= can only be followed by 0, 1, or 2. The automatic engine will be used "
));
15824 regexp_engine = AUTOMATIC_ENGINE;
15825 }
15826 }
15827#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
15828 bt_regengine.expr = expr;
15829 nfa_regengine.expr = expr;
15830#endif
15831 // reg_iswordc() uses rex.reg_buf
15832 rex.reg_buf = curbuf;
15833
15834 //
15835 // First try the NFA engine, unless backtracking was requested.
15836 //
15837 const int called_emsg_before = called_emsg;
15838 if (regexp_engine != BACKTRACKING_ENGINE) {
15839 prog = nfa_regengine.regcomp((uint8_t *)expr,
15840 re_flags + (regexp_engine == AUTOMATIC_ENGINE ? RE_AUTO8 : 0));
15841 } else {
15842 prog = bt_regengine.regcomp((uint8_t *)expr, re_flags);
15843 }
15844
15845 // Check for error compiling regexp with initial engine.
15846 if (prog == NULL((void*)0)) {
15847#ifdef BT_REGEXP_DEBUG_LOG
15848 // Debugging log for BT engine.
15849 if (regexp_engine != BACKTRACKING_ENGINE) {
15850 FILE *f = fopen(BT_REGEXP_DEBUG_LOG_NAME, "a");
15851 if (f) {
15852 fprintf(f, "Syntax error in \"%s\"\n", expr);
15853 fclose(f);
15854 } else {
15855 semsg("(NFA) Could not open \"%s\" to write !!!",
15856 BT_REGEXP_DEBUG_LOG_NAME);
15857 }
15858 }
15859#endif
15860 // If the NFA engine failed, try the backtracking engine. The NFA engine
15861 // also fails for patterns that it can't handle well but are still valid
15862 // patterns, thus a retry should work.
15863 // But don't try if an error message was given.
15864 if (regexp_engine == AUTOMATIC_ENGINE && called_emsg == called_emsg_before) {
15865 regexp_engine = BACKTRACKING_ENGINE;
15866 report_re_switch(expr);
15867 prog = bt_regengine.regcomp((uint8_t *)expr, re_flags);
15868 }
15869 }
15870
15871 if (prog != NULL((void*)0)) {
15872 // Store the info needed to call regcomp() again when the engine turns out
15873 // to be very slow when executing it.
15874 prog->re_engine = (unsigned)regexp_engine;
15875 prog->re_flags = (unsigned)re_flags;
15876 }
15877
15878 return prog;
15879}
15880
15881// Free a compiled regexp program, returned by vim_regcomp().
15882void vim_regfree(regprog_T *prog)
15883{
15884 if (prog != NULL((void*)0)) {
15885 prog->engine->regfree(prog);
15886 }
15887}
15888
15889#if defined(EXITFREE)
15890void free_regexp_stuff(void)
15891{
15892 ga_clear(&regstack);
15893 ga_clear(&backpos);
15894 xfree(reg_tofree);
15895 xfree(reg_prev_sub);
15896}
15897
15898#endif
15899
15900static void report_re_switch(const char *pat)
15901{
15902 if (p_verbose > 0) {
15903 verbose_enter();
15904 msg_puts(_("Switching to backtracking RE engine for pattern: ")gettext("Switching to backtracking RE engine for pattern: "));
15905 msg_puts(pat);
15906 verbose_leave();
15907 }
15908}
15909
15910/// Match a regexp against a string.
15911/// "rmp->regprog" must be a compiled regexp as returned by vim_regcomp().
15912/// Note: "rmp->regprog" may be freed and changed.
15913/// Uses curbuf for line count and 'iskeyword'.
15914/// When "nl" is true consider a "\n" in "line" to be a line break.
15915///
15916/// @param rmp
15917/// @param line the string to match against
15918/// @param col the column to start looking for match
15919/// @param nl
15920///
15921/// @return true if there is a match, false if not.
15922static bool_Bool vim_regexec_string(regmatch_T *rmp, const char *line, colnr_T col, bool_Bool nl)
15923{
15924 regexec_T rex_save;
15925 bool_Bool rex_in_use_save = rex_in_use;
15926
15927 // Cannot use the same prog recursively, it contains state.
15928 if (rmp->regprog->re_in_use) {
15929 emsg(_(e_recursive)gettext(e_recursive));
15930 return false0;
15931 }
15932 rmp->regprog->re_in_use = true1;
15933
15934 if (rex_in_use) {
15935 // Being called recursively, save the state.
15936 rex_save = rex;
15937 }
15938 rex_in_use = true1;
15939
15940 rex.reg_startp = NULL((void*)0);
15941 rex.reg_endp = NULL((void*)0);
15942 rex.reg_startpos = NULL((void*)0);
15943 rex.reg_endpos = NULL((void*)0);
15944
15945 int result = rmp->regprog->engine->regexec_nl(rmp, (uint8_t *)line, col, nl);
15946 rmp->regprog->re_in_use = false0;
15947
15948 // NFA engine aborted because it's very slow, use backtracking engine instead.
15949 if (rmp->regprog->re_engine == AUTOMATIC_ENGINE
15950 && result == NFA_TOO_EXPENSIVE) {
15951 int save_p_re = (int)p_re;
15952 int re_flags = (int)rmp->regprog->re_flags;
15953 char *pat = xstrdup(((nfa_regprog_T *)rmp->regprog)->pattern);
15954
15955 p_re = BACKTRACKING_ENGINE;
15956 vim_regfree(rmp->regprog);
15957 report_re_switch(pat);
15958 rmp->regprog = vim_regcomp(pat, re_flags);
15959 if (rmp->regprog != NULL((void*)0)) {
15960 rmp->regprog->re_in_use = true1;
15961 result = rmp->regprog->engine->regexec_nl(rmp, (uint8_t *)line, col, nl);
15962 rmp->regprog->re_in_use = false0;
15963 }
15964
15965 xfree(pat);
15966 p_re = save_p_re;
15967 }
15968
15969 rex_in_use = rex_in_use_save;
15970 if (rex_in_use) {
15971 rex = rex_save;
15972 }
15973
15974 return result > 0;
15975}
15976
15977// Note: "*prog" may be freed and changed.
15978// Return true if there is a match, false if not.
15979bool_Bool vim_regexec_prog(regprog_T **prog, bool_Bool ignore_case, const char *line, colnr_T col)
15980{
15981 regmatch_T regmatch = { .regprog = *prog, .rm_ic = ignore_case };
15982 bool_Bool r = vim_regexec_string(&regmatch, line, col, false0);
15983 *prog = regmatch.regprog;
15984 return r;
15985}
15986
15987// Note: "rmp->regprog" may be freed and changed.
15988// Return true if there is a match, false if not.
15989bool_Bool vim_regexec(regmatch_T *rmp, const char *line, colnr_T col)
15990{
15991 return vim_regexec_string(rmp, line, col, false0);
15992}
15993
15994// Like vim_regexec(), but consider a "\n" in "line" to be a line break.
15995// Note: "rmp->regprog" may be freed and changed.
15996// Return true if there is a match, false if not.
15997bool_Bool vim_regexec_nl(regmatch_T *rmp, const char *line, colnr_T col)
15998{
15999 return vim_regexec_string(rmp, line, col, true1);
16000}
16001
16002/// Match a regexp against multiple lines.
16003/// "rmp->regprog" must be a compiled regexp as returned by vim_regcomp().
16004/// Note: "rmp->regprog" may be freed and changed, even set to NULL.
16005/// Uses curbuf for line count and 'iskeyword'.
16006///
16007/// @param win window in which to search or NULL
16008/// @param buf buffer in which to search
16009/// @param lnum nr of line to start looking for match
16010/// @param col column to start looking for match
16011/// @param tm timeout limit or NULL
16012/// @param timed_out flag is set when timeout limit reached
16013///
16014/// @return zero if there is no match. Return number of lines contained in the
16015/// match otherwise.
16016int vim_regexec_multi(regmmatch_T *rmp, win_T *win, buf_T *buf, linenr_T lnum, colnr_T col,
16017 proftime_T *tm, int *timed_out)
16018 FUNC_ATTR_NONNULL_ARG(1)
16019{
16020 regexec_T rex_save;
16021 bool_Bool rex_in_use_save = rex_in_use;
16022
16023 // Cannot use the same prog recursively, it contains state.
16024 if (rmp->regprog->re_in_use) {
16025 emsg(_(e_recursive)gettext(e_recursive));
16026 return false0;
16027 }
16028 rmp->regprog->re_in_use = true1;
16029
16030 if (rex_in_use) {
16031 // Being called recursively, save the state.
16032 rex_save = rex;
16033 }
16034 rex_in_use = true1;
16035
16036 int result = rmp->regprog->engine->regexec_multi(rmp, win, buf, lnum, col, tm, timed_out);
16037 rmp->regprog->re_in_use = false0;
16038
16039 // NFA engine aborted because it's very slow, use backtracking engine instead.
16040 if (rmp->regprog->re_engine == AUTOMATIC_ENGINE
16041 && result == NFA_TOO_EXPENSIVE) {
16042 int save_p_re = (int)p_re;
16043 int re_flags = (int)rmp->regprog->re_flags;
16044 char *pat = xstrdup(((nfa_regprog_T *)rmp->regprog)->pattern);
16045
16046 p_re = BACKTRACKING_ENGINE;
16047 regprog_T *prev_prog = rmp->regprog;
16048
16049 report_re_switch(pat);
16050 // checking for \z misuse was already done when compiling for NFA,
16051 // allow all here
16052 reg_do_extmatch = REX_ALL(1 | 2);
16053 rmp->regprog = vim_regcomp(pat, re_flags);
16054 reg_do_extmatch = 0;
16055
16056 if (rmp->regprog == NULL((void*)0)) {
16057 // Somehow compiling the pattern failed now, put back the
16058 // previous one to avoid "regprog" becoming NULL.
16059 rmp->regprog = prev_prog;
16060 } else {
16061 vim_regfree(prev_prog);
16062
16063 rmp->regprog->re_in_use = true1;
16064 result = rmp->regprog->engine->regexec_multi(rmp, win, buf, lnum, col, tm, timed_out);
16065 rmp->regprog->re_in_use = false0;
16066 }
16067
16068 xfree(pat);
16069 p_re = save_p_re;
16070 }
16071
16072 rex_in_use = rex_in_use_save;
16073 if (rex_in_use) {
16074 rex = rex_save;
16075 }
16076
16077 return result <= 0 ? 0 : result;
16078}
